	(870, 'shame', 'I had promised to lend something to my mother-in-law and I forgot á\nit a couple of times.  When she asked me about it the third time, á\nI was ashamed at my absent-mindedness.'),
	(871, 'joy', 'I started a new branch of studies after having failed a former á\none.  When I got back my exam papers I was very happy to know á\nthat I almost had full marks.'),
	(872, 'fear', 'I was diving below the ice, in a cave, at a depth of 26 metres.  á\nVisibility was almost zero and the oxygen level decreased á\nthreateningly.  There were three of us divers on one safety rope.'),
	(873, 'anger', 'My mother carried on using mental pressure concerning something á\nwhich was serious and a real burden to me.'),
	(874, 'sadness', 'My grandfather died, I went to the mortuary and saw the corpse.'),
	(876, 'shame', 'As a child when I was blamed for peeing in the swimming-pool.'),
	(877, 'joy', 'My girlfriend sent me a letter with a shiny picture in it.'),
	(878, 'fear', 'I was about to begin a journey in a car with an acquaintance of á\nmine.'),
	(879, 'anger', 'On the TV news I heard that Nicaragua had complained about the á\nincreasing threat of war with the USA.'),
	(880, 'sadness', 'My girlfriend gave me the mitten (left me).'),
	(881, 'disgust', 'Watching a violent movie.'),
	(882, 'shame', 'The morning after a wild party.'),
	(883, 'joy', 'When, to my surprise, I got to know about having got "very good" á\nhigh school graduation marks.'),
	(884, 'fear', 'My grandmother was about to die, and it had the effect that at á\nnight, after having read a book, and once in bed, in perfect á\ndarkness, the fear arose that I too may suddenly die.'),
	(885, 'anger', 'When I checked my examination paper and realized that I had been á\ncareless, thoughtless, lazy and hasty so as to make unnecessary á\nmistakes concerning things I know and understand.'),
	(886, 'sadness', 'When we decided, my boyfriend and I, that we would separate, I á\nrealized that he would have wanted to continue our relationship á\nand the coming separation hurt him.'),
	(887, 'disgust', 'When an acquaintance of mine told me about the way his parents á\ntreated their sons in an unequal manner.  The most successful of á\nthem got continuous encouragement, and the youngest was not á\nencouraged and was rejected.'),
	(888, 'shame', 'I was talking to a friend of mine about our parents and á\neducation.  I said something and then realized that I did not á\nknow my friend\'s parents, their motives and education.  I felt á\nashamed at having talked about something I did not know anything á\nabout.'),
	(889, 'joy', 'I am not especially good at English, and after the high school á\ngraduation exam in English I tensely waited for the result the á\nwhole day.  In the evening, when I heard that I had done á\nexcellently, I became very happy and the anxiety vanished.  My á\nfamily was at home.'),
	(890, 'fear', 'I feared that I was pregnant.  It was not planned and I would á\nhave been compelled to have an abortion, which I would not have á\nliked at all.  Fortunately, after a week\'s anxiety, I got to know á\nthat I was not pregnant.'),
	(891, 'anger', 'A member of a religious sect tried to convert me, using really á\nevil tricks to persuade me.  After he had left, I was anxious and á\nangry for a long time. After the event, I was alone.'),
	(892, 'sadness', 'When my boyfriend wanted to leave me, I felt sad and melancholic.'),
	(893, 'disgust', 'In a film, there was an episode where they used a chain saw to á\ncut a man.  I could not look at it, but I could not avoid á\nlistening either.  I sought shelter in my boyfriend\'s arms.'),
	(894, 'shame', 'I thought I would be able to use the mangle of the house, and so á\nI did not want any help.  However, I blocked it and I had to get á\nthe janitor to help me out.  He reproached me for not having á\nfollowed the instructions'),
	(895, 'joy', 'When I got an unexpected letter from  a guy, who had been my school á\nmate.'),
	(896, 'fear', 'When my brother went to shoot wild ducks, I feared that the á\nboat would overturn and he would drown or that the gun would á\naccidentally go off.'),
	(897, 'anger', 'My father had once again told me that I should be careful and try to á\nseek admission to other places also apart from the faculty of á\nSocial Sciences at the university of Helsinki.  I was not at all á\ninterested in any other place and had no time to study for other á\nentrance exams.'),
	(898, 'sadness', 'I would have liked to go out to chat with some acquaintances, but á\nI realized that I was not wanted.  I felt hurt, disappointed, á\nlonely and deserted.'),
	(899, 'disgust', 'When an acquaintance (he was drunk) of my room-mate vomitted on the kitchen á\ncarpet.  It was past mid-night and my room-mate had just moved in, á\nthis acquaintance had helped her move in.á'),
	(900, 'shame', 'I was carried away while talking about my visits abroad and I á\ntended to boast a little, till I realized that the listener was á\namused.'),
	(901, 'joy', 'When I got 21/30 points in an exam of statistics. The result was á\nunexpected and it made me realize that statistics do not á\nsurpass my abilities, as I have sometimes thought.'),
	(902, 'fear', 'When a big angry dog put its snout on my arm and had I made one á\nmovement it would have bitten me.'),
	(903, 'anger', 'When my room-mates were watching video-tapes and prevented me á\nfrom watching the news.  The first feeling I had was that I was á\nbeing treated unfairly and then came the feeling of anger.'),
	(904, 'sadness', '[ When after a night of sleeping in another\'s arms, one wakes á\nalone and knows that the lonely arms of the night are not the á\nsame that one meets in the morning.]'),
	(905, 'disgust', 'When an unpleasant person tried to make friends with me.  A á\nsubtle, small, insignificant, grey being whose helplessness and á\nneutrality evoked the feeling of disgust in me.'),
	(906, 'shame', 'Badly chosen words to a vague acquaintance of mine made me feel á\nashamed at having given the wrong impression about what I wanted á\nto say.  Thoughtlessness.'),
	(907, 'joy', 'When my friend told me that he would come and meet me in a á\nmoment.'),
	(908, 'fear', 'My father had been drinking and I feared him when we went to bed á\nat night.'),
	(909, 'anger', 'My friends promised me that they would definitely call me to tell á\nme if they were visiting me or not.'),
	(910, 'sadness', 'A close friend of mine had not contacted me for a long time.'),
	(911, 'disgust', 'A friend of mine came to see me when he was quite drunk.'),
	(912, 'shame', 'I said something especially stupid which I did not mean at all.'),
	(913, 'joy', 'When I felt that an exam, which I had feared, was an easy one and á\nwent well.'),
	(914, 'fear', 'I was afraid when my dog ran out through a crack in the fence á\nwhen  a train was coming.'),
	(915, 'anger', 'When a friend of mine was drawn into a fight because of the á\nstupid gang he belonged to. I felt angry with him and his á\nfriends. They could not think about anything sensible, but would á\nfool around without taking into consideration the feelings of á\nother persons.á'),
	(916, 'sadness', 'I felt sad after having had an argument with my boyfriend.  I felt á\nthat he did not understand me and that there was no point in á\ncarrying on with the relationship.'),
	(917, 'disgust', 'I detested my father who was a drunkard.  He would rave, á\nthreaten and blame my mother and me.  He finally drove us away á\nfrom home.'),
	(918, 'shame', 'When I was on holiday with my former boyfriend, he hit me and á\nbehaved in a very evil and ugly manner in front of the hotel á\npersonnel.'),
	(919, 'joy', 'When I got home from a pleasant trip abroad, I got to know that I á\nhad been accepted at university.'),
	(920, 'fear', 'At school, I had acted against the will of the group, and the á\nnext day they promised to take revenge on me.'),
	(921, 'anger', 'My mother had for some time been trying to separate me from a á\ngood friend who, she thought, was not good company for me.  á\nFinally, at breakfast one day, we had an argument and I tried to á\ndefend my friend.'),
	(922, 'sadness', 'I got to know about the death of a close friend.'),
	(923, 'disgust', 'When I was watching a movie with many violent episodes.  They á\naccurately showed the cutting of corpses, etc...'),
	(924, 'shame', 'When I was caught telling a white lie.  At that time, I was not á\nallowed to stay outdoors after 8 p.m.  One day when I was late, I á\nmade up a story that our neighbour had invited me to his place, á\nthough I had actually forgotten about the time while playing with á\nmy pals.'),
	(925, 'joy', 'When I was pressing figures on the curtain cloth. I had bought á\nthe cloth after months of hindrances.'),
	(926, 'fear', 'I am a kindergarten teacher and I am thoroughly weary of my job.  á\nAfter having taken the university entrance exam I suffered from á\nanxiety for weeks as I did not want to carry on with my work - studies á\nwere the only alternative.'),
	(927, 'anger', 'My life-partner, who was drinking more and more, spoke about á\nkicking the cat.  He had never done anything of the kind, but I á\nknew that he would do so one day, without thinking about it.'),
	(928, 'sadness', 'Estrangement from my best woman friend.  We have been going á\ndifferent ways for quite some time now, but the break was total á\nwhen she got married as her husband is unreasonably jealous of me.'),
	(929, 'disgust', 'My life-partner is going through a crisis (way of life, old-fashioned values) á\nand can only get out of it by talking bold decisions.  I have á\nnoticed his cowardice and attempts to escape his problems by á\ndrinking.  I detest his drinking and his being full of self-pity.'),
	(930, 'shame', 'Again, a quarrel had come up in our difficult relationship.  My á\nlife-partner threw all the books off the shelf.  I am sure that it á\ndisturbed our neighbours since this happened late in the night.'),
	(931, 'joy', 'Begining the week-end with my girlfriend : cozyness, beer and á\nwine.'),
	(932, 'fear', 'The fear about my future : work, making ends meet and health. á\nCoping.'),
	(933, 'anger', 'A friend of mine ridiculed me, telling me that I would never á\naccomplish anything. I felt that he had interfered with my life.'),
	(934, 'sadness', 'I felt sad at having to leave my girlfriend after constant problems á\nand failed attempts at reconciliation.  My sadness was caused by á\nthe irreversibility of the decision.'),
	(935, 'disgust', 'A man spat on the wall of a house.'),
	(936, 'shame', 'In an express bus I sat on a seat meant for senior citizens and á\ninvalids.'),
	(937, 'joy', 'When after an overwhelming anxiety and enquiry, I understood á\nsomething about why I exist and what my task in life is.'),
	(938, 'fear', 'At the railway station, while waiting for the last train at night á\nI noticed that a drunk young man was appraching me in a á\npurposeful mannner.'),
	(939, 'anger', 'While having a discussion with my mother, I realized that she á\ndoes not for a moment doubt the justification of her making the á\ndecisions concerning my life.'),
	(940, 'sadness', 'When I think that I will probably never have a genuine contact á\nwith my parents.'),
	(941, 'disgust', 'While reading Olli Jalonen\'s new book, the distant, cold and á\nselfish relationships between people (in the book) made me feel á\ndisgusted.'),
	(942, 'shame', 'When I approached a person of the opposite sex and was rejected.'),
	(943, 'joy', 'The day I got to know that I would get a shared dwelling with my á\nboyfriend.  My parents place was getting a little crowded with á\nmy growing bother wanting a room to himself.  I first felt doubt, á\nthen joy, but also sadness.  The feeling of joy was the á\nstrongest.'),
	(944, 'fear', 'My grandfather had lung-cancer and was being nursed at á\nhome.  I felt fear when I was alone with him and he almost choked á\non mucus secretions.'),
	(945, 'anger', 'The outrageous conduct of a relative towards me and those close á\nto me.(blaming us and lying)'),
	(946, 'sadness', 'We had to finish the life of our 8 year-old dog.'),
	(947, 'disgust', 'A very drunk person.'),
	(948, 'shame', 'An argument that grew out of an ordinary conversation with a á\nperson very close to me, when we should have been having a good á\ntime together.'),
	(949, 'joy', '[ A chat on the telephone with a friend.]'),
	(950, 'fear', '[ Meeting some new (unpleasant) people or some new, demanding á\nsituation.]'),
	(951, 'anger', '[ For example, unfair pushing in a bus.]'),
	(952, 'sadness', '[ When I am, in my opinion, not understood correctly. ]'),
	(953, 'disgust', '[ When some people act very important in any situation.]'),
	(954, 'shame', '[ Generally, when I am late in attending to matters (for example á\npaying bills).]'),
	(955, 'joy', 'I was in a dancing-tavern and the atmosphere was one of waiting á\nfor the end of the world.  Suddenly people began dancing wildly, á\ninspired by the band.  An unbelievable experience : wonderful á\nthat even Finns sometimes flare up and forget to think "what á\nothers are thinking of me".  It was delightful to dance to one\'s á\nheart content.'),
	(956, 'fear', 'I was travelling back home by boat with two friends of mine after á\na lovely holiday trip.  The night and the sea were dark, and the á\nwind was blowing.  I feared that death was there on the boat, I á\nsomehow felt sure about it.  I feared being left alone.'),
	(957, 'anger', 'I was at home, filling my tax report.  Nobody had time to help á\nme.  I would have liked to do it quickly so that I could go and á\nmeet a friend of mine who had just returned from hospital.  I got á\nangry as both my brother and my father refused to give me their calculator á\nas I had not asked for it nicely.  I could not leave as I á\nhad to wait for help and the tax report had to be done.'),
	(958, 'sadness', 'I tried to talk to my parents over the phone, as I wanted to go á\nhome for the week-end and I knew that I would not be able to bear á\nit.  I tried to reduce the gulf and the conflict between us by á\ntalking in order to unite our worlds.  Result : hysterical mess, á\nblinding and blaming.'),
	(959, 'disgust', 'My mother called me because she had read through the enveloppe a letter á\naddressed to me.  She denied having read it intentionally and á\nsaid "the words just popped out through the enveloppe as the sun á\nwas shining on it". Hah Hah.'),
	(960, 'shame', 'I feared that I would have to describe my sexual life to an á\nolder, strange woman.'),
	(961, 'joy', 'The inflammation of the ear of my child got cured and the doctor á\nsaid that the ear was completely all right.'),
	(962, 'fear', 'My husband suddenly fell ill seriously and during the medical á\nexaminations we did not know what would follow.'),
	(963, 'anger', 'The housing council asked the city to cut 40 linden trees so that á\nthe inhabitants of the lower floors would have a view to the sea.'),
	(964, 'sadness', 'My child, unexpectedly started acting in a restless and á\ndisturbing way at school.  In addition his performance at school á\nweakened.'),
	(965, 'disgust', 'On a trip abroad, a lady-like member of our group turned out to á\nbe an alcoholic.  She spoilt many days of my holidays because of á\nher behaviour and paranoia.'),
	(966, 'shame', 'I failed an exam which I thought I would certainly pass.'),
	(967, 'joy', 'When a student of mine (at music) performed and played remarkably well.'),
	(968, 'fear', 'When climbing up the stairs to the top of a ski-jumping hill.'),
	(969, 'anger', 'My boy-friend came home late one night without having told me á\nabout it before.'),
	(970, 'sadness', 'The breaking up of a long lasting relationship.'),
	(971, 'disgust', 'While watching the movie called "Deer hunter" on TV, when it á\nshowed how prisoners were treated.'),
	(972, 'shame', 'When I noticed that a person I found attractive had seen me á\npicking my nose.'),
	(973, 'joy', 'When I made up with a girl-friend of mine after having been on á\nunfriendly terms with her (my fault).  I cried with joy that á\nevening.'),
	(974, 'fear', 'While cycling in the country, I came across a large herd of á\ncows.'),
	(975, 'anger', 'When I heard that my step-mother had treated my mother in a wrong á\nmanner.'),
	(976, 'sadness', 'When my friend did not pass the high school graduation á\nexaminations.'),
	(977, 'disgust', 'When I heard about the advances an acquaintance of mine had made á\nto my friends, who did not approve of them.'),
	(978, 'shame', 'When after having had sexual intercourse with a friend, I thought á\nthat he had told about it to a friend of his.'),
	(979, 'joy', 'During lectures, I sensed an unexpressed understanding with a boy á\nI did not know.  We exchange glances ; I think he likes me, and I á\nlike him too.  Perhaps he has fallen in love with me .........'),
	(980, 'fear', 'At night, I walk home past a forest.  Once, somebody got stabbed á\nin the forest.  I imagine someone attacking me and I hurry up.'),
	(981, 'anger', 'In a tram, the ticket seller was commanding, taking the role of a á\nleader, trying to emphasize her non-existent authority with undue á\nstrictness towards a good-humoured drunk who could not find his á\nticket at once.'),
	(982, 'sadness', 'A relationship in which I had put my trust, broke up.  I was sad á\nwhen I realized how easy it is to forget something that one had á\nonce regarded as great and significant.'),
	(983, 'disgust', 'A nightmare.  I was dreaming about bloodsuckers, which I tried to á\nshake off from my body, they are everywhere, they get glued, they á\nsuck.  And there are a lot of them.  I panic.'),
	(984, 'shame', 'I told evil lies about a close friend of mine.  I was evil in á\norder to sound jolly, to charm a person whom I wanted to impress. á\n I sold my friend, I was despicable.'),
	(985, 'joy', '[ During inter-rail-trip, after troubles, I met my little á\nsister.]'),
	(986, 'fear', 'Traveling as the only female in a railway carriage in the middle á\nof the night in Italy.'),
	(987, 'anger', 'A male, Honduran acquaintance of mine despised my opinions.'),
	(988, 'sadness', 'When our dog died.'),
	(989, 'disgust', 'While walking on the street with a good friend of mine, we met an á\nacquaintance of hers.  My friend started showing off and telling á\nfalse stories about herself and praising herself.'),
	(990, 'shame', 'I was dishonest to my boyfriend concerning something that is á\nimportant to our relationship.'),
	(991, 'joy', 'After having at last finished my master\'s thesis, I felt great á\njoy and relief.  I had been haunted by the thesis during the á\nwhole of my studies.'),
	(992, 'fear', 'While preparing my master\'s thesis, I was scared that I would not á\naccomplish anything as the subject was rather difficult.'),
	(993, 'anger', 'During the Summer, at my workplace, a person kept interfering á\nwith my tasks and making unfounded remarks.  I felt hatred for á\nhim but it stopped when I realized that he just longed for attention.'),
	(994, 'sadness', 'The last time I felt sad and disappointed was when I did not do á\nas well as I had hoped in one of the final exams.  As compared á\nwith the earlier exams, the questions, I think, were unjust.'),
	(995, 'disgust', 'After the first of May, I detested my fiance\'s friends, who had á\npiled on to our party and spoilt it completely.'),
	(996, 'shame', 'After our sad first of May party, I felt ashamed because the á\nfriends who had been invited had to suffer.  We, the organizers á\nof the party, did not drive the intruders away.'),
	(997, 'joy', 'When I met a good friend of mine after a long time.'),
	(998, 'fear', 'I was camping with a friend of mine and we spent the night in the á\nforest.  I could not fall off to sleep and could clearly hear á\nnoises from outside (steps ?) approaching our tent.'),
	(999, 'anger', 'When I quarelled with my parents.'),
	(1000, 'sadness', 'Being away from a very close friend, I was away from Finland á\nfor a year as an exchange student.'),
	(1001, 'disgust', 'When I saw a spider.'),
	(1002, 'shame', 'While playing I urinated on grandma\'s floor and did not go to the á\nlavatory.  My cousin told grandma and she came.'),
	(1003, 'joy', 'While having a discussion with a colleague of mine, I realized that her á\nconception of man and work were similar to mine.'),
	(1004, 'fear', 'While he was drunk, my life partner tried to hit me.  I felt á\nscared and fled to the bathroom.'),
	(1005, 'anger', 'A "higher status" colleague of mine despised my attitude and á\norganization of work.'),
	(1006, 'sadness', 'I could not meet my love, after having waited for a month, due to á\nillness.'),
	(1007, 'disgust', 'Once again, my life partner came back home drunk at midnight.'),
	(1008, 'shame', 'My love and me rented a room in a hotel one evening.  We stayed á\nthere a few hours and when leaving the hotel, I felt ashamed.'),
	(1009, 'joy', 'I had just moved to the town where I study and I got a postcard á\nfrom a good friend (from my home town).'),
	(1010, 'fear', 'My boyfriend hinted over the phone about wanting to "be free".  á\nHe thus did not say it point blank, silence followed.'),
	(1011, 'anger', 'They had returned much less of my taxes than I had expected.'),
	(1012, 'sadness', 'After my boyfriend and I had separated.'),
	(1013, 'disgust', 'In the morning, the cat of my landlady had vomited on the floor, á\nnear the staircase I take to go to the bathroom.'),
	(1014, 'shame', 'My boyfriend\'s mother, whom I had not met earlier, made an á\nunexpected visit.  I was lying lazily on the bed, reading a á\nnewspaper and my boyfriend was studying.'),
	(1015, 'joy', 'I got a letter from my best friend, whom I had not heard from for á\na long time (a good letter).'),
	(1016, 'fear', 'Someone knocked on the door when I was alone at home (though á\nthere was a door bell).  I looked through the peep hole but it á\nhad been covered.  I called my sister but she could not help me á\nas she was hundreds of kilometres away.'),
	(1017, 'anger', 'My parents put pressure on me to buy clothes, when I would not á\nhave liked to do so.'),
	(1018, 'sadness', 'When my grandfather died, I saw my grandmother crying against my á\naunt\'s shoulder (I had never seen my grandmother cry before).'),
	(1019, 'disgust', 'At school, I detested the spinach gruel which had lumps of flour á\nin it.'),
	(1020, 'shame', 'I told some acquaintances of mine something that I regretted á\nlater.'),
	(1021, 'joy', 'When I got a letter from home.'),
	(1022, 'fear', 'While cycling in the country a dog started running beside me, á\ngrowling and barking, and trying to bite my foot.'),
	(1023, 'anger', 'Disagreements with mother.  When I moved from KankaanpSS, she had á\npromised to help me move but broke her promise because of some á\nhindrance.'),
	(1024, 'sadness', 'When I had to move away from home to study, and I knew that I á\nwould not be coming back home for a long time.'),
	(1025, 'disgust', 'When I noticed two spiders running on the floor in different á\ndirections.'),
	(1026, 'shame', 'When I realized that I had been wrong about a person close to me, á\nbecause of pre-set ideas and prejudices.'),
	(1027, 'joy', 'I found myself a place after looking for one for a long time.'),
	(1028, 'fear', '[ In an aeroplane.]'),
	(1029, 'anger', 'I was angry at my boyfriend who had promised to come to see me á\nbut did not because he spent the evening with his pals.'),
	(1030, 'sadness', 'The breaking up of a relationship.  We decided that the á\nrelationship could not carry on, so it was no surprise to me. á\nAnd anyhow, I had known it would happen sooner or later.'),
	(1031, 'disgust', 'The disgust I feel towards a certain person.'),
	(1032, 'shame', 'After an event in which I felt that I had acted unfairly.'),
	(1033, 'joy', 'I went to see the entrance examination results at university.  I á\nrejoyced at my success.'),
	(1034, 'fear', 'I borrowed a car which was supposed to be used for a long journey á\na few hours later, and one of the tyres burst in the middle of á\nthe town and I did not know what to do.'),
	(1035, 'anger', 'An utterance, which I had intended to be a joke, was taken as an á\noffence.  In my opinion, this was stupid, and I got angry.'),
	(1036, 'sadness', 'My best friend had a relatively severe illness.  I was sad á\nbecause she was suffering.'),
	(1037, 'disgust', 'A man tried to have sexual intercourse with me, though I had á\ncommunicated my unwillingness.  Later on, I felt disgust at that á\nperson as well as myself because I had partly submitted.'),
	(1038, 'shame', 'I told my friend about how I had calculated my salary by cheating a á\nlittle.  When my friend remarked about it, I understood that it á\nwas wrong to do so, and I felt ashamed.'),
	(1039, 'joy', 'A good report card (a scholarship) in primary school.'),
	(1040, 'fear', 'I was walking home with a friend at night along a quiet street.  á\nSomething started rustling in the bush : it was an exhibitionist.'),
	(1041, 'anger', 'I got angry at a friend of mine whom I caught reading my notebook á\n(almanach).'),
	(1042, 'sadness', 'When my grandmother died of cancer.'),
	(1043, 'disgust', 'In a lift a drunken, fat and untidy man tried to make advances at á\nme.'),
	(1044, 'shame', '[ Sometimes I have by accident said to another person something á\nin which it is easy to read a negative attitude.]'),
	(1045, 'joy', 'When I made the acquaintance of a certain person.'),
	(1046, 'fear', 'When abroad, while driving a car along a dark, winding road.'),
	(1047, 'anger', 'When my sister took my things without having asked for my permission á\nfirst.'),
	(1048, 'disgust', 'When I was working, I got treated in a way which I felt was not á\ndemocratic.'),
	(1049, 'shame', 'While working as a domestic helper, one day I had not cleaned up á\nvery well and they made a remark about it.'),
	(1050, 'joy', 'When I went to a job interview, I met a person who was very nice, á\nand his attitude made me glad.'),
	(1051, 'fear', 'My episode of fright happened when I came to study.  I had to á\nstand in front of my still unknown fellow students and talk about á\nmyself.  My hands shook, I flushed and became tongue-tied.'),
	(1052, 'joy', 'I was in a restaurant with my boyfriend when I saw my best female á\nfriend after not seeing her for two weeks.  We rejoyced, hugged á\nand had a long talk.'),
	(1053, 'fear', 'One evening, while going to meet a friend of mine, I had to cross á\na meadow by a dark road.  There were bushes on the other side of á\nthe road.  The weather was damp and a bit foggy.  I heard steps á\nbehind me and kept speeding up my steps all the time.'),
	(1054, 'anger', 'My brother told me that a person (whom I know) had insulted him.  á\nI am very fond of my brother, and as he himself can not get angry á\nor hurt, my protectiveness was aroused and I got angry.'),
	(1055, 'sadness', 'My guinea-pig had been ill for a couple of days.  One evening, á\nwhen I came home I enquired as to how it was doing.  My mother\'s á\nexpression told me that it had died.  My knees refused to support á\nme and I began to weep convulsively.'),
	(1056, 'disgust', 'I happened to see two boys fighting, one of them fell down and á\nhurt his head.  The other one used this to spank the head of the \r\nboy on the ground.'),
	(1057, 'shame', 'I had been away all night without having told my parents about á\nit.  In the morning when I came home, my mother looked tired.  á\nShe said that she had been awake all night because of me and that á\nshe was angry and disappointed.'),
	(1058, 'joy', 'When I was sick my husband bought me a piece of cake.'),
	(1059, 'fear', 'I saw a man who had had a heart-attack and who was being á\ntreated for it.  I feared that my own father could have been á\nthere.'),
	(1060, 'anger', 'When I saw a big man hit another one, and nobody did anything.'),
	(1061, 'sadness', 'When my sister left to go home, in Sweden, after the Christmas á\nHolidays.'),
	(1062, 'disgust', 'I once watched the series called "Dynasty" on TV, and I detested á\nit.'),
	(1063, 'shame', 'I feel guilty as I am not working, and even my studies are not á\nprogressing.'),
	(1064, 'joy', 'When my red-cheeked, content child runs to meet me in the yard of á\nthe kindergarten and gives me a moist kiss on my cheek.'),
	(1065, 'fear', 'A neighbour\'s girl had disappeared and many people were looking á\nfor her.  Someone had gone to notify the police.  Something had á\ncertainly happened to her.'),
	(1066, 'anger', 'Without my permission, my son had made popcorn after coming back á\nfrom school.  The consequences were a spoilt kettle and chaos in á\nthe kitchen but what could have happened with the hot grease ?'),
	(1067, 'sadness', 'The death of a close relative.'),
	(1068, 'disgust', 'One of my fellow students used questionable and unfair means to á\nadvance her studies faster than others.  I detested her.'),
	(1069, 'shame', 'My friend told me in a fairly loud voice the blunders she á\ncommitted last night.'),
	(1070, 'joy', 'After my vacations, one day after a lecture it occured to me to á\nbuy a rose for my mother.  We went together to a pub and my á\nmother told me that she would be getting married next Spring.  I á\ndid not known about it and so was all the more glad.'),
	(1071, 'fear', 'I work at a day care centre, and one day when the children were á\noutdoors a four-year old boy disappeared from the yard.  I was á\nnot looking after them then, but as the manager it was me who was á\nresponsible.'),
	(1072, 'anger', 'I was on vacation, and therefore I did not attend a meeting of á\nthe day care centre.  Nevertheless, the very day I came back they á\ncalled me early morining to ask me "what are you going to do á\nabout the matter ?" (which had been discussed in the meeting).  á\nThen I got angry.'),
	(1073, 'sadness', 'The fact that my mother is getting married again (my mother and á\nfather divorced about 15 years ago) means that she will probably á\nmove to Turku, and our home, which is a one family house, will be á\nsold (I myself have not been living at home for the past six á\nyears).'),
	(1074, 'disgust', 'While travelling in a bus, there were three people sitting behind á\nme (two men and a woman).  They were drunk and the conversation á\nwas unbelievable (about fucking, fellatio, etc...).  They tried á\nto get others to take part in the conversation.  I loathed it and á\nfelt like crying.'),
	(1075, 'shame', 'When I was seven years old, I stole a chewing-gum from a big á\nglass bowl on the counter of a nearby shop, and I got caught.'),
	(1076, 'joy', 'I had been away from home for a long time and when I came home I á\nwas delighted.  It was wonderful to see familiar, dear people and á\nI was rejoycing in advance.  I had been feeling very lonely.'),
	(1077, 'fear', 'I awoke at night and did not remember dreaming about antthing in á\nparticular.  I just felt oppressing fear, it was dark and all the á\nothers were sleeping.'),
	(1078, 'anger', 'One winter day I, unwillingly, was outdoors with my younger á\nbrother (10 years younger than me).  I lost my temper on him and á\nwanted to throw my brother down the snow bank we were on.  I á\npushed him but not as hard as I had wanted to. We were alone the á\ntwo of us.'),
	(1079, 'sadness', 'I was on a class excursion, by boat to Stockholm.  At night my á\nclass mates prepared to clebrate their motive in life which was á\n"life is merriment".  I felt depressed about the way they sought á\nhappiness.'),
	(1080, 'disgust', 'I was on my way home by bus.  A man who had drunk a fair amount of á\nalcohol started talking, trying to hug and pat a woman sitting á\nnext to him.  Fortunately it was not me.'),
	(1081, 'shame', 'I gave a wrong answer at school.'),
	(1082, 'joy', 'When, after a long time, I saw a girl with whom I was in love.'),
	(1083, 'fear', 'When I was walking on a fairly out-of-the-way street.'),
	(1084, 'anger', 'A friend of mine had promised to arrange me some tickets for a á\nconcert which I considered important.  He could not get them the á\nway he thought he would, so he gave up the whole thing.'),
	(1085, 'sadness', 'I was sad when I saw that a beautiful girl was not attainable.'),
	(1086, 'disgust', 'I heard somebody talk about studies in a highly enthusiastic á\n"student-like" way.'),
	(1087, 'shame', 'While attending some affairs, which were taking some time, with á\na bank officer, I felt that my clothes and appearance were out of place, too á\nraggy.'),
	(1088, 'joy', 'While watching an entertainment program in which there was a clever  á\nand amusing sketch.'),
	(1089, 'fear', 'When I was in the army, a room mate of mine came back from á\nfurlough and threatened another fellow with a knife.'),
	(1090, 'anger', 'The last day of school is traditionally celebrated by singing a á\nsong about all the students who are leaving.  In the song á\nabout me, there were things which irritated me a lot.'),
	(1091, 'sadness', 'I worked for seven months in a factory, and made friends with a á\nfellow worker.  Later, I visited my former fellow workers and was á\ntold that, while in the army, my friend had shot himself.'),
	(1092, 'disgust', 'The behaviour of a fellow towards me and some others in the army á\nwas really mean.  I detested this.'),
	(1093, 'shame', 'I tried to date a girl, but she refused.'),
	(1094, 'joy', 'In the army, my result at the shooting exercises got á\nme a three day furlough.'),
	(1095, 'fear', 'When I was 8 years old, I would usually come home from school á\nwith my mother in a car.  For the first time I had to take the á\nschool bus, and I mistook the bus stop and found myself two á\nkilometres away from where I lived.  I was very scared, wondering á\nhow I would get back home.'),
	(1096, 'anger', 'I read in the newspaper that the Student Lodging Fund was going á\nto build new appartments for refugees (in my opinion this is the á\nstate\'s affair).  This is when only a fractoin of the students á\ncan find an appartment.'),
	(1097, 'sadness', 'I lead a rather secure life.  The only thing I can remember is a á\nsong from the nineteenth century which is against alcohol.  Both á\nthe melody and the word (although naive) effected my emotions.'),
	(1098, 'disgust', 'Yesterday in the elevator a man started smoking, this is á\nsomething I just can not tolerate.'),
	(1099, 'shame', 'In primary school I once faltered while answering a question and á\nthe others started laughing.'),
	(1100, 'joy', 'When my favourite football team made a goal and was about to á\nwin the Cup of England.'),
	(1101, 'fear', 'I was less than 10 years old when our neighbour\'s dog chased me á\nto the roof of a small shed and there seemed to be no hope of á\ngetting away from there.'),
	(1102, 'anger', 'While playing a ball game, I was just about to make a goal when I á\nwas thrown off my feet, and I failed to score the goal.'),
	(1103, 'sadness', 'When I heard about the death of Frantois Truffaut, the French motion  á\npicture director, on the radio.  I had planned to go and see his á\nlast film.'),
	(1104, 'disgust', 'I saw a movie called "The Thing", the film directed by John á\nCarpenter.  The monster in the film made me feel disgusted.'),
	(1105, 'shame', 'I had misbehaved at a party and did not wish to meet the person á\nin question later.'),
	(1106, 'joy', 'When I was in the sauna bath.'),
	(1107, 'fear', 'I had a dream in which I was an African elephant.'),
	(1108, 'anger', 'When I came for the lesson, it was cancelled and I had to fill in á\na questionnaire instead.'),
	(1109, 'sadness', 'When my car froze, and I could not start it.'),
	(1110, 'disgust', 'When I saw our computer teacher.'),
	(1111, 'shame', 'When I was going downhill on skis, and fell down twice the first á\ntime.'),
	(1112, 'joy', 'I passed an exam which I thought I had failed.'),
	(1113, 'fear', 'My mother had not come home at midnight.  She had forgotten to á\ntell me about it.  I was very young and all alone at home.'),
	(1114, 'anger', 'My girlfriend started singing (she cannot sing) and did not stop á\ndespite my asking her to do so.'),
	(1115, 'disgust', 'When I was still a child, I saw a horror film on TV in which á\nthere was a rotten human skull.'),
	(1116, 'shame', 'As a small boy, I took a coin from an empty taxi cab.  My mother á\nsaw it and told the driver about it.  I even knew the driver.'),
	(1117, 'anger', 'New Year\'s Eve party in the country, I hardly knew a person; my á\npartner spent most of the time at the bar. I had little á\nopportunity to get to know people because our table was separated á\nand my boyfriend\'s parents were present.'),
	(1118, 'sadness', 'Christmas Eve: there was a tension between my parents, they did á\nnot even try to restore a harmonic atmosphere. Mother stayed in á\nher room almost the whole day. I felt alone and was very sad.'),
	(1119, 'disgust', 'Father said: If you are pregnant, you will have to procure á\nabortion. I was filled with disgust against my father.'),
	(1120, 'shame', 'I had an intimate relation with my boyfriend, but unfortunately á\nwe had sexual problems; therefore I deceived him, but I was á\nashamed when I told my friend about it.'),
	(1121, 'joy', 'After one year of searching, my friend and I have found a flat we á\nare able to pay for.'),
	(1122, 'fear', 'Car accident in the middle of the night.'),
	(1123, 'anger', 'At the weekend I wanted to be absent from school because of a á\nsports event, but my teacher refused to give me the day off á\nbecause he didn\'t like me.'),
	(1124, 'sadness', 'When I was six years old, my favourite cat died.'),
	(1125, 'disgust', 'A gigantic spider climbed over my face and what is more - in my á\nown flat.'),
	(1126, 'shame', 'I was very fat and felt absolutely unwell. I was afraid of á\nleaving the house and getting to know new people.'),
	(1127, 'joy', 'I won a car in a prize-competition. The moment I was informed á\nabout it, I felt joy.'),
	(1128, 'fear', 'My sister had to undergo a very complicated operation, her á\neyesight was at stake.'),
	(1129, 'anger', 'I had a quarrel with my parents; I was convinced to be right.'),
	(1130, 'sadness', 'I heard that a friend had died in an accident; group situation: á\nsuddenly a friend came in and said "Have you already heard á\nthat..."; there was a terrible consternation, silence, then á\neverybody shouted excitedly "How could that happen...".'),
	(1131, 'disgust', 'Scuffle in a carriage of the underground in Vienna, three drunk á\nmen thrashed a man in a wheel chair - I watched the scene from á\nanother carriage.'),
	(1132, 'shame', 'I put an end to a friendship with a girl - I had only pretended á\nlove and affection to be able to sleep with her.'),
	(1133, 'joy', 'In order to be admitted to my final examination, I had to pass á\ntwo examinations. As I had not studied very much, I resigned á\nmyself to be left behind. Nevertheless I succeeded in these á\nexaminations.'),
	(1134, 'fear', 'I had not told my parents about my bad marks in school. One day, á\nmy father wanted to speak to the teachers. Fortunately I could á\ninfluence my parents to take it easy.'),
	(1135, 'anger', 'I wanted to go to a friend of mine who had a party; at the moment á\nI wanted to leave, my father said I couldn\'t go because he needed á\nme for some work in the afternoon.'),
	(1136, 'sadness', 'A friend of mine, who had repeated a year at school once before, á\ndid not pass the final examination and had to take it again half á\na year later.'),
	(1137, 'disgust', 'Eco-activists demonstrated against a project to build a power station á\nat the Danube in the middle of a lowland forest (Hainburg) and á\nthe government decided to delay it for another year. When my á\nfather heard about it, he said that we needed another Hitler.'),
	(1138, 'shame', 'There was a time when my room looked terribly untidy; just at á\nthat time my aunt came to see me; fortunately I could prevent her á\nfrom entering the room.'),
	(1139, 'joy', 'My boyfriend returned after a long absence.'),
	(1140, 'fear', 'My car skidded on the wet street.'),
	(1141, 'anger', 'I wanted to see a friend, I had been looking forward to it and á\nhad certain expectations, but he did not pay any attention to me, á\nplayed cards with other people.'),
	(1142, 'sadness', 'A good friend quitted me after he had behaved in a strange á\nmanner.'),
	(1143, 'disgust', 'In broad daylight I saw an untidy old man pissing and playing á\nwith his penis in the middle of the town.'),
	(1144, 'shame', 'Somebody who knows me very well discovered that I had told him a á\nlie.'),
	(1145, 'anger', 'Recently a good friend only called me when he needed something. á\nHe never said "please" or "thank you" or any other kind word.'),
	(1146, 'sadness', 'My favourite horse died. We had tried our best to save him, but á\nit was hopeless, he had to be shot.'),
	(1147, 'disgust', 'I read a book about the sexual phantasies of women; I read about á\na woman having sexual intercourse with a dog.'),
	(1148, 'shame', 'In our flat the bath-tub is in the kitchen. At the beginning I á\nhad very intensive feelings of shame when I had a bath and people á\nwere in the kitchen.'),
	(1149, 'joy', 'When I met a good friend after a long time. We had had a quarrel á\nbut after two weeks I was really glad to see him again.'),
	(1150, 'fear', 'When we stayed in Vienna with our class, my friend and I behaved á\nincorrectly. Our teacher threatened us with exclusion from á\nschool.'),
	(1151, 'anger', 'When I lost my driving license because I had been driving while á\nunder the influence of alcool.'),
	(1152, 'sadness', 'My mother\'s death.'),
	(1153, 'disgust', 'When I entered the dissecting room for the first time. I think I á\nfelt disgusted mainly because of the bad smell of formaline.'),
	(1154, 'shame', 'I think I felt ashamed for the first time when I entered a night á\nclub.'),
	(1155, 'joy', 'My father stayed abroad for one year. He does not like to write á\nletters because he makes ortographic mistakes. I never had a good á\nrelation to him. He wrote me a letter in which he said that he á\nloved me.'),
	(1156, 'fear', 'When I was a child, I was always afraid of my father. Just when á\nhe looked at me, I felt frightened.'),
	(1157, 'anger', 'A colleague asked me to study with her. I could not explain á\nthings as perfectly as she had expected. So she reacted in an á\naggressive manner.'),
	(1158, 'sadness', 'During the Christmas holidays, I went to see my parents and á\nstayed with them for two weeks. After two or three days, we had á\nthe same conflicts we had had ten years before when I had lived á\nwith them. They were glad when I left.'),
	(1159, 'disgust', 'Old man in hospital, hollow-cheeked, only one half of his nose á\nand glass-eye, rattling breath.'),
	(1160, 'shame', 'When my father came into the bathroom and saw me standing there á\nnaked.'),
	(1161, 'joy', 'When I met my girlfriend - I had not counted on that.'),
	(1162, 'fear', 'One night I had a feeling that somebody was stealing my car, á\nbut I was too frightened to go and see.'),
	(1163, 'anger', 'When we rearranged furniture in our flat and got stuck in a á\nchair.'),
	(1164, 'sadness', 'A person died (not really a friend).'),
	(1165, 'disgust', 'Several weeks ago, I had problems with friends, I felt disgusted á\nby a friend.'),
	(1166, 'shame', 'When I was a child, I thought that I had to be ashamed when á\nasking and doing certain forbidden things.'),
	(1167, 'joy', 'In Southern Tyrol, I was gathering apples, it was a fine day, I á\nwas not thinking about anything, I felt an overwhelming joy.'),
	(1168, 'fear', 'My girlfriend and I slept in a lonely hut (we had drunk alcool). á\nSuddenly some soil fell on us, then some water. Although we tried á\nhard, we could not find out the cause.'),
	(1169, 'anger', 'I helped my little sister (13 years) learning mathematics. á\nObviously she did not want to understand what I explained and á\nstarted to cry. I grew angry.'),
	(1170, 'sadness', 'When my girlfriend told me that she wanted to leave me.'),
	(1171, 'disgust', 'On a trip I passed by a cellulose factory. It was a fine day, á\nbeautiful landscape; I observed this factory with disgust.'),
	(1172, 'shame', 'When I went to a sauna with my father for the first time (I was á\n16). When I entered the sauna naked, I felt ashamed for a short á\ntime.'),
	(1173, 'joy', 'A friend I had missed very much came to see me unexpectedly.'),
	(1174, 'fear', 'On my way through lonely streets I met with a huge stray dog. It á\nstopped at some distance and looked at me. I tried to ignore it á\nbut I was very frightened.'),
	(1175, 'anger', 'A friend of mine tried to persuade me to go at her place to act á\nas a model because she felt too tired. It was a quarter of an á\nhour before the appointed time, I had just lied down and did not á\nwant to go because it was too late anyway. She said that I only á\nwas talking about looking for work, but if it was possible I á\nwould not accept it. I was angry about this unjust judgment.'),
	(1176, 'sadness', 'After I had lived with my boyfriend in a foreign country for half á\na year, I saw that it was impossible for me to stay with him (for á\neconomic reasons). We separated although I loved him.'),
	(1177, 'disgust', 'In a certain book I read about cruelties and violence in prison á\nand souteneur circles; I felt especially disgusted when I read á\ndetailed descriptions of physical and mental torture of less á\npowerful people.'),
	(1178, 'shame', 'When I talked to a psychotherapist for the first time, I started á\nto cry; first I talked to him but he did not say anything and á\nafter a while I was crying.'),
	(1179, 'joy', 'When I worked as an "au-pair-girl" in London, I received a call á\nfrom a good friend who told me that she was in London too and á\nwanted to see me. I was very glad - after that call and á\nespecially when I saw her.'),
	(1180, 'fear', 'It was on St. Claus Day when I was five years old. St. Claus and á\nhis Devil Servant came to see me. St. Claus\' Devil Servant á\nrattled with his chain and bowled terribly. I was so frightened á\nthat my parents had to ask him to leave.'),
	(1181, 'anger', 'A friend called me and told me that she wanted to come and see á\nme. She lived in a village at 50 km distance fom my home town. á\nNext morning I expected her but she didn\'t arrive. As I got á\nimpatient I called her but her parents told me that she had gone á\nskiing. I was very angry because I had cancelled an appointment á\nto be able to see her.'),
	(1182, 'sadness', 'When I was eight years old my father was run over by a car. When á\nI saw his body I was sad beyond words.'),
	(1183, 'disgust', 'A friend prepared a soup with chicken heads and invited me to eat á\nit. I saw the eyes staring at me and the tongues hanging out of á\nthe bills. I was so disgusted that I felt nausea and had to leave á\nthe room.'),
	(1184, 'shame', 'When I had to go to the gynecologist and to sit on that special á\nchair, I felt ashamed.'),
	(1185, 'joy', 'I had the unexpected possibility to see a friend I like very á\nmuch.'),
	(1186, 'fear', 'I was afraid of a certain examination although I was relatively á\nwell prepared.'),
	(1187, 'anger', 'At the hairdresser\'s, I got two stains of dyestuff on my new á\ntrousers. These stains are not removable, so I cannot put on the á\ntrousers again.'),
	(1188, 'sadness', 'In 1977, my grandfather, to whom I had a very close relationship, á\ndied.'),
	(1189, 'disgust', 'A drunken man forced me to kiss him.'),
	(1190, 'shame', 'A friend started to insult another person without reason and I á\nfelt ashamed of her behavior.'),
	(1191, 'joy', 'After a one year\'s stay abroad, I returned home. I was even more á\nglad to see how much my family was pleased to see me.'),
	(1192, 'fear', 'I went home all alone from a restaurant. It was dark, I went very á\nfast. Behind me, there were some drunk men who shouted at me. By á\nchance, I met some friends who accompanied me.'),
	(1193, 'anger', 'A friend who shares the room with me, opened the window in the á\nmorning and left the room the whole day. When I came home in the á\nevening, the room was so cold that I couldn\'t stay there.'),
	(1194, 'sadness', 'When my aunt, whom I had loved very much, died. When I heard á\nabout her death, I was not as touched as at the funeral. I really á\nbecame conscious of her death at that moment.'),
	(1195, 'disgust', 'A friend told me how he managed to win the sympathy of as many á\npeople as possible. He said he first listened to what they said á\nand then he tried to only say things they would like to hear. á\nHe would never express his own opinion. I felt really disgusted á\nwhen he told that.'),
	(1196, 'shame', 'In a restaurant, I made the acquaintance of a boy who always told á\nthe same things in a very loud voice. I laughed and said to him á\nthat he always repeated the same things. Some time later I heard á\nthat he had undergone a complicated brain operation.'),
	(1197, 'joy', 'On our way to France, my girlfriend and I went to Verona. By á\nchance we met an Italian couple - they gave us two tickets for á\nthe dress-rehearsal of "Aida". It was a different world for us á\nfull of fascination. After the representation we ate a phantastic á\npizza in a restaurant near the "Arena".'),
	(1198, 'fear', 'On a mountain tour, my girlfriend and I passed by an inn. Near á\nthe house there was a big dog which began to follow us. As my á\ngirlfriend is afraid of dogs, I had to draw his attention to me. á\nHe jumped towards my shoulders and wanted to play with me but I á\nreally did not like that.'),
	(1199, 'anger', 'I arrived in Vienna in the middle of the night. I asked for some á\nsilly information - as I realized myself afterwards - and the inquiry  á\nclerk reacted in a very arrogant manner.'),
	(1200, 'sadness', 'I had to leave my girlfriend for 4 weeks because of my studies. á\nThis happens frequently. The last 24 hours before my departure á\nare always very depressing.'),
	(1201, 'disgust', 'When I stayed in the house of friends, I washed my face and á\nwanted to dry it with a towel. This towel seemed to have been á\nused over a long time already. It smelled indefinably awful.'),
	(1202, 'shame', 'A friend of mine has not very much money. Therefore, once I á\nstayed with him and his girlfriend, I bought some meat, but nobody á\nwanted to go and prepare it for dinner. My friend said "I thought á\nyou wanted to invite us for dinner". "Of course", I said, but I á\nthought by myself that it must have been enough that I had bought á\nit.'),
	(1203, 'joy', 'When I was informed that a short story I had written had been á\naccepted for publication.'),
	(1204, 'fear', 'Some friends and I were crossing a street when one of my friends á\nwas seized by a car and thrown aside. I had seen the car coming á\nin our direction but I did not have enough time to react and á\nprevent the accident.'),
	(1205, 'anger', 'I wanted to clear up a misunderstanding with a friend that I had á\ncaused. A third person meddled in our conversation, turned my á\nefforts to ridicule so that I did not succeed in what I had á\nintended.'),
	(1206, 'sadness', 'Death of my grandmother.'),
	(1207, 'disgust', 'In school I had difficulties mith mathematics. When I had to work á\nfor an examination, I really felt disgusted.'),
	(1208, 'shame', 'I played in a stage play. Suddenly, in front of 200 people, I á\ncould not remember the words I had to say.'),
	(1209, 'joy', 'After 3 weeks I saw my girlfriend again.'),
	(1210, 'fear', 'One evening, in the tramway, I was afraid of two drunk men á\nmolesting my girlfriend and me.'),
	(1211, 'anger', 'I went singing with a group of young people on January 6th (The á\nthree Magi), a local custom called "star singing". One of the girls, my á\ngirlfriend, broke the star. Being the accompanying person, I felt very á\nangry thinking of the consequences.'),
	(1212, 'sadness', 'When the grandmother of my friend died in a hospital. My friend á\nwas crying and I was sad, too.'),
	(1213, 'disgust', 'I saw a physically handicapped young man whose spittle ran out of á\nhis mouth while speaking.'),
	(1214, 'shame', 'It was in a group situation: suddenly it was my turn to say something, \r\nbut I felt that I was not able to express myself very well - I felt á\nashamed and blushed.'),
	(1215, 'joy', 'I went shopping with my parents - my father payed everything for á\nme, I was very glad.'),
	(1216, 'fear', 'When I was a child, I heard the floor cracking and I thought á\nthere was a burglar in our house; I hid under the blanket and á\ntrembled.'),
	(1217, 'anger', 'During a lecture, a colleague who did not know anything about the á\nsubject, got on my nerves asking silly questions.'),
	(1218, 'sadness', 'When my grandfathers died and I realized how much I would miss á\nthem.'),
	(1219, 'disgust', 'During a football game, another player who was perspiring very á\nstrongly ran into me.'),
	(1220, 'shame', 'I tried to pass an examination particularly well, but I did it á\nworse than ever. I felt ashamed.'),
	(1221, 'joy', 'At a choral concert I appeared as a solist. The concert5 was very á\ngood, I forgot all the hard work that had been done before. There á\nremained only an undescribable joy and a feeling of warmth, á\nsecurity etc.'),
	(1222, 'fear', 'I am a "cantor" - I sing psalms in church. Several weeks ago I á\nhad to sing too, but the organist did not tell me in time. As I á\ndid not know the psalm, I was afraid and said that I could not á\nsing.'),
	(1223, 'anger', 'During the Christmas holdidays I wanted to invite my brother, his á\ngirlfriend and their child for dinner. When I said to my á\nbrother\'s girlfriend that I would like them to come at my place á\nfor dinner, she refused and never mentioned it again as if I á\nhad never asked her.'),
	(1224, 'sadness', 'Several years ago my brother died in an accident. When I heard á\nabout it, I was very sad. It took years until I resigned myself á\nto it.'),
	(1225, 'disgust', 'I read a book about the situation in South-Africa, about the á\nterrible violations of human rights. I was disgusted with the á\nwhite population.'),
	(1226, 'shame', 'My P.T. instructor also works as a masseur. He wanted to massage á\nme, therefore I had to undress. For the first few times this was á\nnot easy for me; I got gradually used to it.'),
	(1227, 'joy', 'When my brother came back home after staying in hospital. He had á\nundergone an operation which had been a matter of life or death. á\nWhen he came home I could see him smile for the first time after á\nmay weeks.'),
	(1228, 'fear', 'After a short stay in Marocco we missed the ferry-boat back to á\nSpain and we had to look for an accomodation. By chance we met a á\nman who offered to take us to a camping site. While I was sitting in his á\ncar I was terribly afraid because I had heard of people being á\nrobbed in Marocco.'),
	(1229, 'anger', 'After an exhausting day I came home and wanted to take a bath to á\nrelax. My father wanted to take a bath first and when he had á\nfinished after an hour, there was no hot water left for me.'),
	(1230, 'sadness', 'I met some nice people during my holdidays. When they left I knew á\nthat I would never see them again.'),
	(1231, 'disgust', 'A drunk man attacked his wife and wanted to humiliate her by á\ninsulting her. Then he turned violent and started to beat her in á\nfront of her child. She left it happen without saying a word in á\norder not to make things worse. I watched the scene and tried to á\ncalm the man, but without success. Just because he was stronger á\nwe had to comply. From that day I detested him.'),
	(1232, 'shame', 'For a medical check-up, we - boys and girls - had to take off our á\nclothes with the exception of our underwear. Then we had to go á\ninto another classroom where older pupils were sitting and á\nstaring at us.'),
	(1233, 'joy', 'One day I did not feel very well and I wanted to talk to á\nsomebody. A friend invited me for dinner and I was very glad.'),
	(1234, 'fear', 'I was driving my car and it was very misty. It was in the night á\nand I was alone in my car. I felt totally insecure, nervous and á\noverstrained.'),
	(1235, 'anger', 'My mother treated me unjustly as if I was a little child. I said á\nmean things. I was unable to defend myself adequately.'),
	(1236, 'sadness', 'When my uncle died whom I had loved very much. I was very sad and á\nI felt totally helpless.'),
	(1237, 'disgust', 'I watched the news at the TV, it was a commentary about á\n"Hainburg". I felt disgusted when I heard members of the union á\nspeak about the situation.'),
	(1238, 'shame', 'I took the tram without paying. There were many people around me á\nwhen I was caught by a controller. I felt ashamed but also angry.'),
	(1239, 'joy', 'A friend of mine often had difficulties with her parents. Once á\nshe had a child she had a better relationship with them.'),
	(1240, 'fear', 'Once our school class went skiing. On a steep slope a boy á\nstanding behind me lost his balance, fell down and drew me with á\nhim. I slided down the whole slope. At about 1 m distance from a á\ntree I could stop.'),
	(1241, 'anger', 'It happened in a tram: some older people started to grumble about á\nthe young people just because I had not immediately left my seat á\nto them.'),
	(1242, 'sadness', 'When I was younger I was very good in apparatus gymnastics. I á\nalways won in competitions, but once I was only at the fourth á\nplace.'),
	(1243, 'disgust', 'A friend was assaulted by a young man on her way home.'),
	(1244, 'shame', 'Some men were talking about me and my sister.'),
	(1245, 'joy', 'I received a letter and a Christmas present from a person I had á\nnot seen for two years.'),
	(1246, 'fear', 'I was at home alone and my mother had asked me to heat the house. á\nI put too much fuel into the stove. It began to glow and there á\nwas a noise in the whole house as if it was going to explode.'),
	(1247, 'anger', 'At the end of my holiday job I got less money than was due to me á\nand nobody mentioned anything about that.'),
	(1248, 'sadness', 'My little cat which I had raised all by myself, hanged itself when á\nplaying in the garden.'),
	(1249, 'disgust', 'At school a classmate who was a very good pupil had to help á\nanother boy who performed less well. He told him on purpose the á\nwrong things so that he had to repeat a year.'),
	(1250, 'shame', 'When I was a child I played my mother a nasty trick to make her á\nfeel hurt.'),
	(1251, 'joy', 'I have a boyfriend and I am very fond of him. When we had our á\n"11-months jubilee", I had forgotten it. But he gave me a red á\nrose.'),
	(1252, 'fear', 'When I was a child I was afraid of big dogs. One day when I came á\nhome a big dog was laying in front of our door. I was so á\nfrightened that I did not dare to enter the door and I waited á\nuntil somebody passed by.'),
	(1253, 'anger', 'I share my small flat with my friend. On her birthday we could á\nnot see each other until evening because we had to stay at the á\nUniversity all day. In the evening I left a lecture before it á\nfinished to be able to buy flowers for her. When I was at home á\nshe called me to tell me that she would stay the night with her á\nboyfriend.'),
	(1254, 'sadness', 'When I was a child I had a grass-parakeet I liked very much. His á\nlegs were crippled so that he could not move very fast. Once I á\ncame into the room, did not notice him and stepped on him. A few á\ndays later he died.'),
	(1255, 'disgust', 'When I was younger I often saw my father come home drunk (he had á\nbig problems at that time). Once he woke me up in the middle of á\nthe night and shouted at me.'),
	(1256, 'shame', 'At school I was bad in mathematics. Although my teacher had á\nadmonished me to do my homework, one day I had forgotten to do á\nit. When my teacher noticed it, I blushed and was ashamed to be á\nrebuked in front of the other pupils.á'),
	(1257, 'joy', 'After a weekend at a seminar I saw my husband again. I hurried á\nhome hoping he would be there. We embraced - I enjoyed feeling á\nhis body.'),
	(1258, 'fear', 'One evening I stayed at home all alone. As we lived on the ground á\nfloor, I was often afraid of burglers.'),
	(1259, 'anger', 'One day, when riding on a bicycle path, a car coming from the á\nopposite direction forced me to get off my bike although I had á\nthe priority.'),
	(1260, 'sadness', 'My father died unexpectedly at the age of 53 years. He certainly á\nwould have liked to live longer. I was also said because I was á\nconfronted with the fact that I would die one day too.'),
	(1261, 'disgust', 'One day, when I was twelve years old, my brother took some slimy á\nsubstance swimming on the surface of a pot of vinegar made of á\ncider and threatened to throw it at me.'),
	(1262, 'shame', 'When I was ten years old a classmate laughed at me because I had á\ntold him that my father had retired.'),
	(1263, 'joy', 'A party with friends on New Year\'s Eve.'),
	(1264, 'fear', 'When I was hitch-hiking and I went with a man who drived like a á\nmadman.'),
	(1265, 'anger', 'I was in "Hainburg" in December and I was angry about the á\npoliticians and the police.'),
	(1266, 'sadness', 'I met again a very good friend after a year and realized that á\nthere had grown a certain distance between us.'),
	(1267, 'disgust', 'When I listened to a conversation of friends talking about the á\npower of money.'),
	(1268, 'sadness', 'When my grandmother died - at her funeral.'),
	(1269, 'disgust', 'I read about a monk who had been murdered and put into a barrel á\nwhich was filled with blood of pigs.'),
	(1270, 'shame', 'I went for a walk with a very close friend; we were talking about á\nour problems, I told her lies.'),
	(1271, 'joy', 'I went to buy a bicycle with my father. When I wanted to pay, my á\nfather took his purse and payed.'),
	(1272, 'fear', 'My mother had fallen down from a ladder when she had been á\ngathering cherries. Her back was hurt. Just when I arrived, I saw á\npeople of the life-saving service giving her medical care.'),
	(1273, 'anger', 'I was waiting behind a car which was going to leave the parking á\nplace, because I wanted to park my car there. Because of uncoming á\ntraffic I had to wait for a short time - another driver placed á\nhis car on the place.'),
	(1274, 'sadness', 'My partner left me after we had been together for a long time.'),
	(1275, 'disgust', 'At a discussion a friend took a "faschistic view", what I had not á\nexpected.'),
	(1276, 'shame', 'At a weekend\'s seminar my trousers suddenly burst, therefore I was á\nprevented from participating in several activities.'),
	(1277, 'joy', 'Before Christmas I got to know a girl but our relationshop could á\nnot consolidate before the holiday. Therefore it was a big á\nsurprise to get a carefully hand-made present from her. - Our á\nrelationship grew closer.'),
	(1278, 'fear', 'When I was a child, I fell into a cellar (when playing) and could á\nbe freed only with big difficulties.'),
	(1279, 'anger', 'I was angry about several drivers who showed an aggressive and á\ndangerous driving habit.'),
	(1280, 'sadness', 'When my grandmother died. I had a very deep relation to her (I á\nlived with her for several years).'),
	(1281, 'disgust', 'Some time ago a girl tried to make me up without any action of my á\npart. She used all possible means. Although I behaved refusingly á\nshe did not give up for a longer time.'),
	(1282, 'shame', 'When I went to the sauna for the first time and there were men á\nand women.'),
	(1283, 'joy', 'A person whom I had not seen for a long time called me and á\ninvited me for a party.'),
	(1284, 'fear', 'When I was walking on the street, a group of drunk, bawling young á\npeople approached.'),
	(1285, 'anger', 'When I was house-hunting: Another person got a flat that I would á\nhave liked, too, because he heaped a floot of words on the á\nletter.'),
	(1286, 'joy', 'When my mother was tremendous on the phone and we talked for á\nhours. She was in a good mood.'),
	(1287, 'fear', 'When I saw a good male friend unexpectedly after a year, as I\'ve á\njust returned from overseas. I was feeling tired, looking a mess, á\nand nervous.'),
	(1288, 'anger', 'When I wanted to talk to someone I liked and whom I have been á\ntold likes me (by his brother and even by himself) however he á\navoids any confrontation, and is vague.'),
	(1289, 'sadness', 'After having left the company of someone who gave me a lot of á\nsupport and made me laugh, found myself alone for days on end.'),
	(1290, 'disgust', 'When a boy had continued to use foul language and swearing in á\nfront of a group of my friends.'),
	(1291, 'shame', 'When I was about seven or eight I was caught having stolen a á\ndoll\'s dress from my next-door neighbour.'),
	(1292, 'joy', 'When planning to marry.'),
	(1293, 'fear', 'No really strong such emotion. Just falling off to sleep when I á\ncaught sight of a 5 cm diameter spider crawling onto the pillow á\nbeside me.'),
	(1294, 'anger', 'My feelings towards would-be in-laws for their participation in á\nrecent broken relationship.'),
	(1295, 'sadness', 'Recent break-up of seriors long-term relationship, helped along á\nby would-be  in-laws.'),
	(1296, 'disgust', 'No very strong such emotion. Treatment of my sister by her á\ndancing instructor - he is a "user", i.e., takes advantage of her á\ngood nature.'),
	(1297, 'shame', 'After failing a second attempt at Med 4, following a number of á\ndifficult personal circumstances.'),
	(1298, 'joy', 'When Wayne and Sue (close friends) were announced our guardians á\nat ther wedding.'),
	(1299, 'fear', 'Car accident nearly occurred between us and drunk driver coming á\nin opposite direction it missed us by approx 1 m and collided á\n(after rolling twice midair) into nearby scrub.'),
	(1300, 'anger', 'When boyfriend lied to me.'),
	(1301, 'sadness', 'When my boyfriend took me to his father\'s grave.'),
	(1302, 'disgust', 'On boat trip - saw mother giving young child (aprox 6-7 years) á\ncigarettes.'),
	(1303, 'shame', 'When harassed by this boy - it was sexual (refer to GUILT).'),
	(1304, 'joy', 'Getting a part-time job.'),
	(1305, 'fear', 'Small car accident. Black ice on the road - cars in front of us á\nstarted zig-zagging and so did we. Car in front did a 180¦ turn we á\nfollowed and ended up in a gully.'),
	(1306, 'anger', 'People hunting animals.'),
	(1307, 'sadness', 'When my grandfather was sick, and died I felt more sad, though, á\nwhen he was sick.'),
	(1308, 'disgust', 'People spitting in railway stations.'),
	(1309, 'shame', 'Falling over.'),
	(1310, 'joy', 'When my last year\'s second semester results came through - I was á\necstatic.'),
	(1311, 'fear', 'I was sleeping in my room but woke in the middle of the night to á\nthink I could hear noises and see shadows moving. I felt that á\nsomeone was in the house.'),
	(1312, 'anger', 'At school, a couple of years ago, a so-called acquaintance told lies á\nabout me to a teacher I was told about it by friends who overheard á\nthe conversation.'),
	(1313, 'sadness', 'My grandfather died. He lived almost as a recluse not caring for á\nhimself as well as he should - Dad and we all helped as much as á\nwe could, but it didn\'t save him from himself. It was an á\nunexpected death. His second de facto wife was lucky she wasn\'t á\njailed.'),
	(1314, 'sadness', 'In my penultimate job I was responsible of a sections with á\nseveral employers, after several years of dedication I was á\ndismissed by a new chef, saying that I was incompetent.'),
	(1315, 'disgust', 'I assisted to a scene where the police attacked a person that á\ndidn\'t have his documents. The savagery was too much, and the á\nattacked person bleeded to much.'),
	(1316, 'shame', 'In a party of friends I got completely drunk.'),
	(1317, 'joy', 'When I get something that seemed very hard like getting a job, a á\nboyfriend, etc. A specific sutuations, was when I started to date á\na boy whom I liked for a long time.'),
	(1318, 'fear', 'When I had to assume a position which I didn\'t expect.'),
	(1319, 'anger', 'When I was dismissed unjustly from the firm where I worked, á\nbecause there where persons that didn\'t have problems, and á\nwouldn\'t miss in the jobs they occupied if they were dismissed.'),
	(1320, 'sadness', 'I felt very sad when I had to give up something that by right was á\nmine and although I didn\'t get it, a kind of suvenir that people á\ndon\'t give you the right to have.'),
	(1321, 'disgust', 'The acts of brutal violence in generally disgusts me. Fights, á\nphisical aggrssion, etc.'),
	(1322, 'shame', 'I felt ashamed when in a certain occasion I had to read a text á\nand didn\'t stop stuttering.'),
	(1323, 'anger', 'When I talked with a teacher yesterday who, to say the least, was á\nrude and unwise and had irrelevant opinions about a friend.'),
	(1324, 'sadness', 'The loss of the woman who loved me most till today.'),
	(1325, 'disgust', 'In a sexual experience with an unknown woman where after the á\nsexual act I only could go away without looking backwards.'),
	(1326, 'shame', 'When I wanted to kiss a friend and didn\'t succeed, I felt shame.'),
	(1327, 'joy', 'When I succeed in writing something I felt and doing it I felt á\nwell and very happy for being able to express to myself something á\nthat was suffocating me.'),
	(1328, 'fear', 'When I crashed my car.'),
	(1329, 'anger', 'When in a difficult moment I couldn\'t express myself correctly á\nand my thought came out with distortions bringing about highly á\nnegative and distorted results.'),
	(1330, 'sadness', 'When I heard about the death of somebody I liked very much and I á\nwas not present either to see the person or to try to share my á\nemotions with other friends.'),
	(1331, 'disgust', 'When I saw a woman subjugated by money and not being able to hide á\nhow she hated herself for not having the will power to get out of á\nsuch a situation because it was convenient, according to what she á\ntold me.'),
	(1332, 'shame', 'When somebody suddenly said something (about me) at a wrong á\nmoment and I didn\'t agree (at that exact moment I was needing an á\nextremely positive word).'),
	(1333, 'shame', 'When my mother surprised me while masturbating.'),
	(1334, 'joy', 'After my final examination at school I was glad that the á\nexamination was over and that I had passed it.'),
	(1335, 'fear', 'When I was a child, I had a nightmare. At that time, I was not á\nyet able to tell anybody about it, so I was very frightened. I á\ncould not explain myself all that and I had to deal with it by á\nmyself.'),
	(1336, 'anger', 'I was angry with a person who behaved terribly at a ball á\noffending her relatives.'),
	(1337, 'sadness', 'When my grandfather died. When I heard about his death, I had a á\nbad feeling in my stomach and I felt as if I had lost something á\nvery precious.'),
	(1338, 'disgust', 'My brother caught a spider and let his frog eat it.'),
	(1339, 'shame', 'Once I spoke without thinking very much - it was quite a á\nnonsense.'),
	(1340, 'joy', 'For about one year I had a rather bad relation with my father. á\nLast Christmas Eve he invited me to stay withhim and I was very á\nglad about it. It was a fine evening.'),
	(1341, 'fear', 'I live outside Graz - so I have to go by bus. One day I went home á\nfrom the bus stop alone. It was dark, I had to go through a á\nforest and there was a dark figure behind me. I was very á\nfrightened.'),
	(1342, 'anger', 'My sister had promised to help me to do a translation from á\nEnglish into German. But the day I needed her she told me that á\nshe was busy - I was very angry.'),
	(1343, 'sadness', 'Several years ago my mother died. She had been ill for a long á\ntime, but nevertheless her death came unexpectedly. I did not and á\nI still do not want to believe that it is true.'),
	(1344, 'disgust', 'I have a horror of spiders and snakes. On a walk through the wood á\nI saw the body of a slow-worm (without the head).'),
	(1345, 'shame', 'I came home from a party rather drunk. I said things I would á\nnever have said normally. Next morning I was terribly ashamed á\nabout what I had said.'),
	(1346, 'joy', 'I had a little cat which was very sick. As I liked it very much I á\nwent to a veterinary with it. He told me how to tend it and it á\nreally recovered its health. Everybody said that I had saved its á\nlife.'),
	(1347, 'fear', 'When I was a child, I had a terrible nightmare with St. Nicholas\' á\nDevil Servant. I asked my mother if he really existed and she á\nsaid yes. The following nights I could not sleep and a á\nlight had to be left turned on.'),
	(1348, 'anger', 'As I usually do not start learning until a short time before an á\nexamination,, I once made up my mind to try to work for a longer á\ntime. But once again I did not do it - and got a bad mark.'),
	(1349, 'sadness', 'A friend told me about his cousin who is my girlfriend. He said á\nshe had treated him in a mean and nasty way. I was surprised á\nbecause in front of other people she had always treated him in a á\nfriendly way. I am very sad about it.'),
	(1350, 'disgust', 'I went out with my sister, her boyfriend and his friend. I did á\nnot like this young man. But suddenly he overcame me and kissed á\nme. He was very strong so that I could not defend myself.'),
	(1351, 'shame', 'During the oral part of my final examination I made a mistake in á\nspeaking so that all the teachers laughed at me.'),
	(1352, 'joy', 'When I passed my final examination at school.'),
	(1353, 'fear', 'When I was on a cave excursion with friends, I suddenly lost them á\nand was afraid of losing my way in the cave.'),
	(1354, 'anger', 'When I felt being treated unjustly by a teacher.'),
	(1355, 'sadness', 'When my grandmother died; I had a stronger relation to her than á\nto my mother.'),
	(1356, 'disgust', 'When I was molested by an old drunk man.'),
	(1357, 'shame', 'When I had a Latin examination in school.'),
	(1358, 'joy', 'When I met my girlfriend again in another town after a long á\nseparation.'),
	(1359, 'fear', 'When I went home alone early in the morning, I had to go through á\na wood.'),
	(1360, 'anger', 'A friend was unpunctual, we wanted to prepare ourselves for an á\nexamination.'),
	(1361, 'sadness', 'When my grandparents moved to another part of the town.'),
	(1362, 'disgust', 'At the butcher\'s I saw an animal which had just been slaughtered; á\nblood was dripping on the floor.'),
	(1363, 'shame', 'In school I was very bad in running long distances and my á\nclass-mates laughed at me for this reason.'),
	(1364, 'joy', 'On my birthday, an old friend of mine sent me a card. I had not á\nmet him for a year and I was very glad that he had thought of me.'),
	(1365, 'fear', 'Once I spent a night with a friend at the secondary school. We á\ntold each other horror stories and suddenly we heard uncanny á\nnoises. I was terribly frightened.'),
	(1366, 'anger', 'When we still attended school, my brother and I usually went to á\nsee our aunt and to show her our term\'s report. She rewarded us á\nwith money. Although my reports were as good as my brother\'s, he á\ngot more money.'),
	(1367, 'sadness', 'My friend was pregnant, but lost her child during the second á\nmonth. I went to see her at hospital - she was crying. I felt á\nvery sorry for her.'),
	(1368, 'disgust', 'When I attended school, our class visited an institution for á\nmentally and physically handicapped persons. Although I tried to á\ncontrol my feelings, I was disgusted.'),
	(1369, 'shame', 'After a party I spent the night with a friend. We both were á\ndrunk, the morning was disillusioning. A friend was me leaving á\nthe room and I felt shabby and immoral.'),
	(1370, 'joy', 'A very good friend of mine had been away for three months. When á\nwe met again, we ran up to each other and embraced.'),
	(1371, 'fear', 'One evening my father told me to go into the cellar and get him a á\nbeer. I was terribly frightened at the idea of a man sitting in á\nthe cellar and assaulting me. For my defence I took an empty á\nbottle with me.'),
	(1372, 'anger', 'I had stolen a bottle of rum from a person who knows me well. He á\nthreatened to call the police if I did not pay 500 Shillings.'),
	(1373, 'sadness', 'When my uncle died I saw a funeral for the first time. All people á\nstood around the open grave and cried.'),
	(1374, 'disgust', 'At a party I met a girl who drew me to her, told me some nonsense á\nand always wanted to kiss me.'),
	(1375, 'shame', 'I put my head into the pullover of a girl to see her breasts. The á\ngirl looked at me so that I felt ashamed.'),
	(1376, 'joy', 'Several days after my final examination at school, I was sitting á\nin an airplane on my way to Greece. I enjoyed that moment very á\nmuch.'),
	(1377, 'fear', 'One night I was lying in my bed awake but I had my eyes closed. I á\nsaw figures with terrible faces and black frocks bending over me á\nand touching me. I opened my eyes but I could still see them. I á\nhad the feeling that somebody was in the room. It was terrible. á\nOnly when I turned on the light I was able to go to sleep.'),
	(1378, 'anger', 'I had arranged with a friend to go with him to Carinthia by car. á\nWe had arranged a place where to meet. I was a bit late and my á\nfriend had left already. I had no money to go by train. I nearly á\nstarted to cry because I was so angry - it was very important for á\nme to go to Carinthia.'),
	(1379, 'sadness', 'Our dog had to be shot because he had killed a roe. I liked him á\nvery much and so I could not resign myself to that. I hated the á\nhunter who shot him.'),
	(1380, 'disgust', 'I was sitting in a station-hall and watching a lavatory á\nattendant. She was very dirty. She started to eat something out á\nof a dirty cup - it must have been something like lard. Then she á\ntook some breadcrumbs out of the pockets of her apron and ate á\nthem. I had to leave - I felt like vomitting.'),
	(1381, 'shame', 'I had to go to the doctor\'s because of a veneral disease. I told á\nthe doctor that I must have been infected by my boy-friend. This á\nwas not true, but I was ashamed to tell the truth.'),
	(1382, 'joy', 'My neighbour was not able to set his car in motion because it had á\nsnowed heavily. I helped him - he was thankful and invited me.'),
	(1383, 'fear', 'I was skiing with friends and they wanted to ski-jump. I did not á\nwant to be left behind, so I braced myself and followed them.'),
	(1384, 'anger', 'At an examination I got a bad mark just because of a small á\nmistake. When I went to the lector and wanted to talk about that, á\nhe did not listen to me but sent me away.'),
	(1385, 'sadness', 'My cut was run over by a car. After searching for a long time I á\nfound her lying in a kerb. I was rather shocked and angry with á\nthe driver.'),
	(1386, 'disgust', 'When I watched a report about El Salvador on TV, I saw people who á\nhad been murdered by terrible methods.'),
	(1387, 'shame', 'At a cross-country race I wanted to take a short-cut (which is á\nnot allowed). I was caught and disqualified. All my friends had á\nobserved that.'),
	(1388, 'joy', 'On my birthday I got a present that I had desired for a long á\ntime.'),
	(1389, 'anger', 'When I am discussing something with a person and I realize that á\nthe other person is thinking over her own argumentations instead á\nof listening, I become angry.'),
	(1390, 'sadness', 'When we were on holidays my girl-friend had to leave me after 4 á\nweeks and I had to stay in Turkey for some more weeks because I á\nhad a job there.'),
	(1391, 'disgust', 'I studied medicine for several semesters. I was always disgusted á\nwhen we had the dissecting-course. I cannot understand why some á\npersons like this course.'),
	(1392, 'shame', 'Some time ago we had a tournament in our tennis-club. For á\ntactical reasons I was chosen to play against a much weaker á\nplayer than I am. Although it would have been enough simply to á\nwin the game, I defeated him extremely. This would not have been á\nnecessary.'),
	(1393, 'joy', 'On New Year\'s Eve I went in a disco with friends. I amused myself á\nand got to know many other people.'),
	(1394, 'fear', 'I had to go to the dentist\'s. When he touched my tooth with his á\ndrill, I was terribly aftaid of the pain I would feel any moment.'),
	(1395, 'anger', 'I was very hungry and just wanted to start eating when a friend á\ncalled me who usually talks for a long time. I was angry because á\nI was prevented from eating.'),
	(1396, 'sadness', 'My sister, whom I like very much, asked me for a favour which I á\nrefused her for some flimsy reason. Some time later I felt sorry á\nfor that and something like sadness.'),
	(1397, 'disgust', 'On my way to a concert I went with a man who tried to molest me. á\nAt that moment I did not care much but now the impression fills á\nme with disgust.'),
	(1398, 'shame', 'I asked my friend to come with me to a disco because I wanted to á\nbe with a person I know well. But when I amused myself with á\nothers I let my friend sit alone, although I had asked her to á\ncome.'),
	(1399, 'joy', 'I had a singing-lesson, but I was not very good. The last á\nexercise was singing scales. I did that very well and my teacher á\nseemed satisfied.'),
	(1400, 'fear', 'A teacher wanted to instill a certain opinion and a certain á\nbehaviour into myself, what I refused. I was afraid when I saw á\nhim.'),
	(1401, 'anger', 'A friend had promised to call me at a certain time. I expected á\nhis call impatiently but in vain.'),
	(1402, 'sadness', 'Years ago on Christmas Eve I felt very sad because I realized for á\nthe first time how I missed my father who had died at Christmas á\nYears ago.'),
	(1403, 'disgust', 'A man whom I like, was drunk and tried to molest me.'),
	(1404, 'shame', 'It was the time when everybody spoke about and discussed á\nHainburg. I was also asked for my opinion. I was ashamed because á\nI had no firm view of the whole thing and therefor was not able á\nto join the conversation.'),
	(1405, 'joy', 'On my 18th birthday I passed the driving-test. I was glad because á\nI had had to study very much, because I had been lucky and á\nbecause - as a proof that it was really difficult - not everybody á\nhad passed the test.'),
	(1406, 'fear', 'At about midnight I had to go by bike through Graz alone. On the á\nwhole it was a distance of several kilometers. A car followed me á\nthrough the streets. Only when I went into a one-way street the á\ncar disappeared. The rest of my way home I was very afraid.'),
	(1407, 'anger', 'I had studied for almost one week for my physics-examination. á\nWith difficulty I passed the examn. I was angry about the teacher á\nand also about myself because I had not remembered enough during á\nthe examn and because the time that I spent studying was wasted.'),
	(1408, 'sadness', 'I had cared for a horse for 2 years. One day it was sold and I á\ncried for several days because I was so sad.'),
	(1409, 'disgust', 'A friend of mine was telling jokes which I felt to be very á\ndisgusting, especially because I was eating.'),
	(1410, 'shame', 'At a carneval-party I smooched with a man - some days later I was á\nrather ashamed for that.'),
	(1411, 'joy', 'During my first week in Graz I met a girl who I had got to know á\nin the train from Amsterdam to Graz. Although I had considered á\nher very sympathetic, we had seperated without changing our á\nadresses.'),
	(1412, 'fear', 'Many years ago I saw the film "Psycho" by Hitchcock for the first á\ntime. When I saw the film I was alone and afterwards I hardly á\ndared to go to bed and hardly was able to sleep.'),
	(1413, 'anger', 'I had got a bad cold. My father said I must be crazy to go by á\nmotorbike at those temperatures. When I answered him that I did á\nnot care about a cold, he said that if I did not care for á\nanything I could leave him (it was for the second time he said á\nsomething like that).'),
	(1414, 'sadness', 'I was at home alone when I realized that a young roe approached á\nour house. I hid because I did not want to frighten it. It á\nlimped. Some time later, when I thought that it had already run á\naway, I saw it lying on our terrace. I came nearer and saw that á\nit was terribly wounded. I informed the ranger who said that the á\nroe must have been attacked by dogs. He had to shoot it.'),
	(1415, 'disgust', 'Several years ago I stayed with friends in the mountains for one á\nweek. We lived in a hut and had to cook for ourselves. One day my á\nfriend did not succeed in preparing spaghetti. That dinner was á\nterrible - nevertheless we all ate rather much and had an á\nimproper and unsavoury conversation.'),
	(1416, 'shame', 'My mother and my grandmother were talking about one of my á\ngrandmother\'s friends whom I hardly know. I gave some deprecatory á\ncomments on him whereupon my grandmother told me that the man had á\ndied recently.'),
	(1417, 'joy', 'I had not studied very much for my final examination at school, á\nso I had to take an additional examination in French. The oral á\nexamination was not very hard for me - the more I was glad when I á\nheard that I had passed it.'),
	(1418, 'fear', 'When I was 8 years old my tonsils had to be operated on. This is á\nnot a complicated operation, but just before it started I was á\nvery afraid so that I will never forget it.'),
	(1419, 'anger', 'My parents are divorced, father pays alimony for me. Two years á\nago my sister who lives with father, suddenly asked mother for á\nmoney. As she considered the amount of money my mother offered á\nher too small, she brought an action against mother. I was á\nterribly angry with my sister.'),
	(1420, 'sadness', 'I arranged with a friend to go skating the next day. He asked me á\nto wake him up by telephone at twelve o\'clock because we had come á\nhome late in the morning. Next day I called him - he was not at á\nhome. As something like that had happened to me several times á\nbefore, I came to the conclusion that one cannot rely on anybody á\nand I felt very sad.'),
	(1421, 'disgust', 'Whenever I see a spider or a snake I feel disgusted.'),
	(1422, 'shame', 'When I had slept with a boy for the first time I felt ashamed for á\nthree reasons. First, because I was only 13 years old, second, á\nbecause I did not really like him, third, because he had caught á\nme napping.'),
	(1423, 'joy', 'My boy-friend told me that he would take me to the training of á\nthe life-saving dogs.'),
	(1424, 'fear', 'I was in a dark cellar and saw a glowing red point. I thought á\nthat it was a person with a cigarette - but it was only the red á\nswitch.'),
	(1425, 'anger', 'A man treated his dog very badly - he insulted and beated him á\nuntil the dog kept lying on the floor with his tail drawn in.'),
	(1426, 'sadness', 'A horse which I had liked very much was taken away.'),
	(1427, 'disgust', 'On TV I saw a report about church in Amerika. A priest was shown á\nwho was performing miracles in front of the camera - I felt á\ndisgusted.'),
	(1428, 'shame', 'When I was a child, my uncle came to see us. I spit at him and á\nran out - I do not know the reason for that. My father came after á\nme and insisted on my apologizing.'),
	(1429, 'joy', 'To be able to prepare myself better for an important examination, á\nI did not spend the nitht with my girl-friend but in the á\nstudents\' hostel. I had not done that for months. The day when I á\nhad the examn, somebody knocked at my door at seven o\'clock in á\nthe morning. My girl-friend who likes sleeping late, had come to á\nbe able to be with me.'),
	(1430, 'fear', 'I studied medicine for several semesters and at that time I á\ndeveloped a great fear of examinations. I was most afraid of my á\nexamination of anatomy. While other students were examined, I was á\ndissecting. I was able to hear everything and was waiting with á\nfear until it was my turn.'),
	(1431, 'anger', 'When I come home in the evening, the first thing I do is to sit á\ndown and smoke a cigarette. One day I found the flat in a totally á\ndesolate state. My girl-friend had wanted to tidy up but had not á\nfinished.'),
	(1432, 'sadness', 'My son\'s mother told me that she wanted to move to Vienna and á\ntake the child with her. This means a rather long distance for á\nme. My whole family was sad and dumbfounded so that my own á\nfeelings were intensified.'),
	(1433, 'disgust', 'When a very near person got into an awkward situation but showed á\nonly helplessness and indecision.'),
	(1434, 'shame', 'I spent an evening with my girl-friend. When we wanted to go to á\nbed I was totally drunk. Next morning I felt rather ashamed.'),
	(1435, 'joy', 'After a long time I saw my boy-friend again.'),
	(1436, 'fear', 'My first public appearance in front of a rathe big audience.'),
	(1437, 'anger', 'I was angry about how the government acted concerning Hainburg, á\nespecially when I saw a discussion about it on TV.'),
	(1438, 'sadness', 'Death of my father; he died of laryngeal cancer.'),
	(1439, 'disgust', 'When I got indecent offers.'),
	(1440, 'shame', 'When I bought new skis; I was ashamed to tell the assistant that á\nI am not good at skiing and therefor bought racing skis.'),
	(1441, 'joy', 'I thought that I had failed an examination, but when I was á\ninformed about the mark, I saw that I had passed it.'),
	(1442, 'fear', 'Before an examination: I had the fealing that I had not learned á\nenough.'),
	(1443, 'anger', 'Once when I was playing table tennis I was already sure that I á\nwould win , but at last I lost the game.'),
	(1444, 'sadness', 'My grandfather\'s funeral.'),
	(1445, 'disgust', 'In cinema I saw a film which showed how a person was torn out his á\nguts when he was still alive.'),
	(1446, 'shame', 'I was sitting in a restaurant with friends. They asked me á\nsomething which they thought I should know. Actually I know it, á\nbut at that time I was not able to remember it.'),
	(1447, 'joy', 'When I had a psychical crisis, I met a girl, who told me that she á\nhad had almost the same problems and how she had finally overcome á\nthem.'),
	(1448, 'fear', 'I had climbed on a cherry tree alone and there was a thick á\ncaterpillar beside my fingers. I feel disgusted by caterpillars á\nand snakes. I was terribly afraid of the caterpillar crawling on á\nmy fingers. Out of the fear I was almost unable to climb down.'),
	(1449, 'anger', 'A friend of mine told other people that I was a slattern (because á\nof an occurence that had happened some time ago). When I heard á\nabout that I was very angry.'),
	(1450, 'sadness', 'My grandfather was seriously ill, he had only a few days left to á\nlive. I had always loved him, but never told him. When I saw him á\nfor the last time, I had the feeling that I had omitted so many á\nthings I could not do again. - There was a fly sitting on his á\nforehead and he was too weak to drive it away. I was very sad á\nwhen I saw that.'),
	(1451, 'disgust', 'Normally my father never tells vulgar jokes, we do not speak á\nabout sexual things, too. But once he told such a vulgar joke, á\nthat I was really disgusted. He did not tell me, but some of his á\nfriends, but I was present.'),
	(1452, 'shame', 'When I was 6 or 7 years old, I pulled down the trousers of a á\nfriend because I wanted to know what she looked like. My mother á\nwatched that and (as a punishment) sent me into the house. We á\nnever spoke about that; I think it was as embarassing for her as á\nit was for me.'),
	(1453, 'joy', 'Unexpectedly I met some persons who I like very much. á\nSpontaneously they invited me and integrated me within their á\ngroup, although it was late in the evening.'),
	(1454, 'fear', 'After a footballmatch I went home by car, a friend drove. I did á\nnot realize that he was drunk until we were in the car. He was á\nmadly racing. Several times we were in dangerous situations and I á\ntold him to be cautious, but he did not care.'),
	(1455, 'anger', 'A friend of mine uses butter instead of oil when he is cooking. I á\nam always angry about that, because it is an unnecessary luxury. á\nRecently we both were cooking and he wanted to use butter again. á\nWhen I had already put the oil into the pan, he poured it out á\nagain and put the butter into the pan.'),
	(1456, 'sadness', 'After some friends had come to see me. They had stayed for á\nseveral days and we had got on very well. When they had left, I á\nhad a feeling of emptyness.'),
	(1457, 'disgust', 'I had a quarrel with a friend who lived with me in the same flat. á\nHe moved out. Before he went he invited me and some friends for a á\ndrink. At last he was totally drunk and smelled disgusting. á\nBesides, he told lies about us and behaved as if he was to be á\npitied.'),
	(1458, 'shame', 'I went to see a friend. There were other people, too, and á\neverybody brought some present. I was the onlyone who brought á\nnothing. My friend was very hospitable and did not show anything á\n- although I knew how he felt.'),
	(1459, 'joy', 'I had a quarrel with my fiancT. When he admitted his fault, á\neverything was allright. It was then for the first time that he á\nsurprised me with coffee and cake and a bunch of flowers.'),
	(1460, 'fear', 'After my boy-friend had beaten me for the first time, I always á\ntrembled when somebody knocked on my door or when I heard steps á\ncoming nearer.'),
	(1461, 'anger', 'I had not eaten anything for 2 days to be able to pay the fine á\nfor my fiancT. But he stayed in another town and spent one á\nthousand shillings in the restaurant during the same time.'),
	(1462, 'sadness', 'I had to give up my love, because it did not work out well.'),
	(1463, 'disgust', 'I was insulted without a reason by a drunk man.'),
	(1464, 'shame', 'My boyfriend had drunk too much and beaten me. When I had to show á\nthe letter the door, which was almost crashed, I felt ashamed.'),
	(1465, 'joy', 'My sister had a daughter. I saw the baby for the first time á\nthrough a pane of glass and she looked at me.'),
	(1466, 'fear', 'My mother, my sister and I were sitting in the sitting room and á\nwatching a film on TV. My father came home drunk and told us to á\nturn off. When we did not do that he switched off the fuse and á\nstarted shouting. We were sitting in the dark and I was afraid á\nthat he would do us a harm.'),
	(1467, 'anger', 'I bought an aquarium which made me much pleasure. I was watching á\nthe fish when my father came in and asked me how much I had payed á\nfor it. He said he would not pay for the current that it would á\nrequire.'),
	(1468, 'sadness', 'When I was 9 years old, I got a cat, but after 3 days he died. I á\nwas very sad, because I had nursed him and taken him to the á\nveterinary\'s - but in vain. Although I had had him only for a á\nshort time I had liked him very much.'),
	(1469, 'disgust', 'When my grandmother was about 80 years old, she lived with us for á\nseveral years. I saw her illness. I did not even want to breath á\nthe air that smelled of her presence.'),
	(1470, 'shame', 'I am left-handed. When I attended the first form, we learned to á\nwrite with pens. I smeared everything I had written. All my á\nfriends had written well and wanted to know why the teacher was á\nlooking at my note-book. I was ashamed.'),
	(1471, 'joy', 'When I was 17, I had a mystic vision. I melted into a dazzling á\nlight, which omitted perfect love. The physical experience became á\nunimportant, I heard or saw the words "overcome egotism". The á\nfeeling of joy remained for month after that experience.'),
	(1472, 'fear', 'When we had swimming instruction, we had to take a header from á\nthe springboard. I usually refused to do that, but at least I was á\nforced to.'),
	(1473, 'anger', 'When I played in a chess championship, I was disturbed by other á\npeople. I asked them to be quiet, but in vain.'),
	(1474, 'sadness', 'When my flute-teacher was replaced by a new one.'),
	(1475, 'disgust', 'When I was a child, I was sometimes forced to eat things that á\ndisgusted me.'),
	(1476, 'shame', 'When I was 12 years old, some friends of our family had come to á\nwatch TV. I lay on the floor and moved my pelvis. When the other á\npeople had gone, my mother told me that it had looked as if I had á\nwanted to make sex.'),
	(1477, 'joy', 'When I was in a situation which seemed hopeless for me, I moved á\nback to my parents. For my father it went without saying anything á\n(normally he ofter grumbles at me).'),
	(1478, 'fear', 'I lived in a flat with a couple. The woman was so jealous of me, á\nthat she sometimes had crying fits. Eventually her husband could á\nnot stand that any more and wanted to kill me.'),
	(1479, 'anger', 'I have a very big family. At my grandmother\'s funeral we all met á\nand everybody pretended mourning. In reality it was like a á\nfashion-show: everybody wanted to show himself.'),
	(1480, 'sadness', 'Often a dog which is treated very badly by his owner comes to us.'),
	(1481, 'disgust', 'After a pleasant evening with friends in my flat, one of them did á\nnot want to leave, because he wanted to sleep with me. He said á\nthat he had fallen in love with me, that he felt alone and so on.'),
	(1482, 'shame', 'I look up to my Karate-teacher. When I came to a training lesson á\nafter I had not trained for one week, I was totally stiff. I was á\nashamed.'),
	(1483, 'joy', 'When I heard that I had passed my final examination at school á\n(with success).'),
	(1484, 'fear', 'Before my final examination.'),
	(1485, 'anger', 'When my mother kept me in leading-strings.'),
	(1486, 'sadness', 'When my father died.'),
	(1487, 'disgust', 'When I worked at the life-saving sevice and saw the first exitus.'),
	(1488, 'shame', 'When I made a fool at an examination.'),
	(1489, 'joy', 'Last year I went to see friends in Yugoslavia - two girls with á\nwhom I get along very well.'),
	(1490, 'fear', 'Before I went to the urologist\'s I was afraid for several á\nreasons: because it was for the first time, because the medical á\ncheck-up might be painful, because of the uncertainty and because á\nsomeone had informed me about it.'),
	(1491, 'anger', 'My girl-friend did not understand me; I was angry with myself á\nbecause I had problems when we seperated - I could not resign á\nmyself to it.'),
	(1492, 'sadness', 'A friend who was 22 years old died.'),
	(1493, 'disgust', 'When I was in the army, we got a certain dish for dinner that I á\ndo not like at all. We were not obliged to eat, but I was very á\nhungry.'),
	(1494, 'shame', 'I had to pay a fine because of speeding.'),
	(1495, 'joy', 'When we got a young dog.'),
	(1496, 'fear', 'I was afraid before I went to the doctor\'s.'),
	(1497, 'anger', 'I had an accident with damage to the car body.'),
	(1498, 'sadness', 'My dog died of a cerebral tumor.'),
	(1499, 'disgust', 'When I worked at the life-saving service I was disgusted by a á\npatient whose outward appearance was distasteful.'),
	(1500, 'shame', 'When I was a child, I had a medical check-up. I had to undress á\nmyself and was examined by several doctors.'),
	(1501, 'joy', 'When I heard that a good friend, who had been abroad for a long á\ntime, would come and see me.'),
	(1502, 'fear', 'When I had my first oral examination after a long time; á\nespecially one day before the examination when I had the feeling á\nthat I had not studied enough and had not enough time to make up á\nfor it.'),
	(1503, 'anger', 'I heard friends grumbling at me in an adjoining room, although á\nthey had behaved in a friendly way when I was present.'),
	(1504, 'sadness', 'When my brother died.'),
	(1505, 'disgust', 'I read about a murderer who brutalized his victims by cutting á\nopen their stomaches and taking out their bowels.'),
	(1506, 'shame', 'When I was a child: I had told my mother a lie and she found it á\nout.'),
	(1507, 'joy', 'I unexpectedly got a present from my father.'),
	(1508, 'fear', 'When I had to go through lonely streets in the middle of the á\nnight.'),
	(1509, 'anger', 'My boy-friend had promised me to come home at about 10 p.m. He á\ndid not return until midnight and had consumed a lot of alcohol.'),
	(1510, 'sadness', 'A relative, whom I like very much, left for the United States.'),
	(1511, 'disgust', 'When I was walking on the street, I slipped on the dung of a dog. á\nI did not fall down, but I felt disgusted by the bad smell on my á\nsole.'),
	(1512, 'shame', 'Some persons, who are important for me, came to see me and I had á\nnot washed the dishes.'),
	(1513, 'joy', 'I met again a very good friend whom I had not seen for a long á\ntime.'),
	(1514, 'fear', 'I got lost in a foreign town. I did not know the language of that á\ncountry and it took me hours to meet my friends again.'),
	(1515, 'anger', 'A friend had promised to get me a book which was very important á\nfor my work, but she forgot it.'),
	(1516, 'sadness', 'My dog, whom I had had for eleven years, died. I watched his á\nsoporification.'),
	(1517, 'disgust', 'A drunk man bumped into me and wanted to grip me. Fortunately I á\nwas able to break loose.'),
	(1518, 'shame', 'When I stayed on a nudism beach, a man was watching me in a á\ndisagreeable way. I had the feeling that he was examining my á\nbody.'),
	(1519, 'joy', 'My friend came to see me after she had stayed abroad. I waited at á\nthe station.'),
	(1520, 'fear', 'After a motor accident (I was the frong-seat-passenger) I spit á\nblood.'),
	(1521, 'anger', 'At an office an application that I had made was turned down á\nbecause of a scrupulous interpretation of the rules.'),
	(1522, 'sadness', 'My uncle died - I felt sad at the funeral.'),
	(1523, 'disgust', 'I saw a drunk man tottering behind his wife and insulting her á\nawfully.'),
	(1524, 'shame', 'After an oral examination I shook the professor\'s hand, but he á\nhad only stretched it out for my ball-point-pen.'),
	(1525, 'joy', 'I bought a Christmas present for my girl-friend. On my way home I á\nwas really glad about having found such a suitable thing.'),
	(1526, 'fear', 'My fear appeared in the form of jealousy. I was afraid that my á\ngirl-friend had fallen in love with another man, I was afraid to á\nlose her.'),
	(1527, 'anger', 'I was angry when I watched a ski-race. All the Austrian skiers á\ndropped out.'),
	(1528, 'sadness', 'During my holiday I met again a friend who had tried to commit á\nsuicide. She had just left hospital, her lips were trembling, she á\nlooked miserable.'),
	(1529, 'disgust', 'On my way home in the middle of the night I saw a drunk man and a á\nwoman who were quarreling, beating each other, shouting and so á\non. I felt disgusted especially because they treated each other á\nin such a degrading way.'),
	(1530, 'shame', 'My girl-friend and I live in one flat with another couple. We get á\nalong very well and usually we share everything. Once we two were á\nsitting in our room and eating a cake when the others came in.'),
	(1531, 'joy', 'I went to fetch my girl-friend at the station. When the train á\narrived and I saw her descending and running up to me, I felt á\nglad.'),
	(1532, 'fear', 'When I wanted to go into a house, there was suddenly a big dog á\nstanding beside me. It was hardly moving, but I did not know how á\nit would react later on.'),
	(1533, 'anger', 'My father had bought too many goods for his shop, there was not á\nenough space to store them.'),
	(1534, 'sadness', 'A friend died of cancer when he was 18 years old.'),
	(1535, 'disgust', 'At a party I saw two persons having a fight. The aggressions and á\nthe hate between these persons produced an unpleasant impression á\non me.'),
	(1536, 'shame', 'During a discussion I said something rather stupid and á\nunnecessary.'),
	(1537, 'joy', 'On my birthday a friend came to see me unexpectedly and brought á\nme flowers. I usually do not see her very often.'),
	(1538, 'fear', 'I was awakened by a dream in the middle of the night. I dreamt á\nthat a stranger was in my house.'),
	(1539, 'anger', 'My boy-friend had promised me to come an 10 a.m. - he was 3 hours á\nlate.'),
	(1540, 'disgust', 'When I heard about a murder of a 16-year-old girl.'),
	(1541, 'shame', 'When I broke the piggy bank of my brother and my mother á\ndiscovered that.'),
	(1542, 'joy', 'After I had been away for a long time a friend told me that I had á\npassed all my written examinations.'),
	(1543, 'fear', 'Recently my younger brother disappeared for two days without á\nleaving a trace. Usually he tells me when he wants to do á\nsomething like that, therefore I was afraid that something had á\nhappened to him.'),
	(1544, 'anger', 'I played chess with my 12-year-old brother. I made a stupid á\nmistake - and he won!'),
	(1545, 'sadness', 'It was only once that I really felt sad: at my grandfather\'s á\nfuneral (after a long time of suffering he had died of cancer).'),
	(1546, 'disgust', '3 years ago I served in the army. Once a collegue denounced me á\nbecause of a delict, which is usually committed. I was arrested á\nfor 3 days. I still detest this man.'),
	(1547, 'shame', 'Once I went home totally drunk and roused all our neighbours from á\nsleep.'),
	(1548, 'joy', 'After I had had a disappointment in my private life, my friend, á\nwho studies in Vienna, came to see me spontaneously.'),
	(1549, 'fear', 'Before an oral examination - which I did not take eventually.'),
	(1550, 'anger', 'A friend had promised me to give me a lift to Graz. To be sure I á\ncalled her before we went. She told me that she had just promised á\nanother person to give him a lift.'),
	(1551, 'sadness', 'I am sad because some relations to friends are not very good.'),
	(1552, 'disgust', 'I think I have hardly had a situation where I felt disgusted. á\nPerhaps once, when I saw a big spider.'),
	(1553, 'shame', 'When my boy-friend left me and I wanted to persuade him to stay.'),
	(1554, 'joy', 'Seeing relations from overseas after a few years.'),
	(1555, 'fear', 'Unknown person knocking repeatedly on backdoor when no one else á\nwas at home.'),
	(1556, 'anger', 'Boyfriend "chatting up" another girl.'),
	(1557, 'sadness', 'A friend breaking up with her boyfriend.'),
	(1558, 'disgust', 'Accidentally seeing a friend in a compromising situation with a á\nstranger.'),
