	(2298, 'anger', 'They wanted something to happen but I didn\'t.'),
	(2299, 'sadness', 'I couldn\'t be with a girl on whom I was very keen.'),
	(2300, 'disgust', 'I and my friends got acquainted with a guy from Sofia who turned á\nout to be gay, but we found that out only after 2 or 3 days.'),
	(2301, 'shame', 'My first girlfriend. I had the feeling that she was going out á\nwith me only because of my defect.'),
	(2302, 'joy', 'Having passed an exam.'),
	(2303, 'fear', 'Having a car accident.'),
	(2304, 'anger', 'I shared a secret with a friend and it later turned out that he á\nhad revealed it to another person with whom I didn\'t get along very well.'),
	(2305, 'sadness', 'The loss of a very good friend.'),
	(2306, 'disgust', 'Negative statement concerning me of a friend before strangers.'),
	(2307, 'shame', 'Adultery with the girlfriend of a friend of mine, of which he á\nlearned.'),
	(2308, 'joy', 'I\'m glad when I have good relations with my colleagues and most á\nof all when we are at a party.'),
	(2309, 'fear', 'I experienced it once when we were on a drive. Our car passed by á\nthe one comming from the opposite direction at an incredibly á\nsmall distance.'),
	(2310, 'anger', 'I get angry with people who attain certain status without á\ndeserving it, only with the support, authority and influence of á\nother people.'),
	(2311, 'sadness', 'I feel sad when I see things done against men and nothing could á\nstop it - at least I think so.'),
	(2312, 'disgust', 'I have experienced disgust with some people - usually double á\ndealers.'),
	(2313, 'shame', 'I am ashamed when I am not prepared in a subject and I have to á\nanswer in the presence of the patients.'),
	(2314, 'joy', 'I experienced it when I was accepted at the Medical Higher á\nInstitute.'),
	(2315, 'fear', 'I felt it when I sat for my exam in anatomy.'),
	(2316, 'anger', 'I experience that feeling when I am unsulted without deserving á\nit or when someone deceives me.'),
	(2317, 'disgust', 'I feel disgusted with toadies, hypocrites, chameleons.'),
	(2318, 'shame', 'When I do something unworthy.'),
	(2319, 'joy', 'After each successfully passed exam I am happy.'),
	(2320, 'fear', 'A friend of mine gave birth to a child. Very dangerous delivery. á\nI was afraid for her and for the baby.'),
	(2321, 'anger', 'I get angry when someone imputes on me things I never can do, á\nnaturally negative. Servility, "connections", impudence, traits á\nthat get me mad.'),
	(2322, 'sadness', 'My brother is a soldier. He promised to come home in a furlough á\nbut in the last moment he phoned and said that he could not come.'),
	(2323, 'disgust', 'I am disgusted with liers, hypocrites, slanderers, flunkeys.'),
	(2324, 'shame', 'Recently I saw a young girl fawning on a man. And what for - á\nmoney and things. I was ashamed to be a woman.'),
	(2325, 'joy', 'After the term exams I happened to meet a person that I respect á\nand of whom I think very highly. It was nice that although we see á\neach other rarely he had not forgotten me.'),
	(2326, 'fear', 'Few years ago my father was very ill. He stayed at a hospital for á\na long time. Then I experienced that terrible feeling that I á\nmight lose him.'),
	(2327, 'anger', 'I have a friend that I deeply trusted but it happened that I lost á\nmy confidence in her for which she herself was to blame.'),
	(2328, 'sadness', 'We are several friends but our characters are very different and á\nwe inevitably split in the two extremes. It is sad that I myself á\ndon\'t know what to do, I try not to hurt either of the "parties" á\nbecause there are conflicts to which one I should belong.'),
	(2329, 'disgust', 'I stayed for several weeks with a friend of mine before she moved á\nto live with her husband. One evening he came drunk and made an á\nawful scene, which I still remember.'),
	(2330, 'shame', 'In the past I experienced this feeling almost all the time - á\nwherever I went, in different sutuations. I was small and I had á\nto be taken to kindergarten, but me the fool didn\'t dare to tell á\nexactly where, finally as a result I was late.'),
	(2331, 'joy', 'I experienced this feeling when I was accepted as a student. á\nBecause everything turned out different from my expectations. á\nAlthough I passed the exam successfully I was accepted as a á\nstudent only when I didn\'t expect it at all, namely at the á\nbeginning of September.'),
	(2332, 'fear', 'In the real sense of the word I experienced fear in my first á\nmonths in the army. During my first night of duty. The cause for á\nall this was a bear. I became panic sticken (may be for the first á\ntime) and even forgot that I had a gun.'),
	(2333, 'anger', 'When I was a soldier I quarrelled with my commander and may be in á\nrevenge for this he detailed me on duty two successive nights. á\nNaturally he checked me up on the second night and found me á\nasleep for which he sent me to the cells.'),
	(2334, 'sadness', 'Sometimes I experience sadness for the Sports High School and for á\nmy unrealized dreams in the sport. Anyway there I spent six years á\nof my life.'),
	(2335, 'disgust', 'Sort of awkward. I\'d introduced (a lover) but introduced as a á\nfriend to some members of my family, and my niece Yavanna who\'s á\nsix was home from school and at Mum\'s and Dad\'s and was really á\nsilly and at first it was ok, but it went on and on - yukky pooh! á\nYou eat your snot, etc. and I felt cross she wouldn\'t stop. But á\nshe had an audience and was in one of those moods. Once I\'d á\naccepted it was something everyone does at time I felt better - á\nit was partly having my friend there.'),
	(2336, 'shame', 'In my 20s - and was going out to dinner to celebrate a friend\'s á\nbirthday. Her (older - in 30s) cousin, really wanted me to get á\ndrunk cos I\'d visited their (cousin & wife) place quite a bit, á\nbut had always been very careful - brought up to believe in á\nmoderation in drink (but not guilt repression etc). I mixed á\ndrinking with smoking (which I rarely did) and got drunk and had á\nto leave the table to get sick in the loo, and later went home á\nand was sick again; have never felt so awful in my life. And I á\ndidn\'t want to face or tell my other flatmates, or family.'),
	(2337, 'joy', 'Spontaneous picnic with sister and friend and children - great.'),
	(2338, 'fear', 'Can think of no time that I have felt fear.'),
	(2339, 'anger', 'Teenage neighbours smashed my letterbox for the fifth time in a á\ncouple of months. It was a deliberate action of kids who had á\nstayed in my home, had meals there yet took a dislike to my á\ndaughter.'),
	(2340, 'sadness', 'Guy I cared for went back to Canada to live.'),
	(2341, 'disgust', 'Bus driver driving roughly - old man fell off seat into aisle - á\ndriver wouldn\'t stop - disgusted with her behaviour.'),
	(2342, 'shame', 'A daughter in court for staff pilfering, she was dressed like a á\n"street walker" - I had a friend form overseas with me and was á\nfalsely trying to impress with my family.'),
	(2343, 'joy', 'Meeting with two of my friends I had not seen for 15 years. They á\nwere special people to me.'),
	(2344, 'fear', 'I was in the Korean War. We were attacked with mortars, me and á\ncompanion. We stopped the jeep and ran for cover. Fortunately á\nneither of us was hit but we both came close to being killed.'),
	(2345, 'anger', 'I\'ve a situation of responsibility an employee who had a habit of á\nbeing late, came late again after promising to say he would be at á\nwork in a few minutes, then arrived 3 hours later. He had been á\ndrinking.'),
	(2346, 'sadness', 'My brother in law was dying of cancer. To see him wasting away á\nwas very sad.'),
	(2347, 'disgust', 'Disgust at myself when I stroked a sleeping girl\'s private parts.'),
	(2348, 'shame', 'My son was apprehended for shoplifting at the age of 14. Because á\nI too had been apprehended at the same age I felt the shame of á\nnot having been able to prevent my son from acting in the same á\nway.'),
	(2349, 'joy', 'When we took out an 84 year old woman for the evening and had á\nhamburgers. She described the evening out as her happiest night á\nout in 20 years.'),
	(2350, 'fear', 'While tramping on a narrow path two of us were confronted by a á\nwoman with two snarling dogs, demanding we get off the property - á\nvia a flooded river !'),
	(2351, 'anger', 'A friend got angry and drove "like a lunatic" with me and others á\nin his car. I was angry about his dangerous driving.'),
	(2352, 'sadness', 'A boy I look after for the probation service deliberately á\noffended to provoke a reaction from the police.'),
	(2353, 'disgust', '4-letter words on a TV programme (Roche) while we were á\nentertaining "conservative" relations who wanted to see the first á\nepisode.'),
	(2354, 'shame', 'A young visitor to the house stole money from an elderly á\nvisitor\'s purse. It wasn\'t noticed for some hours.'),
	(2355, 'joy', 'I was seriously injured in a road accident. The very first steps á\nI took with only one crutch to support me I felt so good. I enjoy á\nbeing alive.'),
	(2356, 'fear', 'I was attacked, standing in a doorway, by a pack of 5 dogs, á\nalsatians and farm dogs with my escape route blocked by a shut á\nfence.'),
	(2357, 'anger', 'In the house where I live there is a new flatmate. His friends á\nunfortunately are the dirt of society, intelligent, fashonable, á\nrich and bored. At a party recently they were doing things I á\ndidn\'t like done in my house. I felt angry at them.'),
	(2358, 'sadness', 'I was driving near my girlfriend\'s house and I decided to keep á\ngoing because it was late and I would be back in the next few á\ndays anyway. The next day she was killed in a road accident.'),
	(2359, 'disgust', 'My girlfriend came home after a business dinner at the most á\nexpensive place in town drunk as a skunk. Whats more she drove á\nhome and couldn\'t remember doing so. I was disgusted by her state á\nand her actions.'),
	(2360, 'shame', 'A good friend of mine told me in comfidence that once he had á\ntried to commit suicide. To meet him you wouldn\'t think so. I á\ntold another friend of mine about this when she was feeling á\ndepressed about her twin brother\'s suicide. I broke a bond of á\nconfidentiality.'),
	(2361, 'joy', 'When I found out that a set task (i.e. 2 essays and a test), the á\nthought of which had oppressed me, were not on the date I had á\nthought.'),
	(2362, 'fear', 'When confronted and in my opinion hassled by the police.'),
	(2363, 'disgust', 'Disgust - no. Maybe it is more precise to say revultion at a worm á\nor a snake. But I mean it in a social aspect when somebody had á\nbehaved like a scoundrel to you, when by his actions he has made á\nyou change your attitude towards him but I thing this feeling the á\nway I meant it, is not typical for the people interrelations.'),
	(2364, 'shame', 'When you betray the trust you have been given. This is connected á\nwith copying at a class-work at school.'),
	(2365, 'joy', 'When, for example, I was in my eleventh school year and I learned á\nI had been classed for the Bulgarian Language and Literature á\nNational Olympiad.'),
	(2366, 'fear', 'When, for example, my grandfather fell seriously ill. It was á\nnecessary for him to be operated and I felt great fear of losing á\nhim because he is so dear to me.'),
	(2367, 'anger', 'When, for example, I was not approved to continue my studies at á\nthe Moscow University, no matter that I had the highest marks and á\nin general the best records of all the candidates.'),
	(2368, 'sadness', 'When, for example, I left for the first time my parents and I á\nwent to live in Sofia.'),
	(2369, 'disgust', 'When, for example, someone is calumnating.'),
	(2370, 'shame', 'When, for example, I fail in my undertakings.'),
	(2371, 'joy', 'Some time ago a close relative of mine got off cheap with the á\nworst.'),
	(2372, 'fear', 'The last time I felt it was when I was coming home late at night.'),
	(2373, 'anger', 'I haven\'t often felt this feeling. Once someone stole my garment.'),
	(2374, 'sadness', 'Recently I happened to remain alone for a long time.'),
	(2375, 'disgust', 'I don\'t remember about a situation when I have experienced this á\nfeeling. Maybe it was when I saw a drunkard in the street.'),
	(2376, 'shame', 'I lied to my best friend and I wouldn\'t reform what I had done.'),
	(2377, 'joy', 'Realizing one\'s desire, an experienced feeling of satisfaction á\nfrom the realization of one\'s desires and aims.'),
	(2378, 'fear', 'Fear of the loss of a close friend, of feeling the ground slipping á\nfrom under my feet.'),
	(2379, 'anger', 'Attitude to some manners of dealing and some "sanctioned" á\nrelations.'),
	(2380, 'sadness', 'Feeling unable to preserve one\'s ideas and ambitions as innocent á\nas they are when you are young.'),
	(2381, 'disgust', 'Attitude to a related family.'),
	(2382, 'shame', 'Exaggerating certain circumstances, wrong attitude and evaluation á\nof these circumstances.'),
	(2383, 'joy', 'I won a sport contest.'),
	(2384, 'fear', 'If a close relative\'s life is in danger.'),
	(2385, 'anger', 'A close person lied to me.'),
	(2386, 'sadness', 'Getting separated from my girlfriend.'),
	(2387, 'disgust', 'Encouter with a prostitute.'),
	(2388, 'shame', 'A theft committed by me.'),
	(2389, 'fear', 'Before an examination.'),
	(2390, 'anger', 'Unjust punishment of a friend of mine.'),
	(2391, 'sadness', 'After the loss of a close relative.'),
	(2392, 'disgust', 'When somebody behaves like a scoundrel. Recently a colleague of á\nmine used the name of another one for his own benefit.'),
	(2393, 'shame', 'I travelled on a bus and I forgot to punch the ticket. A ticket á\ncollector came in and I had to pay the fine. I did it with a feeling á\nof shame.'),
	(2394, 'joy', 'Meeting a loved man.'),
	(2395, 'fear', 'I felt a physical fear, if I can call it this way, today, in the bus where á\nI was sitting on the first seat. While turning the driver didn\'t á\nsee the tram which was making a dash towards us (coming from the á\nside I was), and whose driver intended to cross in yellow á\nlight.'),
	(2396, 'anger', 'At an unjust, or to be more precise, at a bureaucratic treatment á\nof one\'s personality.'),
	(2397, 'sadness', 'When one is alone and knows that all the others are celebrating.'),
	(2398, 'disgust', 'At the sight of an insect, such as the black-beetle.'),
	(2399, 'shame', 'When not fulfilling any of my obligations to a person whom I á\nrespect.'),
	(2400, 'joy', 'I sensed such a feeling when I understood I was admitted to the á\nUniversity. I was at home, the atmosphere was still, though I á\nmyself was full of suspense. I tried to do different things. When á\nthe telephone rang and...! Yes, of course there were other á\nsituations when I felt a similar feeling but I was unmindful of á\nthem.'),
	(2401, 'fear', 'This feeling I sensed quite recently. It was arisen by the á\nterrific thought that I might lose the man I loved !'),
	(2402, 'anger', 'Anger I felt when my boyfriend told me he didn\'t mind breaking it á\noff with me, i.e. each of us to take his own road. Because until á\nthat moment, he deliberately restricted our dates. The motives á\nwere brought to my knowledge later.'),
	(2403, 'sadness', 'Sometimes, when I\'m alone I am seized by this feeling. But it á\nalways helps me to come round and at the same time to judge if it á\nis worth. Very often this feeling is caused to me by people - á\nfriends who I love and respect.'),
	(2404, 'disgust', 'Such a feeling springs up in me sometimes when I have meals at a á\ncatering establishment. It is a result either of the look of the á\nfood or when watching the way some people eat.'),
	(2405, 'shame', 'This happens to me when I am not prepared in a given subject.'),
	(2406, 'joy', 'When I was admitted to the University.'),
	(2407, 'fear', 'I had to have my tonsils out. I had been making up my mind almost á\nfor a year - I was afraid. But during the two hours in the á\nhospital room, while I was waiting to be called for the operation I á\nfelt a real fear - of the pain, of what they were going to do to á\nme, of the unknown.'),
	(2408, 'anger', 'In a conversation my boyfriend expressed definite and quite á\npretentious opinions and he took up an attitude towards a theory á\nwhich he himself had never known. His information was from á\nfortuitous sources.'),
	(2409, 'sadness', 'Summer, heavy rain, storm - I was standing with my face stick to á\nthe window: the childhood, something was going away forever this á\nsummer, I was leaving my home, I was going to study in another á\ntown, for the first time I was leaving my parents, friends, I had á\nto manage myself, a long and loved period of my life was over - I á\nwas crying.'),
	(2410, 'disgust', 'I saw in the street a man spitting.'),
	(2411, 'shame', 'I talked with a man who stammered and without controlling myself, á\nI started to talk imitating him.'),
	(2412, 'joy', 'When I understood that I was admitted to the University.'),
	(2413, 'fear', 'I felt this feeling when one day my landlord\'s cat had crept á\nunder my bed and I couldn\'t cope with it during an hour and a á\nhalf.'),
	(2414, 'anger', 'I feel this feeling when I am to fill in a questionnaire or a á\nform.'),
	(2415, 'sadness', 'When the man I loved decided to leave me forever.'),
	(2416, 'disgust', 'I have felt this feeling when a person whom I believe and respect, á\nlied to me.'),
	(2417, 'shame', 'I feel shame when sometimes, (unconsciously) I behave unethically á\nand without understanding the problems of the man I love.'),
	(2418, 'joy', 'A quarrel was followed by the decision of leaving a person close á\nto me. Several days later my regret was great. I was beside á\nmyself. Quite unexpectedly he came and the conflict was calmly á\nsolved. I was glad at the possibility to be with him.'),
	(2419, 'fear', 'One evening I was watching the news on TV. Again they were á\ntalking about the danger of war. Suddenly I imagined what it á\nmight mean for me, for my friends, for the people close to me. I á\nfelt it a very near and possible event.'),
	(2420, 'anger', 'Unfair and unjust attitude toward a person close to me, what I á\nwas the witness of, caused anger in me.'),
	(2421, 'sadness', 'The thought that I\'ll never sit at the school desk again, caused á\na deep grief at the end of my eleventh form.'),
	(2422, 'disgust', 'I felt disgust with a person whose behaviour was out of the á\nelementary human norms.'),
	(2423, 'shame', 'I had not punched a ticket in the bus because I had a card. But á\nwhen the ticket-collector came it turned out that I had forgotten á\nit. The shame I felt was great though it was not done on purpose.'),
	(2424, 'joy', 'When I understood I was admitted to the Sofia University.'),
	(2425, 'fear', 'I broke my knee when I was skiing over "Yastrebetz" (a racing á\ntrack in a Bulgarian winter resort).'),
	(2426, 'anger', 'The doctors from Belogradchik town determined a wrong diagnosis á\nto my son. A month later, after some complex examinations at ISUL á\n(A medical institute in Sofia), the diagnosis was categorically rejected.'),
	(2427, 'sadness', 'My son lives with my parents in the country and I feel this á\nfeeling always when leaving for Sofia, but the last time it was á\nquite strong.'),
	(2428, 'disgust', 'A colleague of mine asked a lecturer to put him a higher mark in á\norder to keep his good mards and thus to continue getting a á\nscholarship for an excellent grade.'),
	(2429, 'shame', 'I felt this feeling during the exam in higher mathematics.'),
	(2430, 'joy', 'I am a sportwoman as well. I felt joy when after an year of á\npractice, at a contest, I covered the norms for "a master of sports".'),
	(2431, 'fear', 'I felt fear once, when the car in which I travelled directed á\ntowards the precipice along the road.'),
	(2432, 'anger', 'When I see how people around me pass by certain unjustice because á\nof indifference or cowardice.'),
	(2433, 'sadness', 'When I left a man in whom I really believed.'),
	(2434, 'disgust', 'Disgust with drunk people.'),
	(2435, 'shame', 'When I try to lie.'),
	(2436, 'fear', 'When I broke my leg I felt fear.'),
	(2437, 'anger', 'When someone lies to me.'),
	(2438, 'sadness', 'At an unjust insult or injure.'),
	(2439, 'disgust', 'From the cigarette smoke. Usually I feel disgust from it when I á\nam in a restaurant.'),
	(2440, 'shame', 'When I promise to do something but I don\'t fulfill it.'),
	(2441, 'joy', 'When my affairs with the girl I love settled positively.'),
	(2442, 'fear', 'In a dam lake, when the water was let flow to water the plants á\nand I and two other boys were near the water pit. We rescued á\nourselves only thanks to the flippers and the tyre that was with á\nus.'),
	(2443, 'anger', 'It was quite recently, at the football match between the national á\nteams of Bulgaria and France. I felt strong anger with the Scottish á\nreferee who ran the match quite partially.'),
	(2444, 'sadness', 'When I am alone and listen to a song which I like very much and á\nwhich I had listened before together with friends.'),
	(2445, 'disgust', 'A striking act of ingratitude at a public vehicle.'),
	(2446, 'shame', 'I counterfeited a mark in the school register during the lesson á\nin gymnastics. I felt this feeling two days later when I stood á\nface to face with my teacher, whom I highly appreciated and á\nrespected.'),
	(2447, 'joy', 'I passed successfully the preliminary exam for a participation in á\nthe children Assembly.'),
	(2448, 'fear', 'I was alone in my room at the boarding house when at 12 o\'clock á\nsomeone knocked violently on the door.'),
	(2449, 'anger', 'A friend of mine promised to come with me to the cinema but he á\ndidn\'t come.'),
	(2450, 'sadness', 'I felt sadness when I remembered my former boyfriend with whom I á\ngot separated an year ago and when comparing him with my present á\none with whom things are not much of a success.'),
	(2451, 'disgust', 'Recently in the tram, a man ran his fingers over my girlfriend á\nthen over me.'),
	(2452, 'shame', 'I had to prepare a report but I couldn\'t write it. I read from a á\nbook off-hand, I was quite uneasy and I felt I didn\'t manage.'),
	(2453, 'joy', 'Bulgaria won a football match against France.'),
	(2454, 'fear', 'I was going to knock down a pedestrian with my car.'),
	(2455, 'anger', 'I was neglected undeservedly.'),
	(2456, 'sadness', 'My grandmother died.'),
	(2457, 'disgust', 'A man was unfair to a girlfriend of mine.'),
	(2458, 'shame', 'I didn\'t offer my seat to a pregnant woman in the bus.'),
	(2459, 'joy', 'I felt joy when my two twin sisters were born.'),
	(2460, 'fear', 'The night before my wife had given birth to our twins. I felt á\nfear in the hospital yard, I feared if everything was going to be á\nin order.'),
	(2461, 'anger', 'About a month ago the Regional Council refused to pay my wife the á\ndue maternity benefit, because of bureaucratic reasons.'),
	(2462, 'sadness', 'Some months ago my wife gave birth to twin sisters. She had no á\nidea of looking after babies and she felt quite oppressed. The á\nfact that I couldn\'t help her caused grief to me.'),
	(2463, 'disgust', 'I feel disgust with some people when I see what they are capable á\nof, including lack of any dignity, when trying to find a seat in á\nthe tram.'),
	(2464, 'shame', 'Some days ago I had a car accident. It was quite slight but á\nthrough my fault. I felt strong shame because I had the spirits á\nof a good driver.'),
	(2465, 'joy', 'The period when I was pregnant and when I gave birth to my son. á\nI can say those were the happiest months in my life.'),
	(2466, 'fear', 'A fear from the loss of a close friend as a result of his á\nbehavior.'),
	(2467, 'anger', 'When I encountered not only with my father\'s lack of á\nunderstanding but also with his unwillingness to understand me as á\na parent, as far as things for which I (not he) have proves to be á\nright are concerned.'),
	(2468, 'sadness', 'From the fact that my husband and I are not in good terms.'),
	(2469, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted from a quarrel between two married people, in á\nwhich the children were involved as accusers of one of the á\nparents.'),
	(2470, 'shame', 'When I don\'t succeed to fulfill a promise.'),
	(2471, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I saw my daughter after a separation of twenty á\ndays.'),
	(2472, 'fear', 'I felt fear when I sat for one of my exams. Though my fear was á\nnot quite justifiable, I still remember about it.'),
	(2473, 'anger', 'I thought him a good friend but he tried to lie to me several times. á\nLast time was the height of impudence. He promised he would come á\nhome but he didn\'t. I felt a sense of anger and insult.'),
	(2474, 'fear', 'A fear of lack of personal powers.'),
	(2475, 'anger', 'At an undeserved attitude toward a man, when human personality is á\nnot treated decently.'),
	(2476, 'sadness', 'At an irrevocable loss (with respect to human relations).'),
	(2477, 'disgust', 'At an unworthy behaviour of a man, pettiness, stupidity and á\nmostly at a philistinism.'),
	(2478, 'shame', 'At a weakness on my part.'),
	(2479, 'fear', 'Because of a conflict with my parents there was a possibility to á\ninterrupt my studies.'),
	(2480, 'anger', 'I feel a strong anger when I am treated unjustly.'),
	(2481, 'sadness', 'At a prolonged separation with my family.'),
	(2482, 'disgust', 'I was looking for an object when I came across a rotten corpse of á\na rat.'),
	(2483, 'shame', 'I feel this feeling at one and the same degree when I am not á\nprepared to overcome certain obstacle in my life.'),
	(2484, 'joy', 'The day when my son said for the first time "mummy".'),
	(2485, 'fear', 'Before an exam in logics.'),
	(2486, 'anger', 'My husband and I were invited at the house of our nieghbours then á\nwe got an invitation on the part of my parents which we had to á\nrefuse. A a result they called me by words that provoked my á\nanger.'),
	(2487, 'sadness', 'My son lives in the country. I feel sadness when I see mothers á\nhaving walks with their children.'),
	(2488, 'disgust', 'The behaviour of a colleague of mine, which doesn\'t correspond to á\nmy norms of behaviour.'),
	(2489, 'shame', 'I was to take part in a cocktail party on the occasion of our á\nnational holiday as a servant.'),
	(2490, 'joy', 'The sense of joy comes to me always after a period of depression, á\nas an organic feeling for an upsurge. I don\'t exclude the á\nsituative feeling but in this case the reason is not in me, it\'s á\nout of me.'),
	(2491, 'fear', 'I bet that I would jump down from a window. I was sure that I á\nwould jump but before I did it I rather felt fear.'),
	(2492, 'anger', 'A honest "sliding" on the part of a girlfriend of mine. á\nTerribly crossed I started breaking things and tearing books.'),
	(2493, 'sadness', 'Alone I am coming back home in the night after the serial á\n"explanation".'),
	(2494, 'disgust', 'A lie on the part of a person close to me.'),
	(2495, 'shame', 'I thought I had taken a decision but I hesitated.'),
	(2496, 'joy', 'My son was born.'),
	(2497, 'fear', 'I had a car accident.'),
	(2498, 'anger', 'I was drawn up a statement for an infringement of the traffic á\nordinance. In fact I was innocent.'),
	(2499, 'sadness', 'I lost a close friend.'),
	(2500, 'disgust', 'I saw a film about the nazi concentration camps during the war. á\nAfter the film I felt disgust.'),
	(2501, 'shame', 'I was nailed. I lied in connection with a book which I took from á\nthe library, because I had to keep it for a longer time.'),
	(2502, 'joy', 'After 10 days of hard work and having suffered many changes I á\npassed my last exam.'),
	(2503, 'fear', 'Before going to the dentist.'),
	(2504, 'anger', 'When I am made to do things in which I see no sense and I waste á\nmy time. Some time ago I had to participate in a sociological á\ninvestigation and then I got really angry.'),
	(2505, 'sadness', 'When I feel I must be with somebody, to talk with somebody - but á\nI am alone.'),
	(2506, 'disgust', 'Some time ago a man tried to teach me something. "Tried" because á\nit is very difficult to teach somebody when you yourself are not á\ncompetent and cultured.'),
	(2507, 'shame', 'I am ashamed when I am not ready for my seminar in internal á\ndiseases, simply because the assistant professor is a person who á\ndeserves high respect.'),
	(2508, 'joy', 'When I am with friends and I do what pleases me this often á\nhappenes.'),
	(2509, 'fear', 'When I have to go in for an exam and the examinor is a person á\nwith a whimsical character and unsteady requirements.'),
	(2510, 'anger', 'I unfairly got a low mark on an exam and I failed to win a grant, á\nsince then I don\'t have much confidence in myself at an exam.'),
	(2511, 'sadness', 'It happened that I was alone - with no contacts with friends.'),
	(2512, 'disgust', 'I met three drunk boys, almost children, they didn\'t look like á\nnormal people.'),
	(2513, 'shame', 'I was totally unprepared for a seminar conducted by an assistant á\nprofessor whom I highly respect.'),
	(2514, 'joy', 'I was happy when I understood that the girl I liked was in love á\nwith me.'),
	(2515, 'fear', 'I am afraid before an exam or colloquium.'),
	(2516, 'anger', 'I get angry when my smaller brother misbehaves and talks with indecent á\nwords.'),
	(2517, 'sadness', 'When my dog was stolen.'),
	(2518, 'disgust', 'I detest any kind of constraint and hate the attempts of elder á\npeople to force me to a norm of behavior without having legal or á\nmoral rights to do it. I felt this emotion when a neighbour of á\nmine made me kick out my guests because they had talked very á\nloudly and threatened that with "connections" she will expel me á\nfrom the inst.'),
	(2519, 'shame', 'I experienced long ago when I was sightseeing Bulgarians in a á\nforeign language.'),
	(2520, 'joy', 'When I met with friends that I hadn\'t seen for a long time.'),
	(2521, 'fear', 'One evening a friend of mine was telling a fearful story, nobody á\ntook it seriously but I got frightened.'),
	(2522, 'anger', 'I got angry with a stranger in a train who behaved impertinently á\nand immorally'),
	(2523, 'sadness', 'When I failed at the first entrance exam.'),
	(2524, 'disgust', 'The event which got me angry got also an aversion in me.'),
	(2525, 'shame', 'Once I was not ready for a seminar and I was asked to leave.'),
	(2526, 'joy', 'Six months ago when I got acquaintanced with a person whom I á\ntrusted infinitely and from whom I expected help and friendly á\nfeelings. With him I found much in common - in our views and in á\nour fate.'),
	(2527, 'fear', 'Few days ago I really experienced fear. It was connected with á\nunexpected actions on the part of a group of people. This evoked á\nin me many negative emotions.'),
	(2528, 'anger', 'I always get angry when somebody deceives me, or tries to conceal á\nhis lie skilfully and this offends me even more.'),
	(2529, 'sadness', 'Sadness - this is an emotion which I have felt very often á\nrecently. I can\'t remember a concrete example. I will describe my á\ngeneral impression from severl situations which evoked this á\nfeeling in me.'),
	(2530, 'disgust', 'I became disgusted with the man on whom I had counted, who I had á\ntrusted, the man who should have been my mainstay - my father. á\nI could hardly make myself (and the others) believe in this á\nemotion. It has cumulated after events and deeds. Everything can á\nhappen in this world.'),
	(2531, 'shame', 'I am ashamed of the way my father behaves with my mother and á\nsister, and with me too.'),
	(2532, 'joy', 'When I was accepted as a student.'),
	(2533, 'fear', 'I was a bit frightened when it was found that there was something á\nwrong with my liver. However it turned out that it was not á\nserious and I need not worry.'),
	(2534, 'anger', 'With the girl whom I may be loved truly. When she refused to come á\nwith me to an occasion (she was from another town).'),
	(2535, 'sadness', 'For the girl who halped me go on living and made me happy - when á\nI don\'t see her even for two or three days.'),
	(2536, 'disgust', 'For a drunk man (about 20 years old) that I met one evening, and á\nwho behaved impudently with the girls standing by.'),
	(2537, 'shame', 'I was embarassed at the exam in microbiology. I was ashamed with á\nmyself - how little I knew and how good was the examinor. I á\nrarely become ashamed.'),
	(2538, 'joy', 'I felt it when on duty in the hospital I understood that I was á\nnot afraid to face death, that I also helped a little to relieve á\nthe pains of a patient.'),
	(2539, 'fear', 'Fear overwhelmed me when right against the car I was in I saw á\nanother one, as if out of control of the driver.'),
	(2540, 'anger', 'I felt it when a girl who was dear to me lied to my face. I got á\nangry with the fact that she knew I didn\'t believe her but she á\nkept on telling lies.'),
	(2541, 'sadness', 'Sadness, no, I felt something much stronger when my father died.'),
	(2542, 'disgust', 'I got disgusted with a man who was beating a woman in the street. á\nI just happened to be there but I was abhorred by the rudness.'),
	(2543, 'shame', 'I was ashamed of the way I deceived that I could not help a á\nfriend, although it was absolutely possible for me. Nothing was á\nrevealed but I haven\'t called up this person since then.'),
	(2544, 'joy', 'When I knew that my husband and I were going to have a child.'),
	(2545, 'fear', 'Two years ago I saw a film on the TV. Even now it makes me á\nafraid.'),
	(2546, 'anger', 'When my husband stays late at a meeting and I have to be alone.'),
	(2547, 'sadness', 'The loss of a person I loved very much.'),
	(2548, 'disgust', 'Deception from a person I loved very much.'),
	(2549, 'shame', 'I didn\'t tell my parents that I was going to Sofia. I told them á\nthat I was going to a seminar. My mother knew that I was lying but á\nshe didn\'t stop me.'),
	(2550, 'joy', 'I was very happy when I got the message that I had been accepted á\nas a student in medicine.'),
	(2551, 'fear', 'I felt something close to that when I saw that there was a man on á\nthe terrace of the flat.'),
	(2552, 'anger', 'I got angry when I learned how short a time we had to prepare for á\nthe term examinations.'),
	(2553, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when my first boyfriend and I left each other. It was neither á\nhis fault nor mine.'),
	(2554, 'disgust', 'I felt it today when the bus driver shouted rather indecent words á\nat a man without any reason whatsoever.'),
	(2555, 'shame', 'At an exam in pharmacology I tried to prompt a coleague (she á\nasked me something) and the assistant professor made me a sharp á\nremark.'),
	(2556, 'joy', 'When I learned that my parents were going abroad and leaving me á\nalone for a few years.'),
	(2557, 'fear', 'I was at the seaside and my brother disappeared for a couple of á\nhours.'),
	(2558, 'disgust', 'Some time ago I was disgusted with the "cleanness" of the á\nrefectory of our institute.'),
	(2559, 'shame', 'We were at a football match and when we were leaving the stadium á\n(the stadium was packed with people) and I lost my shoe in the á\ncrowd. Our attempts to find it didn\'t give any result and I had á\nto go home without one shoe. In other words to cross the whole á\ntown !'),
	(2560, 'joy', 'When I was admitted to the Institute. I had problems with many á\npeople about my applying for this institute and I decided to á\nprove that one can pass excellently without visiting any á\npreparatory couse. That is - I proved what I could do on my own.'),
	(2561, 'fear', 'Once as a child I dreamed of a fire. Since that time I hadn\'t á\nwanted to sleep in that bed and had feared the night darkness á\n(and so it is now).'),
	(2562, 'anger', 'A chief was unjustly punished on an autumn brigade and the one á\nwho was really guilty kept silent. I stepped in front and told á\nthe truth. The guilty chief called me in after the roll-call and á\nthreatened me.'),
	(2563, 'sadness', 'Years ago I fell in love for the first time. as natural for every á\nschool-girl I was day-dreaming. Later (after 3 years) we left á\neach other. No one was to blame but I felt deep sadness. Even now á\nI remember about it quite often.'),
	(2564, 'disgust', 'It was at a comsomol(??) meeting, the last one because we were to á\ngraduate. The way one of my fellow-students behaved made me feel á\ndisgusted.'),
	(2565, 'shame', 'I was at a children\'s camp abroad. The people (the leaders, my á\ncoevals) were very king to us. One night we smeared our foreign á\nfriends with tooth-paste while they were sleeping and then we á\nroused the whole camp by our shouts. Later I was so sorry. I á\ndidn\'t utter a word for two days, then I went to apologize.'),
	(2566, 'joy', 'When I learned I was admitted to study what I wanted most - á\nfloriculture (this is a narrow specialization from the general á\none).'),
	(2567, 'fear', 'I was walking on the pavement when a white car rolled on it and á\ndirected towards me. I was quite near the house wall when it á\nrolled by and hit me.'),
	(2568, 'anger', 'My grandmother\'s brother had taken active part in the resistance á\nmovement. He had been in prison many times and there he lost his á\nhealth. He became an invalid. When we phoned to First Aid the á\nnurse on duty behaved quite unkindly when she understood how old á\nhe was (79).'),
	(2569, 'sadness', 'My boyfriend is a soldier. He was on a leave. I felt sad when we á\nhad to get separated again.'),
	(2570, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted about a teacher who had rejected all that was á\nhuman in her. She refused to accept the flowers we gave her for á\nthe eighth of March and asked for a foreign parfume instead.'),
	(2571, 'shame', 'I was examined by a teacher I greatly respected. I was well á\nprepared on the subjects but he put some side-issues to me and I á\ncouldn\'t answer.'),
	(2572, 'joy', 'I was very glad when I learned I was a student already. I heard á\nabout it over the phone, I didn\'t believe it at first.'),
	(2573, 'fear', 'I had worries about a certain illness.'),
	(2574, 'anger', 'I suffered from a gynaecological illness. I was quite displeased á\nto hear that my roommates had talked about it and they had á\nmisrepresented the truth. I felt deeply hurt when I learned that á\nit was done by a "good" acquaintance of mine.'),
	(2575, 'sadness', 'When my first boyfriend left me. I tried not to let him á\nunderstand I felt miserable.'),
	(2576, 'disgust', 'I hate hypocrisy. My friend (girl) tried to intrude into my á\naffairs with my future husband. After that she behaved as if á\nnothing had happened.'),
	(2577, 'shame', 'I feel shame when I have made a promise, I can\'t keep it and this á\nhas negative effects which are caused by my behavior.'),
	(2578, 'joy', 'I felt glad when I took the rather difficult organic chemistry á\nexamination.'),
	(2579, 'fear', 'This was what I felt when my boyfriend went to Bourgas to study á\nthere. I had the feeling I would lose him. Anyway the distance á\nPlovdiv-Bourgas seemed to me so great.'),
	(2580, 'anger', 'I confronted with this feeling at the Institute quite recently, á\nthe pedology lecturer was the cause.'),
	(2581, 'sadness', 'This feeling was quite deep when my friend (girl) died in a car á\naccident.'),
	(2582, 'disgust', 'I am disgusted with the behavior of a car driver whose car would á\nrun over me and my friends during our autumn brigade.'),
	(2583, 'shame', 'I felt shame when I discontinued my education for eight months.'),
	(2584, 'joy', 'I sensed a strong feeling of joy when in the plant, at my working á\nplace, I got a message that I was admitted as full time student at á\nthe Higher Agricultural Institute.'),
	(2585, 'fear', 'Fear when fulfilling my obligations on my first night fatigue á\nduty as a soldier.'),
	(2586, 'anger', 'When on a car journey a fellow student crossed our way with his á\nown car and we had to bump into a roadside trunk.'),
	(2587, 'sadness', 'The loss of a close relative who was ill with cancer.'),
	(2588, 'disgust', 'I am disgusted with a nieghbour who is looking for all sorts of á\nquarrel with my parents and me. He feels we are hampering his á\nliving close to us. This has been going on for quite a long time.'),
	(2589, 'shame', 'Some time ago I promised to meet an acquaintance of mine and to á\ncarry him some promised papers. I haven\'t done it until this day. á\nNow I feel quite awkward when I meet him.'),
	(2590, 'joy', 'After a difficult exam. When I had not hoped to take it and had á\ngot a high mark. When you present someone with something and he á\nfeels glad.'),
	(2591, 'fear', 'Fear from the unknown. I felt fear when I sat for the entrance á\nexaminations.'),
	(2592, 'anger', 'I feel angry at people\'s indifference at our ability to be á\npresent at an event and to stay partial to what happens.'),
	(2593, 'sadness', 'When you are far away from relatives and friends. I feel sad for á\nmy early years, for the freedom and the carefree years of á\nchildhood.'),
	(2594, 'disgust', 'I feel disgusted with the bootlickers, with helpless people.'),
	(2595, 'shame', 'I feel ashamed when I act dishonestly toward somebody.'),
	(2596, 'joy', 'I was sitting for an exam in biochemistry, I was very excited á\nbecause it was a supplementary examination. I passed the exam á\nvery well and was glad because I recovered my selfconfidence.'),
	(2597, 'fear', 'Students fear many things but we seem to fear the examinations á\nmost of all. I remember I was horror stricken before my á\nmicrobiology exam, because it was a decisive one.'),
	(2598, 'anger', 'It was necessary to organise a competition in connection with a á\ncelebration. Everyone was to be present at that event. It turned á\nout that there was no audience at all because everyone had á\npretended to be very intelligent and no one had come. I got á\nfurious.'),
	(2599, 'sadness', 'When I part with my friends I feel always sad for some time. I á\ncan\'t remember a concrete example now. For example I have just á\nparted with a friend of mine and I am feeling sad.'),
	(2600, 'disgust', 'In autumn I had to move to another lodging. My landlords, quite á\nintelligent people, warned me I had to move in the nearest á\nfuture. But I had difficulties in moving my luggage because I á\ncouldn\'t wait for a car to come. How amazed I was to hear them á\nthreatening me they would throw our my things. And at that my á\nluggage was well packed and did not stand in their way. I was á\nquite  disappointed and disgusted.'),
	(2601, 'shame', 'During our last exarcise in agricultural machines we went out in á\nthe yard to examine a row of machines. But we seemed not to have á\nfulfilled our task well, because when our teacher came and asked á\nme a question I was unable to answer. I felt awkward because he á\ndidn\'t deserve it.'),
	(2602, 'joy', 'When I succeded in establishing a contact with a girl (who is now á\nmy girlfriend).'),
	(2603, 'fear', 'I fear before each exam.'),
	(2604, 'anger', 'When my bosom friend tried to lie to me.'),
	(2605, 'sadness', 'When I quarrelled with a very close friend of mine.'),
	(2606, 'disgust', 'When I see the acts and deeds of a blind drunk man.'),
	(2607, 'shame', 'When I wasn\'t well prepared for a terminal exam and the teacher á\ntried to give me a three by asking me some very easy questions. I á\nburned with shame then.'),
	(2608, 'joy', 'I feel joy usually after each taken exam, the last one was in á\nFebruary.'),
	(2609, 'fear', 'It was not long ago when I and two of friends of mine got quite drunk á\nand one of them began to rave under the influence of the alcohol. á\nI felt fear of what could have happened.'),
	(2610, 'anger', 'I felt anger at my last exam, I felt angry with our teacher, á\nbecause he did not rate me objectively and I failed.'),
	(2611, 'sadness', 'I met a girl some time ago and I cared very much about her but it á\nhappened so that we left each other. I felt some sort of sadness, I think á\nI can call it so.'),
	(2612, 'disgust', 'I had a very good friend (boy) and I thought I could rely on him á\nbut he behaved badly with a girl who used to trust us completely.'),
	(2613, 'shame', 'Immediately after the New Year holidays I happened to visit a á\nparty where there was a lot of alcohol and I became drunk. On the á\nnext day I felt sort of ashamed when I remembered what I had said á\nand done on the night before.'),
	(2614, 'joy', 'When I was admitted to the Higher Institute.'),
	(2615, 'fear', 'I felt fear when I fell down and broke my leg into pieces and I á\ncould not feel it at all.'),
	(2616, 'anger', 'I felt angry when I failed in an exam about which I knew quite a á\nfew things and I did not deserve to be plucked.'),
	(2617, 'sadness', 'When my mother and father were on an excursion in Chechoslovakia á\nand I was at a student camp and I heard over the radio about the á\nevents that were taking place there.'),
	(2618, 'disgust', 'I felt disgust with alcohol in general when a close friend of á\nmine got so drunk that he didn\'t realize what he was doing and it á\nwas quite shameful.'),
	(2619, 'shame', 'I felt ashamed when my parents found out that I had deceived á\nthem.'),
	(2620, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I was admitted to the Higher Agricultural á\nInstitute.'),
	(2621, 'fear', 'I feel fear quite often but this feeling was very strong last á\nyear when my husband was quite unexpectedly sent to the hospital.'),
	(2622, 'anger', 'That was what I felt with a teacher who put down quite unreal á\nmarks.'),
	(2623, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when a friend of mine died and I felt that something á\nhad irrevocably gone away from me.'),
	(2624, 'disgust', 'I felt disgust with a lady teacher who used to nag, to mock, to á\ninterrupt everyone of my fellow students each time we had a class á\nwith her in our first year.'),
	(2625, 'shame', 'That was what I felt when I told my first lie and then was á\ncought.'),
	(2626, 'joy', 'I was for the first time on a brigade this year. At that time my á\nsister was to bear a child. I was mad with joy when I opened the á\ntelegram from my parents and learned I had a nephew.'),
	(2627, 'fear', 'It was some years ago when one evening some people came home and á\ntold us my father was badly injured in an accident.'),
	(2628, 'anger', 'I faced this feeling when I realized I wasn\'t admitted to the á\ninstitute in the first classifying, in spite of the high mark I á\nhad got at the entrance examination.á'),
	(2629, 'sadness', 'Always when I get separated from my friends and relatives from my á\nhome town.'),
	(2630, 'disgust', 'I feel disgust with my first boyfriend who made fun of our love á\nin an abominable way.'),
	(2631, 'shame', 'I have always felt ashamed for some people\'s behavior to their á\ntoo old parents. I have felt hurt and shy when they have left á\nthem to the mercy of fate.'),
	(2632, 'joy', 'Naturally when I got myself discharged this was my second á\nbirthday.'),
	(2633, 'fear', 'When I failed my first exam at the Higher Institute.'),
	(2634, 'anger', 'A nuisance used to live in our flat a month ago. I experienced á\nthis feeling when I tried to chase her out.'),
	(2635, 'sadness', 'After my father\'s death.'),
	(2636, 'disgust', 'With an alcoholic.'),
	(2637, 'shame', 'Once I had dinner at an elegant restaurant and I did not have á\nenough money to pay the bill. There were a lot of people there á\nand I felt quite awkward.'),
	(2638, 'joy', 'I felt the greatest burst of joy when after being heavily ill for á\na long period, my father came back home.'),
	(2639, 'fear', 'I was terrified during an axcursion in Italy. I was lost and left á\nalone in this unfamiliar country.'),
	(2640, 'anger', 'I took part in a football match. The referee was extremely á\npartial to the opposite team. This stirred up my discontent and á\nanger.'),
	(2641, 'sadness', 'When my first girlfriend an I left each other.'),
	(2642, 'disgust', 'During a summer holiday at a bar I happened to see a dead to the á\nworld woman.'),
	(2643, 'shame', 'When I first had a sexual intercourse.'),
	(2644, 'joy', 'When I got a message that I was employed as a nurse at a á\nkindergarten.'),
	(2645, 'fear', 'When I first sat for an entrance examination.'),
	(2646, 'anger', 'When a teacher though pretending to be a highly cultivated á\nteacher and a man, slapped a classmate of mine in the face quite á\nundeservedly.'),
	(2647, 'sadness', 'When I got separated from my first love.'),
	(2648, 'disgust', 'Many times, when my father used to come home drunk and maltreated á\nphysically me and my mother.'),
	(2649, 'shame', 'When for the first and the last time I tried to crib and the á\nteacher was with her back to me but right when I was taking the á\nmaterials out she turned round and saw me.'),
	(2650, 'joy', 'Being invited out by a person I wished to get closer to. He á\ntelephoned and invited me to go out with him the next night.'),
	(2651, 'fear', 'Watching a horror movie with friends.'),
	(2652, 'anger', 'The breakup of a relationship. After the event I was upset/sad á\nthen angry maybe 2/3 weeks later.'),
	(2653, 'sadness', 'The funeral of a friend who was killed in a car accident. She was á\nof my own age, there were many of my own friends present, as well á\nas her family etc.'),
	(2654, 'disgust', 'Disgust for a person who treated me badly, and has treated other á\npeople similarly - including lying, hiding facts, being á\ndeceitful, unfair, etc.'),
	(2655, 'shame', 'Losing my temper and allowing myself to act childishly by yelling á\nand screaming at a person who I felt had done me wrong - in á\neffect lowering myself to their level.'),
	(2656, 'joy', 'Achievement of a task by a friend who had begun a new job. She á\nwasn\'t confident of handling the situation so was thinking  of á\nleaving the job only after 2 days employment.'),
	(2657, 'fear', 'Walking home at night after university - part of the way, there á\nare ano lights and I am walking down a thoroughfare with the á\nthouth of no one hearing me if I have to scream.'),
	(2658, 'anger', 'When my son omits to carry out certain duties at home that he á\nknows needs doing.'),
	(2659, 'sadness', 'When I saw my niece (5 yrs) crying in the hallway for her mother á\nwho had passed away about a month ago.'),
	(2660, 'disgust', 'With a woman who had walked into my place of employment and á\nurinated on the floor in front of everyone.'),
	(2661, 'shame', 'When I found a letter addressed "To Mum" by my son, 6 months á\nlater, he begged me not to sell his new shoes which he messed up á\nafter wearing them for the first time.'),
	(2662, 'joy', 'Felt joy a few years ago when I was away on holiday. And sat very á\nclose to my best friend looking straight into the eyes.'),
	(2663, 'fear', 'I had to tell someone that I was interested in remaining celibate á\nand alone. And that my spiritual master strictly prohibited á\nsexual relations outside of marriage. This caused great fear á\nthrough lack of conviction afraid to hurt someone\'s feelings á\ndespite my own being hurt in the process.'),
	(2664, 'anger', 'In a sociology class I felt very angry towards some members of á\nsociety for exploiting the Polynesian people, dawn raids by á\nPolice (Martin Luther King, Blacks in S.A.). But this was just a á\nreflection of my own shortcomings.'),
	(2665, 'sadness', 'Felt sad about some street kids in QUEII square, Aotea square. á\nBecause they had been sniffing glue and some were very young. I á\nwent into the role of a performing clown.'),
	(2666, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted by my paranoid attitude towards myself, my á\nhomework at university and disgusted about my lack of retention. á\nEspecially in learning another language.'),
	(2667, 'shame', 'I felt shame at the hurt I caused to my family especially my á\nparent father, shame of hurting people emotionally. A misconceived á\nself-blaming that didn\'t do me any good. Shame at being myself as á\nI am.'),
	(2668, 'joy', 'When I meet old past pupils of mine - and find they are all doing á\nwell - I feel joy. Yesterday I met a young woman (20 yrs) I\'d á\ntaught her at 6 yrs, then at 12 yrs and hadn\'t seen her for last á\n3-4 yrs; she was no longer a waitress but a meter maid for á\nCouncil.'),
	(2669, 'fear', 'A Maori language oral test, yeaterday - Although I had studied á\nintensely - once in the examiners room "I blew it" -  I was so á\nnervous I couldn\'t reply easily - It was very important, but I á\ngot only blankness.'),
	(2670, 'anger', 'A friend visited and made comments that my house/garden were not á\nas neat/tidy as in the past. I\'d not seen her a year - She á\nimplied I\'d gone to the pack (I\'d only been working full time, á\nand taking 3 University exams part time).'),
	(2671, 'sadness', 'When my father a 4th/5th generation colonial (from Eng.) attacked á\nme verbally about my chosen partner. A man whom he discarded á\nbecause his colour skin was not white. His ultimate disgust á\nsaddned me.'),
	(2672, 'disgust', 'People who came to our home - and requested "Put out your smoke". á\nThat we should not smoke in our house... and asked not even á\npolitely. It disgusted me because I think people need to adapt to á\nthe situation.'),
