	(3552, 'fear', 'We were in the country and I walked away from the others one á\nnight.  Suddenly something moved sharply in front of me and I was á\nnot able to see what it was.'),
	(3553, 'anger', 'When I was young, I became very angry as I was not allowed to á\nstay up all night for the fair in my town.'),
