	(3557, 'joy', 'When I learned, after the ecography, that my mother was expecting a á\nbaby girl.  That was what I wanted.'),
	(3558, 'fear', 'One night, walking along a park, I began to think that some á\nroughnecks would appear suddenly with knives and things like á\nthat.'),
	(3559, 'anger', 'I had an exam and I had it well prepared.  I did the first part á\nvery well but did not know the second part.'),
