	(3603, 'disgust', 'The man who threw me out of the flat disgusted me.'),
	(3604, 'shame', 'The first time that I caressed a girl, I was about thirteen and á\nshe was eighteen.  I noticed that it did not affect her at all.'),
	(3605, 'joy', 'I met a girlfriend again after not seeing her for several months. á\n I saw her in a discotheque.  We do not like discotheques but we á\nwent there because we knew we would meet there.'),
	(3606, 'fear', 'I was walking in the countryside alone when I came across two á\ndogs who began barking at me.  I did not know whether they were á\ntied up or loose, but I was afraid of them approaching me.'),
	(3607, 'anger', 'I was angry when my sister began to talk nonsense and to laugh at á\nthe way I swept the room.  My anger grew (I tried to control á\nmyself).  After telling her to leave me alone, I vented my anger á\non her as she did not obey me.'),
