	(3824, 'fear', 'We were riding in a friend\'s car.  He was driving very fast and á\nsuddenly a another car crossed the road in front of us.  My á\nfriend had to turn the car rapidly.'),
	(3825, 'anger', 'When I found one of my new pullovers wrinkled inside the á\nwardrobe.  My brother had done it.'),
	(3826, 'sadness', 'When I went to see the result of an exam and saw that I had á\nfailed.'),
	(3827, 'disgust', 'When I was getting up, I found a live cockroach in my bedroom.'),
	(3828, 'shame', 'The mother of a friend of mine passed by me and saw me sitting á\non a boy\'s lap.  I tried to greet her but could not help á\nblushing.'),
	(3829, 'joy', 'The final marks were to be given in the morning.  I wanted to get á\nthere late because I was very afraid.  When I arrived there, á\neverybody was very happy and I had also passed.  We had a á\nwonderful time all day long.'),
	(3830, 'fear', 'I went to visit a friend in hospital.  He was going to be á\noperated the next day.  I was afraid that they would not let me á\nin and I did not know what his reaction would be on seeing me.'),
	(3831, 'anger', 'A friend of mine played a joke on another friend over the á\ntelephone.  This friend, crying, called me and I got very angry á\nand made the other person apologize.'),
	(3832, 'sadness', 'A friend of mine told me that my boyfriend had been with another á\ngirl this Summer.  We had been going out together for four years á\nand we had not done so for the last three months.  I could not á\nbelieve it.'),
	(3833, 'disgust', 'I was at a friend\'s place for lunch and she fell ill and á\nvomited.'),
	(3834, 'shame', 'I was dancing in a theatre.  I was not sure whether some frieends á\nof mine had come to see me.  I was very scared of doing things á\nwrong.'),
	(3835, 'joy', 'On holiday, seeing the lanscape in Gerona.'),
	(3836, 'fear', 'Travelling by coach on a rather narrow and wet road.'),
	(3837, 'anger', 'They wanted me to pay for a ticket twice because they said that á\nthe one I had was out of date.'),
	(3838, 'sadness', 'When I came back from my holidays.'),
	(3839, 'disgust', 'When I saw an insect going up my arm.'),
	(3840, 'shame', 'When I entered a bar looking for a friend.'),
	(3841, 'joy', 'When some friends of mine asked me to go camping with them for a á\nfortnight.'),
	(3842, 'fear', 'Once, when I was very young, my mother left me alone in the á\nhouse and came back very late.'),
	(3843, 'anger', 'When my aunt told me angrily that I was a good-for-nothing and á\nshe was fed up with my behaviour.'),
	(3844, 'sadness', 'When my parents and sister went on a trip and I was separated á\nfrom them for about three months.'),
	(3845, 'disgust', 'When a person I did not know hurt a friend of mine.'),
	(3846, 'shame', 'When the literature teacher made me recite a poem in the middle á\nof the class and I had to gesticulate.'),
	(3847, 'joy', 'I phoned a friend of mine to ask her for news about the marks in á\nan exam.  She told me that I had passed.'),
	(3848, 'fear', 'I was spending my summer holidays in a village.  My friend and I á\nwere coming back from a discotheque at night and we heard a noise á\nfrom an alley.  We were very scared and we got into my friend\'s house. á\n A moment later, an unknown car picked up a person from this á\nalley.'),
	(3849, 'anger', 'My mother and I had an argument over buying some clothes for me.  á\nShe did not accept the fact that I did not like the same things á\nas her, and we ended up shouting at each other.'),
	(3850, 'sadness', 'One day, I was home and there was a phone call informing me that á\nsome of my relatives had died in an accident.'),
	(3851, 'disgust', 'When I saw a film in which there was a scene where women were cut á\nto pieces.  Above all, it was the blood and the confusion which á\nimpressed me most.'),
	(3852, 'shame', 'I was walking to school and I passed by a red cross post where á\nthere were many soldiers.  They began to pass remarks at me.'),
	(3853, 'joy', 'I was told that I had passed the statistics exam.  I had not á\nexpected this so I was very happy.'),
	(3854, 'fear', 'When my brother hit his head and lost consciousness at the sports á\npractice.  For some time he could not remember what had happened á\nbut he recovered later.'),
	(3855, 'anger', 'I get angry with my brothers and sisters when they do something á\nthat I do not like.  They know this and still do it so as to á\ntease me.'),
	(3856, 'disgust', 'When opened a box of biscuits and found worms inside.'),
	(3857, 'shame', 'When I was young I was told to to the shop to buy a dozen eggs.  á\nI went and asked for one egg and the people in the shop laughed á\nat me and so did my family when I told them what had happened.'),
	(3858, 'joy', 'When I spoke to my daughter and wished her luck for the á\nexaminations she was about to take.'),
	(3859, 'fear', 'When I was told that my daughter, who is at a boarding school, á\nwas very ill and that they needed me there the same day.'),
	(3860, 'anger', 'One day in a clinic, the father of a child came in and assaulted á\na colleague for something that she had not done deliberately.'),
	(3861, 'sadness', 'When I was told that my uncle had passed away.'),
	(3862, 'disgust', 'The transport to pick us up for lunch was always late and the á\ndriver made the same excuse every day.'),
	(3863, 'shame', 'One day when I came back home, I found my favourite dish broken.  á\nI blamed the servant for it, later I found out that it was not á\nthe servant but my daughter who had broken it.'),
	(3864, 'joy', 'When a cousin of mine was discharged from the hospital after       á\na long illness.  I had thought that this illness would never end.'),
	(3865, 'fear', 'When a man who had a knife grabbed me and threatened me with it,   á\nduring my holidays in Monze.á'),
	(3866, 'anger', 'A certain friend tried to push me off a seat in a very violent á\nway for no apparent reason.  It may be that he was excited about á\nsomething.'),
	(3867, 'sadness', 'When the neighbour of a friend of mine was stabbed to death by á\nthieves in Kabwe.  They stole his van.'),
	(3868, 'disgust', 'When we were young, a friend of mine tried to dissect a frog while  á\nwe were playing near his home.'),
	(3869, 'shame', 'The time I shouted at most of my friends at a party.  It was as if á\n all my friends had done something wrong, or may be it was the á\ninfluence of the beer.'),
	(3870, 'joy', 'After going through much shame, I became a Christian and á\nsomething new happened in my heart.  Joy that overflows was á\nmanifest in me.'),
	(3871, 'fear', 'When I was about six years old, I mistook a cat for a leopard      á\nwhen it entered my room at night.'),
	(3872, 'anger', 'When a person the same age as me insisted that I call him á\n"Mister".  I refused to succumb, but he persisted and I got angry á\nas he had belittled me.'),
	(3873, 'sadness', 'When I lost my father on the 25th of September,1970.  He died of á\na sore on the leg.'),
	(3874, 'disgust', 'When I failed the grade 7 twice and only passed it the third á\ntime.'),
	(3875, 'shame', 'I was going around with a foreigner\'s wife and my entire family á\ngot to know about it, this was just when I had become a á\nChristian.'),
	(3876, 'joy', 'When I first passed a job interview.'),
	(3877, 'fear', 'I was almost caught in the girls hostel by the security men, I á\nwould have been expelled from school had I been caught.'),
	(3878, 'anger', 'When I was accused of having refused to do some hostel work while á\nI was at school.  Actually I had not been allocated any work.'),
	(3879, 'sadness', 'A friend of mine could not make it back to Unza after having á\nfailed the exams.'),
	(3880, 'disgust', 'I usually come back home early but this day I came home back late á\nto find some visitors at my place.'),
	(3881, 'shame', 'I got pass marks in the H.S.S compulsory courses while most á\npeople performed well.'),
	(3882, 'joy', 'When I heard that I had made it to the second year at UNZA.'),
	(3883, 'fear', 'When my father\'s home was to be broken into by thieves who had á\nguns.'),
	(3884, 'anger', 'When a friend tried to back bite me on false grounds.  This made á\nme wonder if he was a really a good friend.'),
	(3885, 'sadness', 'When my girlfriend\'s nephew passed away.'),
	(3886, 'disgust', 'When someone whom I trusted, disappointed me terribly.'),
	(3887, 'shame', 'I was with my colleagues and we met an elderly man who was very á\ndrunk, as he approached us he started to undress.'),
	(3888, 'joy', 'When I hooked a girl in Kitwe.  She was very beautiful for my á\nstandards, a rare bird of this kind accepted me as a boyfriend.'),
	(3889, 'fear', 'When someone tried to bewitch me and my friends at night.'),
	(3890, 'anger', 'When I was victimized for running away with a girl who was á\nsomebody else\'s wife and niece at the same time.  I was very á\nangry over this issue because I was told to pay him money after á\nhaving been punished for it.'),
	(3891, 'sadness', '1976, Soweto uprising in South Africa and the racist Gout\'s á\nreaction to the students demands concerning the educational á\nsystem.'),
	(3892, 'disgust', 'When I got  grade "C" in M160 at the end of my first year at á\nUNZA.  I had expected a "C+" or a "B" as M160 is easy, going by my á\ncapacity in mathematics.'),
	(3893, 'shame', 'When I was found urinating, behind a toilet instead of inside it, á\nby my class mates and the teachers.  I was told to pick up my own á\nurine from the wet soil, I did it.'),
	(3894, 'joy', 'When I was accepted for further education, here at the á\nuniversity.'),
	(3895, 'fear', 'When I was walking at night, I saw fire suspended in the air and á\nit was split into several segments by something I could not see.  á\nI suspected that it was witch-craft.'),
	(3896, 'anger', 'When I was accused by my brother of having stolen a 5 kwatcha á\nnote from my mother\'s bag.  I was beaten up for this, the money á\nwas found later.'),
	(3897, 'sadness', 'When I received a message that my brother was seriously ill and á\nwas in hospital.'),
	(3898, 'disgust', 'When I was refused a transfer from my school to another, simply á\nbecause it was far away from my house.'),
	(3899, 'shame', 'When I was taking an exam in grade 5.  The examinator found me á\nwith a note-book and accused me of copying, All the students á\nlaughed at me.'),
	(3900, 'joy', 'When I got first division in the exams before leaving school.'),
	(3901, 'fear', 'When I went to town in a double dekker bus.  The bus was about to á\nfall on the way when the driver controlled it.  It had almost á\nfallen.'),
	(3902, 'anger', 'When I was in form 3, my aunts lied to my daddy telling him that á\nI had told them that I was pregnant.  My daddy  told my mother á\nand she asked me if it was true.  I was very angry with my aunts.'),
	(3903, 'sadness', 'When I received a letter telling me that my mother was very ill.'),
	(3904, 'disgust', 'When a drunkard, in town yelled at me saying that I was a á\nprostitute.'),
	(3905, 'shame', 'My brother came to see me and found me with a boy friend.  When á\nmy boyfriend greeted him, he did not answer and instead started á\nshouting at me and scolding me in the prescence of my boyfriend.'),
	(3906, 'joy', 'When I had my four children.'),
	(3907, 'fear', 'When two of my children were critically ill with measles.'),
	(3908, 'anger', 'When I got a low grade in an administration course.'),
	(3909, 'sadness', 'When I got divorced from my husband after ten years of marriage.'),
	(3910, 'disgust', 'When my mother betrayed me by obtaining money from my husband á\nwhen we were separated - pending divorce.'),
	(3911, 'shame', 'When I gave my boyfriend a brush-off.'),
	(3912, 'joy', 'This happened when I went to check my first year results, I had  á\nthought that I would fail and I found that I had a clear pass in á\nall my courses.'),
	(3913, 'fear', 'When I woke up at night to find a fire spreading towards the bed á\n-rooms.  I was very frightened as I realized that I faced death.'),
	(3914, 'anger', 'When a friend of mine was trying to make a fool out of me.'),
	(3915, 'sadness', 'I experienced this emotion when my friend committed suicide after á\nwe had spent the afternoon playing and discussing life and it\'s á\nproblems.'),
	(3916, 'disgust', 'When I heard of the assassination of the Indian prime-minister, á\nIndira Gandhi.'),
	(3917, 'shame', 'When I got drunk at a party and made a fool of myself by á\nvomitting all over the place and insulting the people who were á\nthere with me.'),
	(3918, 'joy', 'When I was told that I had passed the exams.'),
	(3919, 'fear', 'When a thief broke into my house at night.'),
	(3920, 'anger', 'When my sister broke my china tea set.'),
	(3921, 'sadness', 'I felt very sad when my son died after a short illness.'),
	(3922, 'disgust', 'I met my best friend\'s husband with a prostitute.'),
	(3923, 'shame', 'When I failed to answer a simple question.'),
	(3924, 'joy', 'When I learnt that I was selected for form I.'),
	(3925, 'fear', 'When I was nearly beaten up by the brother of my girlfriend.'),
	(3926, 'anger', 'When I heard that my girlfriend was talking behind my back and á\nlooking down on me.'),
	(3927, 'sadness', 'When a friend, who has been with me at school, failed to make it á\nto UNZA.'),
	(3928, 'disgust', 'When my girlfriend told me that she was no longer interested in á\nme.'),
	(3929, 'shame', 'I choked on a cold drink in front of girls who were strangers.'),
	(3930, 'joy', 'When I passed the grade 7 exam.'),
	(3931, 'fear', 'When I was told by the doctor, after many months of coughing, á\nthat I had tuberculosis.'),
	(3932, 'anger', 'When a cousin of mine took my bottle of T.B tablets, put water in á\nit and threw it in the dust-bin.'),
	(3933, 'sadness', 'This happened when one of my uncles died just whan I was á\nplanning to go and visit him during the next holidays.'),
	(3934, 'disgust', 'When I realized that my closest friend had said bad things about á\nme when I was not around and had betrayed me by making friends á\nwith my boyfriend\'s other girl.'),
	(3935, 'shame', 'When five of my friends at the secondary school found out the bad á\nthings that I had been saying about them.'),
	(3936, 'joy', 'The time I qualified to enter secondary school.'),
	(3937, 'fear', 'One evening I saw the old guard-man I knew, change into something á\ninhuman for about 5-10 seconds, this really frightened me.'),
	(3938, 'anger', 'When I was mistakenly accused of being a thief when I accidently á\ngave a fake coin at a counter.  I realized this before I handed á\nover the coin, but the man called me a thief and called a á\nwitness.'),
	(3939, 'sadness', 'The day I woke up to find that a kitten I had wanted to keep had á\nbeen eaten by the neighbour\'s dogs.  It had been locked out by my á\nwife who claimed that it had dirtied the sheets.'),
	(3940, 'disgust', 'The day I was forced to use a public convenience place in town.  á\nIt was so filthy that it really made me sick.'),
	(3941, 'shame', 'My mother caught me stealing some food when I was a young á\nboy.'),
	(3942, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I came to know Christ.  That is when I became a á\nChristian.'),
	(3943, 'fear', 'When I broke the window pane of my next door neighbour\'s house.'),
	(3944, 'anger', 'When my brother did not send me the transport money to resume      á\nmy studies in time at UNZA.'),
	(3945, 'sadness', 'When I heard that my nephew had passed away.'),
	(3946, 'disgust', 'When my father thought that I was an unrelaible son.'),
	(3947, 'shame', 'When I stole a book in class and the teacher caught me, the rest á\nof the class laughed at my attempt.'),
	(3948, 'joy', 'When my uncle gave me my first year\'s results.  I opened the á\nenvelope and my eyes ran into two "B+" - in EC110 and M160, this á\nmeant that I had qualified for a major in economics.'),
	(3949, 'fear', 'I turned the knob of my granny\'s two band radio and did not hear á\nany broadcast,  " What ! Have I broken the knob ? How much does á\nit cost ? What if the spare part is not available ? "  --I did á\nnot know how to tune a radio.'),
	(3950, 'anger', 'I peeped into Maurine\'s bedroom and saw two people - Maurine anbd á\nmy step-dad.  I thought, " Why did she break her promises ? Why á\nhad she invited me ? Why do old men go for young girls ? "'),
	(3951, 'sadness', 'When I missed the chance of becoming a graduate in mining á\nengineering, after having prayed one week in the church I was á\nnot even selected.'),
	(3952, 'disgust', 'I stormed into the room, hoping to cool myself with some soft á\nmusic from my three band radio cassette.  There was only young á\nKaley there and he explained, " Your aunt has sold it as she á\nwanted to buy clothes."'),
	(3953, 'shame', 'When a lady I was flirting with told all my class-mates that she á\nwas in second year while I was in first year, everyone laughed á\nand started looking at me.'),
	(3954, 'joy', 'This was when the girl I was in love with accepted my proposal á\nand everything went smoothly, just as I had wanted it to.  It was á\ncontrary to my previous feelings of uncertainty about her á\nresponse.'),
	(3955, 'fear', 'It was when I dreamt that I had encountered Satan, he wanted to grab me á\nand take me to his kingdom.  He was very repulsive and I have á\nnever seen anything like that before.'),
	(3956, 'anger', 'This was when I found out that a cousin of mine had taken away my á\ntrousers without my consent.'),
	(3957, 'sadness', 'When I failed a test at my primary school.  I was then in grade 7 á\nand we were about to take the main exam.'),
	(3958, 'disgust', 'This was when I saw, for the first time, a naked woman á\n(prostitute) run away from a house after having been discovered á\nby the guardian.'),
	(3959, 'shame', 'This was when I was discovered stealing a piece of bread at home, á\nI was very hungry a few hours before supper.'),
	(3960, 'joy', 'I was in grade 7.  We had an inter-house volley-ball competition. á\n In Luapula I was the youngest member of the team and I scored  á\nthe winning goal using my head.  I jumped up with joy and fell á\ndown.'),
	(3961, 'fear', 'I was escorting a relative on a bike, we passed by a dark road á\nwith bushas on each side.  Half way down this road, suddenly, we   á\nsaw a white dog appear from one side.  Before we could do á\nanything, it had vanished and moreover it did not seem to have á\nany legs.'),
	(3962, 'anger', 'The comrade staying next doors insulted me for what he called  á\nthe misuse of his iron.  He called me stupid, self centered etc.  á\nI wanted to punch him but instead went for a walk to the mining á\nschool to cool off.'),
	(3963, 'sadness', 'A close relative was at odds with a very powerful firm.  All his á\nthings had been taken, His dad had died a little before this á\nevent.  He gathhered his children and vowed to give them a good á\nlife with a new start - the words were hollow, he bit back his á\ntears .....I asked to be excused and then went and cried in the á\nloo.'),
	(3964, 'disgust', 'A pig in the well from which we drink.'),
	(3965, 'shame', 'My girlfriend had started going around with another boy.  Her á\ncousin, also a friend of mine, asked her as to who she preferred. á\n Both of us were present and she chose the other guy.'),
	(3966, 'joy', 'I was at school whhen I received a letter from the dean of my á\nschool congratulating me for my performance at the previous á\nyear\'s exam.'),
	(3967, 'fear', 'This was at secondary school, a prefect framed up some case and á\ntook it to the deputy head-master.  I was called by the á\nhead-master and he threatened to suspend me.'),
	(3968, 'anger', 'When I travelled all the way to my former school to collect my á\ncertificate, only to be told that I owed them some money, I knew á\nnothing about this.'),
	(3969, 'sadness', 'My sister was in a hospital, later in the evening we received the á\ninformation that she had died.'),
	(3970, 'disgust', 'When at school I thought that I was going to get the best results á\nin mathematics, but it was someone else who got the prize.'),
	(3971, 'shame', 'When I received a letter from my girlfriend telling me that she á\nwas engaged to an another man.'),
	(3972, 'joy', 'My being admitted to UNZA.'),
	(3973, 'fear', 'While paddling in the river during a storm.  I feared drowning.'),
	(3974, 'anger', 'I entrusted a friend with the delivery of some money to my á\nfather, however he misused the money.'),
	(3975, 'sadness', 'The loss of my mother.'),
	(3976, 'disgust', 'Over an argument.'),
	(3977, 'shame', 'At school - being whipped by the teacher in front of the class.'),
	(3978, 'joy', 'My first kiss.'),
	(3979, 'fear', 'When I saw a ghost.'),
	(3980, 'anger', 'My trouser\'s zipper was open when I was at a public wedding.'),
	(3981, 'sadness', 'When a friend left me and went back home for good.'),
	(3982, 'shame', 'Insulted my girlfriend during a peptalk.'),
	(3983, 'joy', 'When I passed my form three exams.'),
	(3984, 'fear', 'The time I was threatened with expulsion from secondary school (form á\nfour).'),
	(3985, 'anger', 'When I discovered that the people I trusted most were talking á\nbehind my back.'),
	(3986, 'sadness', 'When I heard about the death of my aunt.'),
	(3987, 'disgust', 'When my brother promised me money but he failed to fulfill the á\npromise.'),
	(3988, 'shame', 'I was running in front of a crowd when I slipped and fell on a á\nwet lawn.'),
	(3989, 'joy', 'As the time to get the results drew near I became more and more á\nanxious.  My friend called me and said, " You have passed."  My á\nheart was full of joy.'),
	(3990, 'fear', 'I watched a very terrfying film in LT2.  This film really pushed á\nmy heart out of my body and I was forced to go out before the á\nsecond reel ended.'),
	(3991, 'anger', '" I have been hearing rumours that you have not been allowing á\npeople in your room," he said.  This sentence really shot my á\nheart.  I failed to find the right words, instead I walked away á\nwithout uttering a word.'),
	(3992, 'sadness', 'One Saturday morning I had got ready to go out swimming with my á\nfriends.  Unfortunately the weather did not permit it, so we á\nstayed indoors.'),
	(3993, 'disgust', 'One day I went to town to get my grocery.  On my way back, I took á\na mini bus which was full of drunk students.  I felt very á\ndisgusted.'),
	(3994, 'shame', 'I had gone to aa bookshop to buy some books.  Somehow, I got very á\ncross with the security guard checking through what I had bought. á\n I lost my temper and screamed at him.  Later I felt very ashamed á\nat myself as a lot of people I know were there.'),
	(3995, 'joy', 'When I heard that a close relative of mine had given birth at a á\nvery young age, in a very remote area and had had very few problems.'),
	(3996, 'fear', 'The possibility of having failed the examination.'),
	(3997, 'anger', 'When someone chased me from his house.'),
	(3998, 'sadness', 'When I realized that I did not have the basic things needed by a á\nstudent like me.'),
	(3999, 'disgust', 'When some people, including me, are treated in a way which á\nequates them to an animal or a thing.'),
	(4000, 'shame', 'When someone I know was caught in an "adultery" situation.'),
	(4001, 'joy', 'My girlfriend wrote to me telling me that she was four months á\npregnant and that I was responsible for the "damages".  This made á\nme happy as I longed to have a child to call mine.'),
	(4002, 'fear', 'The shooting started and we all lay down to protect ourselves á\nfrom the flying bullets.  This incident occured on our way to á\nFeira, during the Zambia army patrols in the Rhodesia war.'),
	(4003, 'anger', 'I went to the dining hall and found that the cooks were cleaning á\nthe plates and there was no food for me, and the blue birds  á\n(security guards) were busy eating the food that was supposed to á\nbe for me.'),
	(4004, 'sadness', 'That afternoon I received two messages informing me, one that my á\nbrother was in a coma in the U.T.H suffering (kidney disease) and á\ntwo, that my uncle met with an accident on his way to the hospital á\n to see my brother.'),
	(4005, 'disgust', 'This happened when I went to visit my friend in Chelston and á\nfound him screwing my girlfriend.'),
	(4006, 'shame', 'When I walked out of my room with only my pants on and found my á\ngirlfriend and her female friend looking for me outside.'),
	(4007, 'joy', 'When a girl I wanted very much, said "yes" and fell in love with  á\nme.'),
	(4008, 'fear', 'One evening, when I had gone fishing with my friends, we heard á\nthe roar of a lion near by and had to run for our lives.'),
	(4009, 'anger', 'When somebody stole my brother\'s disco machine.'),
	(4010, 'sadness', 'When my uncle died.'),
	(4011, 'disgust', 'A class-mate answered (accidentally) the call of nature in the á\nclass during a tough mathematics examination.'),
	(4012, 'shame', 'I was double crossing my fiancee and one day she caught me red á\nhanded.  She forgave me later.  I was very ashamed of what I had á\ndone.'),
	(4013, 'joy', 'I was very happy when I discovered that I had passed my first á\nyear examination and was among the thirty students who would á\nmajor in economics.'),
