	(5286, 'shame', 'Saw something stupid and ignorant happening in the countryside.'),
	(5287, 'fear', 'I was very scared when I went to the examination hall for my M.Sc á\nexamination as I had studied a limited partion of the course á\nthoroughly and I was in great doubt whether that would be asked.'),
	(5288, 'anger', 'I was most angry when India lost the Triangular Cricket trophy á\nheld in Australia.  I was so angry that I fought (orally) with my á\nfriend.'),
	(5289, 'sadness', 'I was very sad  when I got the XIIth standard results, when I got á\nlow marks as compared to my friend and I could not get admission á\nto courses like medicine.'),
	(5290, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted at myself when I dropped a vital catch, while á\nplaying a cricket match, and we lost the match; though the catch á\nwas difficult.'),
	(5291, 'shame', 'There is one thing which makes me feel shameful,  when I see á\nfriends of my age group working and earning a lot, when I am á\nstill studying.  A friend I met a week ago after a period of 5 á\nyears is earning more than Rs 3000/ month.'),
	(5292, 'joy', 'When I got my first unknown compound while doing my M.Sc á\nresearch, I was very happy.  This is because my research was based á\non this type of reactions and compounds.'),
	(5293, 'fear', 'I was very scared at the time of the Ty.B.Sc examination as I had á\ndecided to get 1st class results.  I was afraid thinking of how á\nthe papers would be.'),
	(5294, 'anger', 'When my neighbours accused my brother of stealing their á\nrose-bush, I was very angry as he had not touched it at all.'),
	(5295, 'sadness', 'When I heard that my girlfriend was getting married to another á\nperson, I felt very sad.  That day I did not eat anything and á\nkept thinking of her all day long.'),
	(5296, 'shame', 'When I had insulted my father two years back, at that time I was á\nvery angry due to some reasons.'),
	(5297, 'joy', 'This happened a year when I was having a hard time, I got á\nadmission to do research despite obstacles in the procedure of admission.'),
	(5298, 'fear', 'It was the time when I was in no position to secure a Ist class á\nin the M.Sc exam and this was likely to affect my career.'),
	(5299, 'anger', 'I missed an opportunity to go abroad because of some silly á\nmistakes for which I had to suffer a lot.'),
	(5300, 'sadness', 'It was at the time of my M.Sc exam, when I was not in a position á\nto take the exam after having studied seriously.'),
	(5301, 'disgust', 'When I opted for my research field, for them the percentage of á\nmarks was more important than my knowledge.'),
	(5302, 'shame', 'When I was not in a position to control myself.  I had said too á\nmuch and had been cruel with no other than my mother.'),
	(5303, 'joy', 'When I got the first compound through column.'),
	(5304, 'fear', 'When I did not get the compound which is known.'),
	(5305, 'anger', 'When I got low marks in B.Sc final.'),
	(5306, 'sadness', 'When my first love was not successful.'),
	(5307, 'disgust', '[ When mix was coming from column for several days.]'),
	(5308, 'shame', 'When I had been angry at my friend without any reason.'),
	(5309, 'joy', 'It was about a fortnight ago, I was declared successful in the á\nU.G.C exam this year (only four in Bombay succeeded).  My joy á\nknew no bounds.'),
	(5310, 'fear', 'When I was a kid, I always opened the door to greet my father á\nwhen he came back from work.  One day it so happened that his á\nhair was scattered due to over-crowding in the train, and when I á\nopened the door as usual I saw something else.  I was so scared á\nthat I could not talk.'),
	(5311, 'anger', 'This also happened when I was very small.  I was beaten up by my  á\nmother for no fault of mine, I had just beaten up my younger á\nbrother for what I thought was his fault.  I was very angry with á\nmy mother.'),
	(5312, 'sadness', 'After studying a lot for my H.S.C exams, I could not make it to á\nthe medical stream and I felt sad about this.'),
	(5313, 'disgust', '[ Honestly, I have never felt disgust at any situation in my á\nlife.]'),
	(5314, 'shame', '[ Sorry, I was never ashamed about anything in my life.]'),
	(5315, 'joy', 'When I got admission in M.Sc (I) Organic Chemistry, I was very á\nhappy.'),
	(5316, 'fear', 'When I came to know that my exams were on two successive days and á\nthat there was very little time (about 9-10 hours) to study in á\nbetween.'),
	(5317, 'anger', 'I was very angry when my friend lost my practical\'s journal, á\nwhich I needed to study for the exams.'),
	(5318, 'sadness', 'I was very sad when I did not get admission in the English á\ncollege, as I had 1% less marks than they wanted.'),
	(5319, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted when our cricket team manager dropped me from the á\nteam.'),
	(5320, 'shame', 'I was ashamed at myself when I saw that the other boys and girls   á\nof my age earn a lot of money by doing very good and hard work.'),
	(5321, 'joy', 'When I passed the TOEFEL with very good marks.'),
	(5322, 'fear', 'When I was going to take the practical exams.'),
	(5323, 'anger', 'When I was teased by my friend for not scoring good marks in the á\nexams.'),
	(5324, 'sadness', 'When I was ditched by my girlfriend.'),
	(5325, 'disgust', 'When I lost the notes of the lecturer I had borrowed from my á\nfriend.'),
	(5326, 'shame', 'When I was teasing a girl, who turned out to be my brother\'s á\ndame.'),
	(5327, 'joy', 'The moment I got the news that I had been selected for the U.G.C á\njunior national research fellowship.  It was a dream come true.'),
	(5328, 'fear', 'My brother lost his temper and started smashing things in the á\nhouse.  I was quite scared, that something terrible might happen, á\ntill the situation was brought under control.'),
	(5329, 'anger', 'I wanted to go to Bhopal for relief work (gas tragedy).  My boss á\nsimply refused to let me go, I was so angry that the only thought á\nthat came to my mind was to quit the job.'),
	(5330, 'sadness', 'A friend of mine was hospitalized after having been diagnosed as á\nhaving typhoid, he had to forgo his exams and also his ambition á\nof doing a dissertation at the M.A level.  It was a very sad á\nevent for me and I felt very sorry for him so I volunteered to á\nstay with him in the hospital.'),
	(5331, 'disgust', 'There was a family fight in my house some time back.  My uncle á\nhad given me a watch as a present and I lost it.  During the á\nfight he accused me of having sold the watch.  I was disgusted at á\nhis false accusations.'),
	(5332, 'shame', 'I had written a "love-letter" to a class-mate of mine, this was á\nmeant to be a joke.  Unfortunately it fell in the wrong hands  á\nand I had to face the consequences.'),
	(5333, 'joy', 'I have a girlfriend, who is almost like a daughter to me.  She is á\nstudying out of station and I get to see her only once a year.  á\nHer arrival is always a joyous one.'),
	(5334, 'fear', 'While I was pushing a court roller out of a ditch, I slipped and á\nfell down and the roller rolled back towards me -down slope-It is á\na miracle that I still have my legs intact.'),
	(5335, 'anger', 'I was the compere at a party and all my efforts to get the show á\nrolling were thwarted by the immobile, non co-operative guests.  á\nI felt frustation - bordering on anger.'),
	(5336, 'disgust', 'A railways officer, when asked by the ticket checker to produce á\nhis tickets, got very aggressive and started abusing and using á\nhis authority in a very wrong way.'),
	(5337, 'shame', '[ I am quite shameless, not applicable.]'),
	(5338, 'joy', 'When I was successful at my work I was full of joy.'),
	(5339, 'fear', 'When I was treated improperly by someone.'),
	(5340, 'anger', '[ When bad and disgusting language is uttered by people, or when á\nsomeone tries to show what is beyond his own capacities.]'),
	(5341, 'sadness', '[ I missed my twin when I was on the verge of being thrown, which á\nI disliked.]'),
	(5342, 'disgust', 'When Kanishka was blown up, I really felt disgusted at people á\nkilling each other.'),
	(5343, 'joy', 'When I received the best actor award at the inter-college drama á\ncompetition.  It gave me tremendous joy and satisfaction which á\nlasted for several days.'),
	(5344, 'fear', 'When my mother met with a serious accident and there was danger á\nthat she would not survive and if she did she would loose á\nher memory.'),
	(5345, 'anger', 'When an acquaintance of mine beat up another person for no just á\nreason, and thus showed off his power.'),
	(5346, 'sadness', 'When a friend of mine died in a hiking accident.  I was not á\npresent there and only got the news later.'),
	(5347, 'disgust', '[ Do not remember any incident.]'),
	(5348, 'joy', 'I felt this emotion when my name was announced on the radio that á\nI had been selected to come to Lilongwe School for Health á\nSciences to take a training course as a Medical Assistat.'),
	(5349, 'fear', 'I felt the above condition when I took my brother\'s bicycle to a á\nmarket and unfortunately the bicycle was stolen and I didn\'t know á\nhow I could tell the owner about the stolen bicycle.'),
	(5350, 'anger', 'I felt angry when my only pair of trousers was stolen and could á\nnot be able to find out who the thief was or anyone who knew á\nabout the story.'),
	(5351, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when my dear friend was needed from training school á\ndue to his failure in a number of subjects and simply didn\'t know á\nwhat he had to do.'),
	(5352, 'disgust', 'I felt the emotion when I entered a certain ward in the hospital á\nto visit my relative who was sick.'),
	(5353, 'shame', 'I felt the above condition when I was found in a house playing á\nwith another man\'s wife where I was asked questions and I was á\nunable to answer.'),
	(5354, 'joy', 'When I was at school, no one thought I could pass my MCE so at á\nthe end of the year my name was announced on the radio that I had á\npassed. I was the happiest person.'),
	(5355, 'fear', 'I was living with my brother and one day he went away on business á\nand I was left alone to look after the house and the property. At á\nnight thieves came and wanted to break into the house.'),
	(5356, 'anger', 'My young brother took my wristwatch in my abscence and sold it to á\nhis friend at a cheaper price.'),
	(5357, 'sadness', 'I had a girlfriend who lived several kilometers away from my á\nhome. One day she wrote me that she\'d visit me. On her way she á\nhad a car accident and was badly injured. I was very sorry to see á\nher lying in a bed in the hospital.'),
	(5358, 'disgust', 'One of my best friends was found lying flat on the road because á\nhe was drunk and was taken by the police and put in a cell. I á\nwent to see him the following morning, the place was really a á\nmess and was smelling badly. I didn\'t like it.'),
	(5359, 'shame', 'It was my father\'s birthday party when I was asked to bring a á\ntray of tea and other drinks.'),
	(5360, 'joy', 'When I was accepted to study at this school I was very happy.'),
	(5361, 'fear', 'I was moving in the graveyard at 6.00 pm one day and was griped á\nby fear because I was told that ghosts detain people moving there á\nat night.'),
	(5362, 'anger', 'There is a mad boy in our village. This boy hit me with a raw á\npaw-paw in the face.'),
	(5363, 'sadness', 'It was last September when I felt very sad. It was when I heard á\nthat I was not selected to study in the University of Malawi.'),
	(5364, 'disgust', 'In Ward 1A was an epileptic patient who was burnt the whole body á\nand was stinking very much such that the whole ward was affected. á\nFew people could come near him.'),
	(5365, 'shame', 'An out-patient asked me to read for him a certain prescription á\nbut I was unable to do so. The patient was dissappointed and lost á\nhope in me.'),
	(5366, 'joy', 'It was in December last year that I was chosen to come to this á\nInstitution to study as a Medical Assistant.'),
	(5367, 'fear', 'In March I was busy studying during the night I could only sleep á\ntwo or three hours only for fear that I would be weeded and sent á\nback.'),
	(5368, 'anger', 'I once caught a letter in my girlfriend\'s handbag from a certain á\nman. I felt anger.'),
	(5369, 'sadness', 'I was once nominated as an Officer Cadet in the Armed Forces and á\nmy name was cancelled on the list of nominees of those who were á\nsent to Kenya for Training.'),
	(5370, 'disgust', 'The time I went to see one of my girlfriends at Area 18 I found á\nthat she was not there but in the room she was sleeping, in the same á\nroom there were some women visitors with children so the room was á\nsmelling very badly with some faeces and urine in it so I didn\'t stay á\nany longer.'),
	(5371, 'shame', 'It was last week on Sunday that I was walking with my girlfriend á\nalong Kawale road going to town so I tried to stop a car for a á\nlift and the driver didn\'t stop and I felt shame because people á\nwere looking at us.'),
	(5372, 'joy', 'There was joy in me when I heard that I was to take a course as a á\nMedical Assistant.'),
	(5373, 'fear', 'When I saw a dead body in the mortuary I became afraid and I was á\nfilled with fear.'),
	(5374, 'anger', 'A certain Area Party Secretary came home in the morning and said á\nwe had to leave our home and build somewhere and the reason á\nbeing that they wanted to establish a market. The Chairman knew á\nnothing about it and was very angry.'),
	(5375, 'sadness', 'I was so sad when I heard that my Uncle had passed away. He was á\nthe only man who was supporting my parents as well as myself.'),
	(5376, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted with my girlfriend\'s behaviour. She was going out á\nwith other boys who were also my friends.'),
	(5377, 'shame', 'It was a shameful moment when I heard that I had failed my á\nPrimary School leaving Certificate Exam in 1978. My girlfriend á\nwas there when the news was released.'),
	(5378, 'joy', 'When I was in Form 4, at Secondary School, I was elected as a á\nschool Library Assistant and also the leader of Catholic á\nStudents, so I felt very joyous.'),
	(5379, 'fear', 'I broke my Uncle\'s Radio player accidentally and so I feared that á\nhe was going to cut me off from going to his house as well as á\nplaying it again.'),
	(5380, 'anger', 'It was in March 1985 when one of my fellow students borrowed my á\nwristwatch and after sometime he broke a glass of that watch I á\ngot angry when he was telling me but the anger didn\'t take long á\nto fade.'),
	(5381, 'sadness', 'When I was about to write my Junior Certificate Exams, I received á\nsad news telling me that my elder sister had passed away.'),
	(5382, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted with the behaviour of one of my fellow students á\nduring my Secondary School life. He was a habitual noise-maker á\nand caused great conflicts with the teachers.'),
	(5383, 'shame', 'I remember when I was in Standard 6, I failed one of the terminal á\ntests and I told my parents that I had passed but after they á\nfound out from the class teacher that I had failed, I was proved á\na liar.'),
	(5384, 'joy', 'The joy came to me when I heard that I was going to start a á\nMedical course at the Lilongwe School for Health Sciences.'),
	(5385, 'fear', 'The emotion came when I misbehaved at school and the Principal á\nthreatened me that I was going to be expelled.'),
	(5386, 'anger', 'The emotion came when a certain boy opened my locker without my á\nknowledge.'),
	(5387, 'sadness', 'The sadness came to me when I heard that my girlfriend whom I á\nloved so much got married to another man before a rebuff from á\nher.'),
	(5388, 'disgust', 'The emotion came to me when a certain girl who was not polite to á\nher mother hit her sister severely.'),
	(5389, 'shame', 'The shame came when I was beaten by my teacher at school in front á\nof boys and girls some of whom were my friends and a girlfriend á\napart from being classmates.'),
	(5390, 'joy', 'When I was told that I was selected to attend Medical Assistant á\nTraining.'),
	(5391, 'fear', 'When I was told to attend an operation in theatre.'),
	(5392, 'anger', 'This situation happened when my friend John ate my banana which I á\nkept in the cupboard.'),
	(5393, 'sadness', 'When I was told that my father had passed away.'),
	(5394, 'disgust', 'This situation occurred when I entered into a smelling ward.'),
	(5395, 'shame', 'This situation happened when I was found kissing a girl who was á\nmy friend\'s girlfriend.'),
	(5396, 'joy', 'When my father married a certain lady. The reception was held at á\nKasungu town Hall.'),
	(5397, 'fear', 'At night when I was coming from Lingadzi Inn I heard a hyena á\ncrying in the Lingadzi jungle. I was alone.'),
	(5398, 'anger', 'I felt angry when I was told that I had not been selected to go á\nto the University.'),
	(5399, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when I was told to walk out of the classroom because I á\nwas within the row of students who were making noise.'),
	(5400, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when a certain lady spoke words of sarcasm when á\nI was trying to propose to her.'),
	(5401, 'shame', 'When I broke a tea saucer. I felt ashamed. This was during the á\nbirthday of my girlfriend.'),
	(5402, 'joy', 'My girlfriend who had been very far away from me came to my á\nplace. She saw me and ran after me. I didn\'t know that she had á\ncome. I couldn\'t see her. She held my shoulders standing behind á\nme.'),
	(5403, 'fear', 'I was given a wristwatch by my first girl and after two days á\nanother girl of mine also gave me a wristwatch.'),
	(5404, 'anger', 'My girlfriend mentioned a certain girl\'s name who was my girl á\nsome time back and she is no longer mine that she said she was á\nstill mine.'),
	(5405, 'sadness', 'I had been caught red-handed having stolen some paw-paw. I was á\nthen taken the elders owning the paw-paws.'),
	(5406, 'disgust', 'I was double crossing Mercy and Maria. They one day came to know á\neach other. I was found by Mercy red-haded when I was with Maria.'),
	(5407, 'shame', 'I had a girlfriend in the same class I was. I did not do well in á\nmy Exams, but she did satisfactorily well and was taken into á\nanother class leaving me behind.'),
	(5408, 'joy', 'This happened when I was selected to go to Secondary school to á\nstart Form I in October 1980.'),
	(5409, 'fear', 'As I was taking venous blood from another patient I introduced á\nair into the place of puncturing and there was a swelling which á\nis dangerous to the patient hence I became afraid.'),
	(5410, 'anger', 'My lovely girlfriend double-crossed me and so that I found her á\nchatting with another guy.'),
	(5411, 'sadness', 'I really became sad when mother passed away while I was very á\nyoung.'),
	(5412, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted when my brother was arrested because of stealing á\nmoney.'),
	(5413, 'shame', 'I was ashamed when my classmates discovered that I fell in love á\nwith an uneducated girl.'),
	(5414, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I passed my Malawi School Certificate of á\nEducation.'),
	(5415, 'fear', 'When I had crossed Lilongwe forest I heard that there was a rabid á\nhyena just near the path in the forest.'),
	(5416, 'anger', 'I was angry when I heard that my only girl was going about with á\nanother man. So I decided to drop her but later the story came to á\nbe untrue.'),
	(5417, 'sadness', 'When I was not selected to go to the University of Malawi I felt á\nvery sad.'),
	(5418, 'disgust', 'When I was presumed to have stolen maize from the school garden.'),
	(5419, 'shame', 'I once proposed my own niece whom I did not know but I discovered á\nafter she was my girlfriend.'),
	(5420, 'joy', 'When I married my wife and took her home for the first time.'),
	(5421, 'fear', 'When my friend was involved in a car accident.'),
	(5422, 'anger', 'When I was charmed by my relatives.'),
	(5423, 'sadness', 'When my mother died in August 1978.'),
	(5424, 'disgust', 'When I entered the wound intensive care at the Central Hospital á\nin Blantyre which was stinking.'),
	(5425, 'shame', 'When I first failed my standard 8 exams for the first attempt for á\nForm I selection.'),
	(5426, 'joy', 'My friend took me to Civo Stadium to watch and listen to the á\nmusic of the International singer Sam Mangwana. I had no hope of á\ngoing there since I had no money so he gave me the money for á\nadmission.'),
	(5427, 'fear', 'I had fear when I was left alone at the bus depot at night. I had á\nproblems of how to move to this place.'),
	(5428, 'anger', 'I felt angry when I heard that my sister had failed the á\nExaminations which we hoped she was going to pass with á\ndistinctions.'),
	(5429, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when I heard that my girlfriend was double-crossing me á\nwith the boy who is my best friend.'),
	(5430, 'disgust', 'I felt disgust when I saw a friend walking in stagnant water á\nwithout putting on gum boots.'),
	(5431, 'shame', 'I experienced shame when I failed to keep a promise to meet my á\nfriend at the bus depot. He later came and asked me why I had not á\nturned up.'),
	(5432, 'joy', 'The joy came when I first proposed a girl at Secondary School.'),
	(5433, 'fear', 'As I was in a ward one man died and I was instructed to watch the á\nlast offices. But this was my first time to see a dead person - á\nfear came.'),
	(5434, 'anger', 'I was very angry when I heard that my brother was beaten by his á\nfriends.á'),
	(5435, 'sadness', 'I was very sad when I heard about the death of my teacher who á\ntaught me in Standard 8.'),
	(5436, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted to see a person vomitting and I was told to clean á\nthe place where the vomit was.'),
	(5437, 'shame', 'I was ashamed when a certain friend of mine I used to move with á\nfailed to propose to a lady yet we always said to ourselves no á\nlady can refuse our proposal.'),
	(5438, 'joy', 'My sister gave birth to twins, healthy ones.'),
	(5439, 'fear', 'I was looking after my father\'s sheen in the forest. One day á\nwhile playing with friends from neighbouring villages the flock á\nescaped me and went into a far place. It became dark and I was á\nafraid of father. I went home and hid myself.'),
	(5440, 'anger', 'I planned to travel a distance of 20 kilometres on my bike. I á\nplanned this when I was working in the hospital. When I went to á\nthe house I found that a friend had taken my bike without my á\nconsent.'),
	(5441, 'sadness', 'It was in the evening when I heard that my girl went to Zambia á\nand that she would never come back.'),
	(5442, 'disgust', 'A sister broke a cup and when mother asked I was reported to have á\nbeen responsible.'),
	(5443, 'shame', 'One day mother slaughtered a chicken for a brother who had come á\nback for holiday. In everybody\'s absence I opened the foodstore á\nand ate all internal organs of the chicken. When mother á\ndiscovered, we were all called and I was found with hands stained á\nwith soup. I was ashamed being the eldest of all in the family.'),
	(5444, 'joy', 'This emotion happened when I passed my primary school examination á\nand was selected for Secondary School.'),
	(5445, 'fear', 'At primary school I was accused by some boys of being in love á\nwith a certain girl in their class so they had to shout and beat á\nthe girl and the matter was reported to the headmaster.'),
	(5446, 'anger', 'I was very angry when one day I went to see my girlfriend I á\ntalked to her and could not answer back. She was depressed for á\nreasons which were not known to me.'),
	(5447, 'sadness', 'I was very sad when I was shouted at by Uncle and was told that I á\nwas not to be given school fees because I didn\'t go to work in á\nthe garden since I had gone to escort my sister to the bus depot.'),
	(5448, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted when I was told to dress a big rotten stinky á\nwound which, coming closer, made me feel like vomitting.'),
	(5449, 'shame', 'I was ashamed one day when we were found stealing and roasting á\nmaize cobs from Agricultural experimental projects.'),
	(5450, 'joy', 'It was August 30th when I heard on the radio that I passed my á\nM.C.E. exams and I was really happy and joyous because of the á\nevent.'),
	(5451, 'fear', 'I was walking alone along the place where people fear that there á\nare always thieves there and the people who kill their friends á\nduring the night two months ago.'),
	(5452, 'anger', 'I once was accused of falling in love with someone\'s girlfriend á\nwhich was not true because the girl was just a friend of mine.'),
	(5453, 'sadness', 'It was when I failed standard 8 exams while all my friends á\npassed and went to secondary school. In class I was always á\ngetting more marks than they did.'),
	(5454, 'disgust', 'My first day to work in hospital, when I was dressing wounds I á\nwas disgusted when I came across one wound with a very bad smell.'),
	(5455, 'shame', 'One day I was with my girlfriend and other friends were behind á\nus, I fell down because the place was slippery and I really felt á\nashamed.'),
	(5456, 'joy', 'It was when I was allowed to take my wife away from her parents á\nafter being refused for three times on grounds that she should á\nfirst write her examination.'),
	(5457, 'fear', 'When two hyenas made crying noise on the window of my bedroom at á\nhome when I was preparing for my MCE examination during the á\nnight.'),
	(5458, 'anger', 'It was when my Instructor awoke me late at night to get prepared á\nfor the training at Military college when he was coming back from á\nhis personal social activities.'),
	(5459, 'sadness', 'I slept in a tent at the Barracks which caught fire at night and á\nmy best possessions got burnt in there.'),
	(5460, 'disgust', 'It was when my father beat my mother while she was ill for three á\nweeks and now she was recovering.'),
	(5461, 'shame', 'When parents of a certain girl refused to let me marry their á\ndaughter because I was not fit to do so yet the girl accepted á\neverything and later she followed what her parents insisted and á\nshe told me never to talk to her again.'),
	(5462, 'joy', 'This came in when at one time I met a girl who I didn\'t expect to á\nfall in love with me. Fortunately I tried my luck and she accepted á\nmy proposal. At the same time she was giving me a lot of money á\nwhich was just like a miracle to me.'),
	(5463, 'fear', 'When I was travelling at night.'),
	(5464, 'anger', 'I experienced this when one of my friends reported to the á\nHeadmaster that I had gone out for beer, whilst the information á\nwas not true at all. So I had to fight the friend before the á\nHeadmaster.'),
	(5465, 'sadness', 'When I was at school.'),
	(5466, 'disgust', 'One of those days when I was going to school with my brother and á\nhe annoyed me.'),
	(5467, 'shame', 'This was when one of the Clinical officers scolded us in the á\nhospital on how to make beds but we did not deserve to be á\nscolded.'),
	(5468, 'joy', 'That was soon after the results of the interview which nearly á\n9,000 people attended in all the three regions of Malawi. My joy á\ncame after hearing on the radio that I was one of the people á\nselected to undergo the Medical Assistant training at the á\nL.S.H.S.'),
	(5469, 'fear', 'Fear came towards the end of May when the P.T.S. results were out á\nafter hearing the failure of my fellow three friends.'),
	(5470, 'anger', 'I was once this week angry when soemone trying to compress my á\nmind due to his nonsense speech which himself could not tolerate á\nat all.'),
	(5471, 'sadness', 'This condition accumulated in my mind when funeral news was á\nbrought to my awareness, that a close relative had passed away.'),
	(5472, 'disgust', 'A condition in which I was disgusted followed when I lost money á\non my way home from the college.'),
	(5473, 'shame', 'I was very ashamed when I was neglected by a certain friend whom á\nI was thinking loved me very much.'),
	(5474, 'joy', 'It was when I was selected to go to a Secondary school to start á\nform I.'),
	(5475, 'fear', 'It was when I stepped on a python (snake) unknowingly while it á\nwas sleeping near a baobab tree.'),
	(5476, 'anger', 'It was when my friend had stolen my money (K10) and had á\ndisappeared.'),
	(5477, 'sadness', 'It was when my father was taken into detention by the CIDS for á\ntwo years for a reason I don\'t know up to now.'),
	(5478, 'disgust', 'It was when I drunk urine during my childhood thinking it was á\nwater. My friend had urinated in the tin.'),
	(5479, 'shame', 'It was when my father caught me with a girl in dark corners and á\nasked me what I was doing there.'),
	(5480, 'joy', 'Time had struck 8 o\'clock when I heard from the radio that I had á\nbeen selected to Robert Blake Secondary School for Form I. I was á\nvery happy for the selection. My parents and I were very happy á\nand full of joy.'),
	(5481, 'fear', 'My brother had bowel obstruction, having heard that he was going á\nfor surgery, I was afraid he might not come back to life after á\nhearing of the General Anaesthesia.'),
	(5482, 'anger', 'I felt very angry after one driver had run over my beloved niece.'),
	(5483, 'sadness', 'I was away to school (Primary). In my abscence my young brother á\nat home got sick suddenly. My parents took him to hospital. On á\nthe way he died. It came to me as a sad, sudden and shocking á\nnews and I felt very sad.'),
	(5484, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when I went to one of the Central hospitals á\nwhere my hope of getting good treatment was turned down by one of á\nthe doctors who said I was alright despite my feeling pain.'),
	(5485, 'shame', 'I was in my room, I just heard that my Uncle had been caught in á\nsomebody\'s house with somebody\'s wife. He had to appear in court. á\nI went to see what would happen to him.'),
	(5486, 'joy', 'When I heard that I had passed Primary School Leaving Certificate á\nand was selected to go for Secondary education.'),
	(5487, 'fear', 'When I heard that there is teasing and bulling at Secondary á\nSchool.'),
	(5488, 'anger', 'When I heard that I was not to be provided with another pair of á\nmedical uniform.'),
	(5489, 'sadness', 'When I heard that my father had passed away.'),
	(5490, 'disgust', 'When I vomitted a lump of blood.'),
	(5491, 'shame', 'When a certain girl I believed to be my life partner refused an á\nengagement.'),
	(5492, 'joy', 'I met my girlfriend on the way and she joyfully welcomed me on á\nthe way home.'),
	(5493, 'fear', 'One time I set up my journey at night going to a certain bar. On á\nthe way I met my friends and they told me that two people had á\ndied because of heavy fighting. I proceeded on but with fear.'),
	(5494, 'anger', 'An incident occurred to me when I was going home with my á\ngirlfriend. On the way, a man named Banda grabbed my girlfriend á\nin my presence. I was really angry with him and as a result I á\nthrew stones at him and he ran away.'),
	(5495, 'sadness', 'When I found my baby whipped by my Auntie. I was really sad and á\nup to this moment my sadness is still on.'),
	(5496, 'disgust', 'I was really disgusted when I saw one of my friends soiling on á\nhis clothes. I thought he was mad.'),
	(5497, 'shame', 'One day I went for a bath. I took off my clothes and as soon as I á\nhad finished my brother came in. I felt sad and I found no reason á\nwhy he came in.'),
	(5498, 'joy', 'I felt happy when I saw my brother at the bus depot after 3 á\nmonths without seing each other.'),
	(5499, 'fear', 'When we were going to Nkhoma last Saturday the vehicle was moving á\nvery fast, so I feared we might crash since the road was too á\nrough.'),
	(5500, 'anger', 'When they put the blame on me when I scored the third goal at the á\nmatch.'),
	(5501, 'sadness', 'I felt very sad when I lost my three Kwacha at civo Stadium when á\nSam Mangwana was playing some Rumba records. That was not what I á\nexpected, I wanted some Disco records.'),
	(5502, 'disgust', 'In ward 2A there was a patient suffering from Syphilitic á\nParaplegia and had pressure sores. The wounds had offensive smell á\nthat only a few people .... the place.'),
	(5503, 'shame', 'It was when we were beaten or lost the football match by 5-1 and á\nthen I scored the third goal to my own side.'),
	(5504, 'joy', 'On December the 28th I was filled with Joy when I was told by my á\nbosses that I had been selected to attend a course at the á\nLilongwe School for Health Scienced in Lilongwe.'),
	(5505, 'fear', 'It was last week on Saturday night when I was at Mchesi. I feared á\nto cross the Lilongwe River Bridge to come back to School due to á\ndarkness - until somebody had to escort me.'),
	(5506, 'anger', 'It was at Malawi Army, Dormer Squadron, when some of my workmates á\ngot promoted to Seargents (sgts); we were having similar á\nRanks.'),
	(5507, 'sadness', 'It was mid May 1985, When we had a Test on Nursing. My classmate á\nhad an answer sheet, so he tried to peep. The Nursing Tutor á\ncaught him. During this time I was turning my question paper and á\nit made noise. This friend blamed me of causing the whole matter á\nfor him to be caught.'),
	(5508, 'disgust', 'In May somebody blamed me that I made him to be caught while á\npeeping during the Nursing Test which made me feel disgusted.'),
	(5509, 'shame', 'In our class we had a test on Nursing, so a friend from the Army á\nwas caught peeping, by using a paper which had already answers á\nwhich was written by him. So all of us from the Army got ashamed.'),
	(5510, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I heard over the radio that I had been successful á\nin my Primary School Leaving Certificate Examination and was á\nselected for Secondary School.'),
	(5511, 'fear', 'One day I was busy day dreaming along the road and suddenly I á\nheard the sound of jamming car braked behind me. I woke up from á\nmy dreams and it was about to crash me.'),
	(5512, 'anger', 'When I was doing my last year at Secondary School I was robbed of á\nmy clothes, wristwatch and my pair of shoes. After investigations á\nit was found that all the things were stolen by one of the boys á\nin our hostel.'),
	(5513, 'sadness', 'It was on 9th January 1983 when I received a message from home á\ntelling me that my father passed away on the previous day with a á\nhistory of cancer of the oesophagus. This time I was doing my á\nthird year of my Secondary School.'),
	(5514, 'disgust', 'I was stopped from entering a party while I was at School but I á\nhad an Invitation card with me. This was done because they said I á\nwas too young to join elderly people.'),
	(5515, 'shame', 'In 1972 I failed my Examination because of my own crooky á\nbehaviour of dodging from Examinations.'),
	(5516, 'joy', 'When I had an anticipatory honey-moon with my fiancTe.'),
	(5517, 'fear', 'When it was found that I had gone out of the school premises á\nwithout permisssion and at the wrong time.'),
	(5518, 'anger', 'When a classmate hit me on my occipital region when I was busy á\nstudying and concentrating on my classnotes.'),
	(5519, 'disgust', 'When somebody made me touch human faeces.'),
	(5520, 'shame', 'Soiled my short trousers with faeces.'),
	(5521, 'joy', 'When I heard my name being announced on the radio that I had been á\nsuccessful in an interview for admittance for a medical Assistant á\ntraining course. I was really happy and I enjoyed myself by á\ndancing to music from the Radio cassette.'),
	(5522, 'fear', 'One time I was injured when I was playing football at School in á\nBlantyre. I was brought to the hospital while my leg was totally á\nswollen. The x-rays confirmed there was no fracture but á\ncollection of blood n the muscles. I feared when they started to á\nincise the swollen part with surgical blade.'),
	(5523, 'anger', 'One day I was really angry when all my food was eaten by a dog. á\nMy anger was against my mother because she was careless. She á\ndidn\'t keep the food in a hidden and proper place.'),
	(5524, 'sadness', 'One day I came across a certain boy who was intruding my á\nfriendship as lovers with my girlfriend and I was very sad á\nbecause I didn\'t expect that girl to disappoint me I regarded her á\nas being very faithful.'),
	(5525, 'disgust', 'One time at the hospital I passed near the intensive care room. á\nThe offensive smell that came out disgusted me in such a way that á\nI didn\'t even dare to enter the room.'),
	(5526, 'shame', 'At one occasion I was ashamed of being refused after a proposal á\nfor a friendship with a certain girl. I was ashamed because she á\nrefused publically in the presence of my fellow friends.'),
	(5527, 'joy', 'When I was selected to start Form I at Chilumba Secondary School á\nout of the 100 pupils I was among the 4 who were successful. á\nFamily History showed that I had done better than all my brothers á\nwho had passed after repeating for several times.'),
	(5528, 'fear', 'We went fishing some 5 or 8 kilometers off the shore of Lake á\nMalawi. Before we could settle down the lake became very rough to á\nthe point of threatening our lives.'),
	(5529, 'anger', 'I was angered by a classmate who poured soup on to my clothes. He á\nwas trying to use a short-cut method in getting his supper. á\nComing behind my back, he wasn\'t noticed by me and as I was á\nretreating from a hungry congested people I knocked his plate á\nwith my head. He didn\'t accept being wrong but blamed me for á\npouring his soup.'),
	(5530, 'sadness', 'I was sad when my MCE grades were out. I had gone for a football á\nmatch a mile away from home. The mail found me there. I was á\ndisappointed and didn\'t play the other half of the match.'),
	(5531, 'disgust', 'I was dancing Malipenga (traditional dance). I exaggerated the á\nsteps I was supposed to make in the negative way. This happened in á\nfront of spectators. It was bad for our Boma (group) because I á\nwas on the front line where ability is displayed and it is this á\nability that counts when choosing the winning side.'),
	(5532, 'shame', 'News was spread that I had been found doing sexual intercourse á\nwith a small girl. At first this annoyed me but later on I became á\nashamed because many people seemed to believe it.'),
	(5533, 'joy', 'I passed my MCE Examination. at first I was worried but when I á\nheard my name I had joy in my heart and I arranged for a trip to á\nattend a wedding ceremony.'),
	(5534, 'fear', 'I was studying in class at night. I was in Form II by then. There á\nwere rumours about an earthquake. That night dogs were chasing á\none another and passed through the window outside the classroom. á\nThose who saw the dogs thought it was a lion and were terrified. á\nTrying to run away the desks were dragged and there was a shaking á\nmovement. I thought it was an earthquake and jumped out of the á\nwindow.'),
	(5535, 'anger', 'Someone told a lie that I had stolen his money.'),
	(5536, 'sadness', 'My Uncle was beaten by his troublesome son. He fell unconscious á\nand gained consciousness after some time. That time I was at á\nschool; this news reached me through someone.'),
	(5537, 'disgust', 'I felt disgust when I received visitors at an odd hour. I was á\nseriously preparing for Examinations, so I did not appreciate á\ntheir coming.'),
	(5538, 'shame', 'I answered a certain question from Dr. Maqgda wrongly. She asked á\nsomething about Femur and my answer was saying something á\nconcerning the brain. So I was very ashamed amongst my friends.'),
	(5539, 'joy', 'I met a certain lady at Mchesi and I proposed a word of love to á\nher and at the same time she accepted my proposal.'),
	(5540, 'fear', 'My father gave me money for school fees and I didn\'t pay school á\nfees instead I spent it on beer and did not tell him about this.'),
	(5541, 'anger', 'There was a cup final match between Limbe Leaf Wanderers and á\nSilver Strikers and someone promised to give me some money for á\nadmission fee to watch this game. Unfortunately he did not give á\nme.'),
	(5542, 'sadness', 'I had received bad news informing me that grandmother and á\ngrandfather had passed away. The first one to die was my á\ngrandmother and after two days grandfather died too.'),
	(5543, 'disgust', 'It happened that one of my best friends just took my shirt á\nwithout my knowledge, I hadn\'t put it on for many days and I was á\nshort of clothes.'),
	(5544, 'shame', 'I had high-heeled shoes one time, but a certain girl who saw the á\nshoes told me that they were out of fashion and I looked as an á\nold man when I was in those shoes.'),
	(5545, 'joy', 'Passing a very difficult examination which I didn\'t expect - MCE.'),
	(5546, 'fear', 'As we were going to Area 10 a dog chased me. I was afraid it á\nmight bite me.'),
	(5547, 'anger', 'Brother took my money to use for his own purposes.'),
	(5548, 'sadness', 'After hearing the news about the death of my sister, I felt very á\nsad.'),
	(5549, 'disgust', 'After buying a ticket, I lost it before I reached my destination á\nand the bus Inspector dropped me at a place I didn\'t know.'),
	(5550, 'shame', 'I was very much ashamed after a friend beat me at school and I á\nwas defeated.'),
	(5551, 'joy', 'When I was selected to a University College of Nursing.'),
	(5552, 'fear', 'When one of my relatives went out at night leaving me and my á\nfriend alone, I cheated my parents that she didn\'t go out, after á\nthey had heard that she was out, I was afraid that she might have á\nbeaten me.'),
	(5553, 'anger', 'When someone took my writing materials yet I was to write á\nExaminations in a few minutes.'),
	(5554, 'sadness', 'When I failed my Standard 8 Examination for the first time.'),
	(5555, 'disgust', 'When a boy whom I refused to be my lover told all his friends á\nthat I was his girl he has refused me because I was not faithful á\nto him.'),
	(5556, 'shame', 'When someone pointed out that I was proud, yet I didn\'t dress up á\nproperly. This was when I and my friend went for a dnce one á\nSaturday.'),
	(5557, 'joy', 'I felt joy when I heard my name being called on the radio as one á\nof the students who had passed the interview of Nursing and was á\nselected to start Nursing.'),
	(5558, 'fear', 'I felt fear when one night my aunt and Uncle left me alone at á\ntheir house to look after the baby when they went to a party.'),
	(5559, 'anger', 'I felt angry at one time when I was chatting with friends and á\nsuddenly another friend joined us and started opposing any á\ncomment I added to our chatting.'),
	(5560, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when a thief stole all the clothes from my friend\'s á\ncupboard at school (boarding).'),
	(5561, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when I was not given money for lunch at school á\nby my father as a punishment for beating my little brother.'),
	(5562, 'shame', 'I felt shame when I was asked by my cousin that I promised to buy á\nher a birthday present but I didn\'t buy it for her in front of á\nfriends.'),
	(5563, 'joy', 'When I passed my MSCE Exams and was selected to go to college.'),
	(5564, 'fear', 'I was with my boyfriend forgetting that I had left the house á\nunlocked. Unfortunatly a thief came and stole all the kitchen á\nutensils. Thereafter I was afraid of the consequences.'),
	(5565, 'anger', 'My best friend started moving out with my boyfriend. When I heard á\nthis my heart sank because I didn\'t expect that my own good á\nfriend could do such a thing, so I got angry.'),
	(5566, 'sadness', 'I was sad when I heard that my cousin died because of being á\nbewitched by her husband\'s second wife.'),
	(5567, 'disgust', 'My friend promised to take me out for a movie but he didn\'t turn á\nup.'),
	(5568, 'shame', 'I met a woman who was looking for our house. She stopped me but I á\nran away. When I arrived at home I found the same woman and she á\ntold my parents what had happened so I felt ashamed.'),
	(5569, 'joy', 'When I was selected to come here.'),
	(5570, 'fear', 'Somebody told her friend that she would hit me wherever we would á\nmeet.'),
	(5571, 'anger', 'This was when my boyfriend told me that I was double-crossing him á\nwith a certain boy.'),
	(5572, 'sadness', 'When I heard that my friend had started drinking beer.'),
	(5573, 'disgust', 'I went to a party and there were some cakes which weren\'t good á\nand had a bad smell.'),
	(5574, 'shame', 'One day I was supposed to go to a movie with my boyfriend. In the á\nmorning I went to see my Auntie and I didn\'t come back up to á\nevening.'),
	(5575, 'joy', 'When the church choir came one Sunday after being away for some á\nweeks.'),
	(5576, 'fear', 'When I came home late one day. I was afraid I would be shouted at á\nby my parents.'),
	(5577, 'anger', 'When a little brother of mine damaged a cassette.'),
	(5578, 'joy', 'When I had my first boyfriend.'),
	(5579, 'fear', 'I and my cousin went to a filmshow at night. We went without á\nmaking it known to my mother. While we were there at interval, I á\ncame across my mother just close to where we sat.'),
	(5580, 'anger', 'During the Xmas holiday, I and my best friend at Secondary School á\nhad planned to meet at a Cultural afternoon at the Mt. Soche á\nHotel after missing each other for such a long time. When I asked á\nmy mother for permission, she told me not to go for no good á\nreason. I felt very angry with her.'),
	(5581, 'sadness', 'When I was transferred from Chichiri Secondary School to St. á\nMary\'s Sec. School. I was happy at Chichiri as a day scholer and á\nhad made a lot of friends. I was going to a boarding and that á\nmeant parting with my friends as well as my boyfriend for the á\nfirst time.'),
	(5582, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when my cousin decided that she would stop á\ngoing to school saying she wanted to get married. She was only 14 á\nyears by then and she didn\'t understand what she was thinking.'),
	(5583, 'shame', 'When I failed my Primary school leaving Examinations. I never á\nthought I would fail. When I heard I had failed I really felt á\nashamed of myself.'),
	(5584, 'joy', 'I was filled with joy when I heard that I had been selected for a á\nUniversity course.'),
	(5585, 'fear', 'Sometime back, my boyfriend and I were having a walk nearby my á\nparent\'s house. Suddenly we met my grandfather and I was á\nafraid that he would report to my parents.'),
	(5586, 'anger', 'One day I was angry with my friend who went into my drawer and á\ntook a piece of paper on which I wanted to write a letter and á\nused it for her business without my knowledge.'),
	(5587, 'sadness', 'It was shocking news to me when I received a telegram from home á\ntelling me that my grandmother had passed away. I had to go home to attend á\nthe funeral but unfortunately I found that the burial had already á\ntaken place.'),
	(5588, 'disgust', 'I was disgusted with my brother\'s behaviour when he kept throwing á\nthings away because of his anger, after mum had shouted at him.'),
	(5589, 'shame', 'I was ashamed with my biology lecturer when he asked me a á\nquestion and I could not answer it.'),
	(5590, 'joy', 'I wrote a difficult Exam at one time while in my Secodary School. á\nWhen the results were announced on the radio, I came second out á\nof 80 students hence I felt joy.'),
	(5591, 'fear', 'When the week for Exams came. I got afraid as to how I would á\ntackle the questions.'),
	(5592, 'anger', 'Last week a friend of mine called on me and said I was moody and á\ndifficult to persuade. With this I got angry with her.'),
	(5593, 'sadness', 'I experienced this emotion when my grandfather passed away.'),
	(5594, 'disgust', 'In my village there was this tax collector who used to cheat á\npeople and collected more than was wanted, the surplus was for á\nhis family and himself.'),
	(5595, 'shame', 'I felt ashamed when my lecturer said in class that I á\nhappened to be the dullest of all.'),
	(5596, 'joy', 'When I received a beautiful birthday gift form my parents.'),
	(5597, 'fear', 'When I was called for an Interview at Kamuzu College of Nursing.'),
	(5598, 'anger', 'When I damaged my wristwatch which I liked very much.'),
	(5599, 'sadness', 'When my cousin passed away.'),
	(5600, 'disgust', 'When my fellow classmates were involved in a quarrel.'),
	(5601, 'shame', 'When I failed Psychology examination when most of the students á\npassed.'),
	(5602, 'joy', 'I had stayed for months without seeing mother because our á\nholidays were short and my home is far. Some times, mother came to á\nsee me at school, I was very joyful, and I didn\'t want her to go.'),
	(5603, 'fear', 'One day during our clinical practices, we had a very ill patient. á\nUnfortunately the patient passed away. I had seen him dying and á\nit was the first experience. During the night I became afraid á\nfearing the dead body.'),
	(5604, 'anger', 'It was during the beginning of the term. I had K100 and kept it á\nin my handbag. I left the handbag in the wardrobe but didn\'t á\nlock it. Next time I found that K30 were stolen.'),
	(5605, 'sadness', 'My best friend had failed Exams. She had to leave and so we got á\nseparated.'),
	(5606, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when my appointment to meet the E.N.T. á\nspecialist had been turned down. The specialist came from U.K. á\nand went the same day and we do not have one.'),
	(5607, 'shame', 'I had been telling lies and people discovered instantly that I á\nwas telling lies. I felt very shameful and I felt like á\ndisappearing from people.'),
	(5608, 'joy', 'I had an interview for entry into college. The results were to be á\nannounced on radio. After a long period of waiting the results á\nwere released. I had succeded - tension was relieved by joy.'),
	(5609, 'fear', 'When I stepped on a snake at home, it was dark but there was á\nmoonlight.'),
	(5610, 'anger', 'I went to a fair where a guy who was drunk kept bothering me and á\nin the end I got really angry.'),
	(5611, 'sadness', 'When I heard that my Uncle had passed away in a road traffic á\naccident.'),
	(5612, 'disgust', 'I went to a party with my boyfriend who got so drunk and started á\nvomiting. It was so disgusting.'),
	(5613, 'shame', 'We were writing Primary school leaving Examinations when I had á\nfallen at the steps going into the Exam room.'),
	(5614, 'joy', 'I was given a gift by my sister. There were many pleasant things á\nin this parcel.'),
	(5615, 'fear', 'I was alone walking in a deserted part of the city and I had some á\nfear that some men would attack me and rob me.'),
	(5616, 'anger', 'I wrote an Exam and happened to have not done as well as I á\nthought I would. I was angry to myself for not having done so á\nwell.'),
	(5617, 'sadness', 'I lost my purse that had money in it. I was sad until I found it.'),
	(5618, 'disgust', 'I received a letter which was too strong for me. It said I had á\ndone something which I really didn\'t do.'),
	(5619, 'shame', 'A friend of mine was shouting at me in a group of juniors.'),
	(5620, 'joy', 'The day I was told that I had passed my Malawi School leaving á\nExams and I was selected to go to college.'),
	(5621, 'fear', 'When I was travelling home by bus and suddenly the bus hit and á\nthe bus leaned against a wall.'),
	(5622, 'anger', 'I was angry when someone stole a magazine which I had borrowed á\nfrom another friend and locked it in a drawer.'),
	(5623, 'sadness', 'When my best friend promised to come at my house and I had to á\nprepare so many expensive things for her but only to learn at á\nlast that she would not turn up.'),
	(5624, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted one day when, as we were eating, a child á\ndefecated on the table side.'),
	(5625, 'shame', 'I felt ashamed one day when my teacher shouted at me in the á\npresence of my boyfriend.'),
	(5626, 'joy', 'When I had passed MCE examinations.'),
	(5627, 'fear', 'I was afraid when my boyfriend came home because my parents á\ndisapproved him of his coming home. I thought they would chase me á\nout of the house.'),
	(5628, 'anger', 'I was angry when my friends said that I should not receive á\nNursing Science books because there was a rumour that I was á\nintending to leave the college.'),
	(5629, 'disgust', 'When I was a child I broke plates because I wasn\'t given food on á\nthe grounds of coming home late.'),
	(5630, 'shame', 'I was ashamed of being laughed at by my colleagues when I failed á\nto answer a question in the classroom.'),
	(5631, 'joy', 'I was filled with joy when I heard that I had been selected to á\ncome here at Kamuzu College of Nursing.'),
	(5632, 'fear', 'I was afraid to walk through the forest one day when I dropped á\noff the bus around 6.30 pm.'),
	(5633, 'anger', 'I was angry when somebody stole my half petticoat.'),
	(5634, 'sadness', 'I felt sad when my father was sick.'),
	(5635, 'disgust', 'I felt disgusted when somebody told me that my previous boyfriend á\nwas her boyfriend.'),
	(5636, 'shame', 'I was ashamed when my boyfriend went to sit with another girl á\nwhen he invited me to come to watch Drama festival.'),
	(5637, 'joy', 'The time I learnt that I had passed my Malawi School leaving á\nCertificate Examinations.'),
	(5638, 'fear', 'Afraid of a dead body.'),
	(5639, 'anger', 'A tailor ran away with my skirt.'),
	(5640, 'sadness', 'Cooks refused to give me food.'),
	(5641, 'disgust', 'I saw a septic, smelling wound.'),
	(5642, 'shame', 'I was ashamed when I was being introduced to the church á\ncongregation.'),
	(5643, 'joy', 'A boy I had been admiring so much asked me to go out with him.'),
	(5644, 'fear', 'I was playing with friends then I decided to splash some sand á\ninto a car which was moving nearby. The driver got angry and came á\nto report to my parents.'),
	(5645, 'anger', 'Sometime back another girl who was in terms with my ex-boyfriend á\ncame to shout at me at twelve midnight. It was because she á\nthought I was still interested in the boy.'),
	(5646, 'sadness', 'In May 18th, 1984 my boyfriend went to the U.S.A. In December I á\nwas told he passed away. He had cancer of the Oesophagus.'),
	(5647, 'disgust', 'One day I was walking with my boyfriend. We met my ex-boyfriend á\nand out of jealousy he started calling me names.'),
	(5648, 'shame', 'My father who is very quiet discovered I was going out with a á\ncoloured boy. He called me names and was really upset.'),
	(5649, 'joy', 'When I passed standard 8 exams I jumped, rolled over the ground.'),
	(5650, 'fear', 'I felt so afraid when dad fell ill, he had never suffered from á\nthat disease since and I had never seen him as he was.'),
	(5651, 'anger', 'I was furious when the teacher pointed out in class that I á\nwas the quietest girl in class.'),
	(5652, 'sadness', 'It was extremely sad to me when I heard that a patient who I was á\ntaking care of in hospital had passed away. He had some abdominal á\npains.'),
	(5653, 'disgust', 'I felt this situation when a certain woman from a close village á\nshouted at my mother because she didn\'t get what she wanted, she á\nwanted some salt to put in her relish.'),
	(5654, 'shame', 'I was ashamed when I got the lowest result (mark) in class. All á\nthe same I didn\'t worry too much because I knew I would have got á\nmuch better if I had read enough.'),
	(5655, 'joy', 'The time I first saw my cousin who is living in Tanzania.'),
	(5656, 'shame', 'I failed my Nutrition paper which was the paper ending the á\ncourse.'),
	(5657, 'joy', 'I was filled with joy when I heard that I had passed my Secondary á\nschool leaving certificate exam.'),
	(5658, 'fear', 'I was afraid when my mother left me alone to live in our house á\nfor one month.'),
	(5659, 'anger', 'I was angry when my boyfriend did not turn up as promised.'),
	(5660, 'sadness', 'I was very sad when I heard that my uncle had passed away á\nuntimely at home.'),
	(5661, 'disgust', 'One day my friend told me that she had heard that I was moving á\nabout with her boyfriend. I was disgusted with the news.'),
	(5662, 'shame', 'I was walking one day and I met a man who wanted to ask me about á\nmy brother but I didn\'t stop to hear what he was saying. I was á\nashamed when I found him at home and he told my brother what had á\nhappened.'),
	(5663, 'joy', 'When my boyfriend came form Rumphi to Lilongwe for a visit I was á\nvery happy to see him and couldn\'t believe it was him with me.'),
	(5664, 'fear', 'When I dream of anything terrifying I used to have fear for the á\nrest of the day that the dream might come true e.g., being beaten á\n(or eaten ?) by a snake.'),
	(5665, 'anger', 'I had been in love with a certain young man who pretended to love á\nme but one day I found out that he had another girlfriend who was á\nalso a friend of mine.'),
	(5666, 'sadness', 'I wrote a letter to my boyfriend but he couldn\'t answer it in á\ntime so as a defence mechanism I just found that I felt so sad á\nabout it and couldn\'t talk to anyone.'),
	(5667, 'disgust', 'Once I offended a friend, instead of her coming to me to ask and á\ndiscuss the matter she was just telling other people about it and á\nsay all she could about me.'),
	(5668, 'shame', 'I was once chatting with friends. Then some boys came and joined á\nus. These boys took all my 3 friends away and I was left alone in á\nshame without knowing where to go from there.'),
	(5669, 'joy', 'When I heard that I had passed my end of first year exams and I á\nwas ready to enter 2nd year because I felt I had failed as they were á\nvery hard.'),
	(5670, 'fear', 'I broke a window of a neighbouring house and I feared my mother\'s á\njudgement and action on what I had done.'),
	(5671, 'anger', 'The headmistress at a secondary school accused me of banging the á\nclassroom door when I didn\'t in front of the whole class.'),
	(5672, 'sadness', 'I received a message that my elder brother was involved in a car á\naccident and was admitted in hospital.'),
	(5673, 'disgust', 'The carterer refused to give me sugar to add to my tea saying á\nthat there was no sugar whilst it was there, so I left the cafe á\ndisgusted without taking the tea.'),
	(5674, 'shame', 'I insulted my friend for a small reason and after time I realised á\nthat I was wrong and felt ashamed; everytime I meet her I feel á\nashamed.'),
	(5675, 'joy', 'When I was selected to start Form I at Malosa Secondary school.'),
	(5676, 'fear', 'When a thief entered the house in which I was sleeping.'),
	(5677, 'anger', 'When my dress was stolen.'),
	(5678, 'sadness', 'When my grandmother died after a long illness.'),
	(5679, 'disgust', 'When I boarded Yanu Yanu bus I sat near a man who was smoking á\ntobacco.'),
	(5680, 'shame', 'When I refused to fetch water for my aunty while she was busy.'),
	(5681, 'joy', 'I was very joyful when I heard that I had passed the standard 8 á\nexams. The day I heard the news was the day I celebrated my á\nbirthday.'),
